title: salmon and dill
directions: Combine the tomatoes, scallions and dill.
Add your smoked salmon, olive oil and zest.
Let stand together for 1 hour.
Toss with the pasta.
Contains 430 calories per serving.

title: custard pie
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 9-inch glass pan. Be sure all areas are well covered. Combine all ingredients in a blender container and blend 30 seconds. Pour into pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Makes it's own crust.

title: wyatt's baked eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant.
Soak in salted water in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.
Soak dry bread crumbs in evaporated milk plus whole milk.
Saute green peppers, onion and celery in butter until tender; drain well.
Mix the bread crumbs, eggplant and sauteed vegetables.
Add eggs, salt, sage and chopped pimiento.
Blend well.

title: clam cakes
directions: Combine ingredients. Let stand 5 minutes.
Fry like a pancake.

title: rolled pecan cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar and add rest of ingredients. Roll into finger cookies.
Bake at 325° and roll in powdered sugar.

title: porcupine balls
directions: In bowl, combine hamburger, onions, salt, pepper, 1/2 cup tomato sauce, 2 eggs and uncooked rice.
Mix well.
Roll into balls.
Brown.
Pour rest of tomato sauce over balls plus 1 1/2 cans of water.
Cover and cook for 45 minutes on tripod 6 to 8 inches from coals.

title: swiss steak
directions: Flour and pepper the meat.
In a large frying pan, brown the meat and then remove so you may brown the remaining meat.
In the same pot, fry onions and peppers about 5 minutes.
Then add mushrooms, garlic, parsley, bouillon cube and wine.
Return the meat to the pot.
Cook slowly.
Turn the meat every half hour. Should cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours (or the whole meat mixture can be put into a Pyrex dish, covered and cooked in the oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours).

title: easy chili
directions: Brown and drain the ground beef.
Place in kettle or slow cooker.
Add the remaining ingredients in order, mixing thoroughly after each ingredient is added.
(If a thicker chili is desired, drain the fluid from the beans as well as the corn.)
Cook over a low flame or in a slow cooker for at least 3 hours.
This chili is especially good when served with cornbread.

title: quick start breakfast drink
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Whip until smooth. Makes 4 servings.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Place rhubarb in crust.
Mix other ingredients and pour over rhubarb.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
When almost done, about 35 to 45 minutes, top with meringue.

title: apple fritters
directions: Slice peeled apples; add to the batter made from all ingredients.
Drop by spoonful in hot oil; turn.
Serve with powdered sugar on side.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Slice up potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan; cover with water.
Add butter and Pet milk. Cover with foil and cook at 350° about an hour or until done, then add sliced cheese and peppers. Cook in oven uncovered until cheese melts.

title: eldon's green beans
directions: Cut and drain green beans. Add sugar, vinegar, salt to taste, a small amount of diced parsley and a dash of basil.
Heat and add butter for seasoning.

title: apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, nutmeg, flour, cinnamon, and salt. Add apples, mix well. Turn into pastry lined pie plate. Dot with butter. Cover with top crust, making slits. Seal and flute. Cover edges with 2 strip of foil, to prevent excessive browning. Remove foil the last 15 min. of baking time. Bake at 425° for 40-50 min. until crust is brown and juice begins to bubble thru crust slits.

title: oven fries
directions: Peel potatoes and cut them into wedges.
Place the other ingredients in bag and shake mix.
Put potato wedges in and shake to coat.
Arrange on a flat-bottomed pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until done.
The longer baked, the chewier they get. Serves 4.

title: special chuck roast
directions: Place roast in center of heavy foil in roasting pan.
Brush with A.1. steak sauce and sprinkle with onion soup.
Then spread with mushroom soup.

title: milk tapioca
directions: Cook tapioca and milk over very low heat until tapioca is clear.
Mix sugar, eggs, cornstarch, vanilla and salt; add to milk and tapioca.
Stir until this thickens.
When cold, add crushed pineapple and 1 cup cream, whipped.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar, add eggs, sift flour three times with baking powder and salt.
Add liquid and flour.
(Flour first and flour last.)
Put into round cake pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for about 30 to 35 minutes.
Test with toothpick.
Let cool and ice with your favorite icing.

title: egg casserole
directions: Mix cubed bread, sausage, eggs, milk, salt, pepper and mustard together.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch pan and let set overnight.
In the morning, cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top and return to oven for 15 minutes.
Take out and let set for 10 minutes before serving.

title: buttermilk white cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add butter, shortening, vanilla, 1 cup buttermilk and egg whites.
Beat 2 minutes.
Bake in 2 greased and floured 9 x 1 1/2-inch round pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes, then remove.

title: cocoa cream pie or pudding
directions: Microwave Instructions:
Mix together cocoa, sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Add milk.
Mix well, using a wire whisk.
This takes a total of 12 minutes on High to cook.
Stir after each 2 minutes. Easy.
Can also be cooked on top of stove.

title: ham barbecue
directions: Boil hams in water for 2 to 4 hours, until ham falls off bone. When the ham has cooled, pull meat off the bone and shred (by hand).
Combine barbecue sauce, pineapple, dressing and tomatoes in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add sauce to ham and bake (uncovered) in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours to cook down.
Stir occasionally.
Much better a day or two later.

title: shrimp mold(hors d'oeuvres)
directions: Bring tomato soup and water to a boil.
Add unflavored gelatin, dissolving over low heat.
Stir in cream cheese until melted.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add mayonnaise, onion, celery and shrimp.
Pour into a greased, 6-cup mold.
Refrigerate to set.
Serve with crackers.
Serves 20.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Cut stalks of rhubarb in 1/2-inch pieces before measuring. Mix sugar, flour and eggs.
Add to rhubarb and bake in one crust with lattice strips across top.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: crunchy garden slaw
directions: Combine shredded cabbage, celery, cucumber and green pepper. Stir together mayonnaise or salad dressing, vinegar, mustard, sugar, salt and paprika.
Pour mayonnaise mixture over vegetables; toss to coat vegetables.
Cover and chill.
Garnish with pimiento. Makes 8 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, apples and oranges and add sugar to them in bowl.
Dissolve jello and add cranberry mixture to jello.
Add pineapple.
Chill.

title: caramel pecan clusters
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in large bowl.
Microwave, stirring often, until melted.
Add pecans and coat well.
Place on greased cookie sheet in small mounds.
Melt chocolate in glass measuring cup in microwave.
Pour slowly over pecans mounds.

title: spiced cranberry - orange mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water in a large bowl. Stir in cranberry sauce, cold water, lemon juice, cinnamon and cloves.
Refrigerate 1 1/2 hours or until thickened.
Stir in oranges and walnuts.
Spoon into 5-cup ring mold.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm and unmold.
Great for the holidays.

title: california salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Chill.

title: fat-free carrot muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 8 (6 ounce) brioche pans or jumbo muffin pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Place pans in 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder and ginger.
In large bowl with wire whisk, mix shredded carrots, yogurt, egg and vanilla.
With spoon, stir flour mixture into carrot mixture until moistened.
Spoon batter into pans.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool carrot muffins in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove; cool slightly.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Each serving contains 280 calories, 0 grams fat, 1 mg cholesterol and 440 mg sodium.

title: famous pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add salt, well beaten eggs, syrup and chopped nut meats.
Mix well.
Bake in 9-inch raw pastry shell for 1 hour at 300°.

title: pistachio ambrosia
directions: In a large bowl, mix pineapple together and sprinkle pudding mix on top. Let sit for about 3 minutes.

title: hot fruit salad
directions: Drain all the fruit.
Slice the pears.
Pour in casserole dish.
Melt oleo; add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Pour over fruit.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Melt ingredients and boil for 2 minutes.
Arrange graham crackers on cookie sheet (with sides).
Pour boiled mixture over crackers, covering completely.
Sprinkle with almonds or pecans. Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: bierocks
directions: Brown hamburger meat, onion and cabbage.
Drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Roll out biscuits.
Fill with ingredients.
Add biscuits on top.
Pinch the edges to seal in ingredients.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
This recipe will serve 4 people.

title: herbed butter
directions: Mix herbs and butter together.
Press butter mixture into small containers or form into balls.
Different herbs, such as marjoram and thyme work well.
Serve with vegetables, fish, pastas and breads.

title: caramel nut bars
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 c. milk. Mix rest of milk, cake mix & butter. Press 1/2 of mixture into a 9 X 13 pan. Bake 8 minutes at 350 degrees. Sprinkle 1 c. walnuts & 1/2 c. chocolate chips over crust. Top with caramel. Repeat using remaining ingredients. Bake for 18 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix. Make at least 8 hours before serving. Serve with chips or vegetables.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In a large bowl, combine pineapple chunks, cheese, pineapple juice, flour and sugar.
Top with crushed crackers & butter slices.
Bake in preheated oven for 30 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: deep freeze pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers and onions for 24 hours in water and salt. Drain well
and rinse.
Drain well.
Boil vinegar and sugar. Cool.
Pour over cucumbers and onions.
Package for freezer.

title: heavenly hamburgers
directions: Cook everything except cheese together until done. Add cheese and stir until melted.
Spread buns with mayonnaise or mustard and add mixture.
Wrap each bun in foil and heat in 350 degree oven for about 20 minutes.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Combine carrots and water in a large saucepan; cover and cook over medium heat for 20 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Add enough water to liquid to measure 3 tablespoons.
Set carrots aside.
Combine carrot liquid, cornstarch, orange juice, salt, pepper and margarine in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Cook 1 minute or until thickened.
Add carrots; cook 1 minute, stirring well.
Spoon onto serving plates.
Sprinkle with parsley. Yield: 8 servings.

title: barbecue style meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease loaf pan.
Combine first six ingredients with 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Place in loaf pan. Combine the remaining tomato sauce with other ingredients.
Pour over loaf.
Bake 1 hour.

title: berried delight
directions: Mix crumbs, 1/4 cup of sugar and butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Press firmly onto bottom of pan. Refrigerate until ready to fill.

title: carrots elegant
directions: Cook carrots, covered in water, until tender; drain.
Turn carrots into a 1-quart baking dish.
Stir in raisins, oleo, honey, lemon juice and ginger.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated oven at 375° for 35 minutes.
Take out of oven and sprinkle with almonds.

title: easy brunswick stew(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Shred meat or chop. Stir together meat and remaining ingredients in a 6-quart Dutch oven. Cover and simmer over low heat 2 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix the butter, peanut butter, sugar and vanilla.
Roll into bite size balls and refrigerate.
Next, melt the chocolate chips and paraffin in a double boiler.
Place toothpicks into the refrigerated balls and dip into the chocolate, placing on wax paper to harden.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Flour and brown chicken in oil.
Place in baking dish.
In bowl, combine soup with wine and tarragon.
Pour some of this sauce on the chicken.
Add mushrooms and water chestnuts.
Pour on remaining sauce.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mexican corn
directions: Put the corn
and
soup
in
a pan and let it come to a boil. Simmer
for
two
or three minutes.
Add Cheez Whiz and heat until well
blended.
Then
add the rice.
If too thick, add a little water or milk.

title: swiss chicken bake
directions: Put chicken breasts in shallow baking dish.
Cover with Swiss cheese slices, then cover with soups.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and margarine to form dough.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over dough. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: papata
directions: Cook chicken; remove from liquid to cool.
Cook noodles in chicken broth.
Saute pepper and onions.
Mix all together; cook on top of stove (before adding cooked chicken, cut to bite-size pieces).

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix and put in pan.
Bring to boil and pour over above mixture of beans, etc.
Marinate in refrigerator and serve.

title: beef and okra skillet
directions: In skillet, brown meat; drain.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add tomato sauce, undrained corn, okra and brown sugar. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes. Arrange cheese slices atop.
Cover; heat 3 to 4 minutes to melt cheese.
Serves 8.

title: crunchy parmesan chicken
directions: Combine onions, cheese, bread crumbs and seasonings.
Dip chicken in egg/milk mixture and roll in cheese mixture.
Pour melted butter over chicken and bake 55 to 60 minutes at 375°.

title: zesty meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine contents of envelope and water.
Add beef, catsup, bread crumbs and egg. Shape into loaf and place in shallow baking pan.
Bake 45 minutes or until done.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Beat on low speed 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly with rubber spatula. Beat on high speed 3 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into two 9-inch round pans or one 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes for layers, 40 to 45 minutes for rectangular cake, until top springs back when touched lightly.
Cool 10 minutes in pans on a rack.
Remove from pans; cool completely on rack.
Frost as desired.

title: mystery cheese dish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Choose baking pan to fit bread. Slices should be flat, buttered side up.
Completely filling bottom of pan.
Spread grated cheese over it.

title: chex mix snack
directions: Melt oleo in pan (use oblong roasting pan).
Mix all ingredients well.
Put in oven. Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Crumble 1 package of crackers in a baking dish.
Cream together cream of chicken soup, chicken broth and sour cream.
Pour 1/2 of creamed mixture on crackers.
Layer chicken and pour rest of cream mixture.
Crumble 2 packages of crackers on top and pour melted margarine on top of crackers.
Bake at 325° or 350° until it bubbles and crackers brown.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until brown.

title: hot spinach dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (175°C). In a large bowl, combine spinach, stuffing mix, Parmesan cheese, garlic powder, black pepper, Italian seasoning, melted butter and eggs. Shape into walnut-sized balls and place on a baking sheet. Bake in preheated oven for 20 minutes or until heated through and browned.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Stir mayonnaise until no lumps.
Mix all ingredients well in mayo.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Serve with seafood or salad.

title: coconut macaroon cupcakes
directions: Stir together flour and dry milk.
In a small mixer bowl, beat butter.
Add sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add egg yolk and evaporated milk; beat well.
Add flour mixture alternately with 1/3 cup water.
Beat well.
Stir in coconut.
Spoon about 3 tablespoons of batter into each paper cup in muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Mix ingredients by hand.
Roll into small balls.
Refrigerate. Ready to eat!

title: ants on a log
directions: Wash celery; spread the peanut butter inside of celery stalks. Sprinkle raisins on top of the peanut butter.
Eat and smile.

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: Mix sugar, cranberries and pineapple.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Add fruit and marshmallows.
Whip the cream. Blend all together.
Serves 16.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Pour cake mix and Jell-O together; add oil and water.
Beat until smooth.
Add one egg at a time, then add 1/2 cup strawberries.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add sour cream, pecans and raisins.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and vanilla.
Pour half of the batter into a greased tube pan.
Sprinkle with half of the topping.
Pour in remaining batter.
Top with the remaining topping.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Melt the margarine or butter by room temperature.
Set aside. Must be room temperature or cooler.
Beat the eggs until foamy, then mix in the sugar, brown sugar and flour, then blend in melted butter.
Add the chocolate chips and nuts.
Fold together in two deep dish uncooked pie crusts.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: nutted wild rice(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Heat the raisins in 1/2 cup water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Set aside.

title: shepherd's eggs
directions: The shepherd's of Egypt had a very different method of preparing eggs.
They placed them in a sling which they turned so rapidly that the friction of the air heated them to the desired doneness.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender.
Drain and mash well.
Put in Pam-sprayed casserole dish and add other ingredients and top with bread crumbs.
Bake in moderate 325° oven until cheese melts and egg is done.
This cooks real well in your microwave.

title: egg rolls
directions: Heat oven to 350. Cook turkey in skillet over medium high heat, stirring occasionally, until no longer pink; drain. Stir in remaining ingredients except phyllo and cooking spray. Cook 2-3 Minutes, stirring occasionally, until coleslaw mix is wilted.

title: dallas school peanut butter delight
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter (or oleo), milk and salt in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Blend well.
Spread in 9-inch square pan.
Let stand until firm and completely cool.
Cut into squares.

title: party bars
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and water.
Pat into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 22 minutes.
Layer marshmallows, M&M's and peanuts.
Return to warm oven until marshmallows get puffy; cool.
Cut into small squares.

title: cleo's vegetable salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with boiling water.
Add all ingredients; mix well.
Put into jello mold and refrigerate.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Add pineapple and one can of coconut.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes.
When cool, punch holes in cake with a fork and pour cream of pina colada coconut milk over cake.
Top with Cool Whip and another can of coconut on top of Cool Whip.
tags: cream of pina colada coconut milk

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Saute sausage and drain and roll in paper towels.
Beat eggs, milk and salt.
Layer sausage, cheese and cubes of bread in a casserole dish.
Pour egg mixture on top.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: corn chowder
directions: Fry the bacon over low heat until it begins to brown; stir occasionally. Add onion; let cook.
Add diced potatoes, celery, carrots or cabbage and boiling water.
Cook until potatoes are tender, about 10 to 15 minutes. Stir well. Add salt, pepper, creamed corn and milk. Bring to a boil and serve.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: baked red snapper
directions: Marinate fish fillets in Cella for 30 minutes (1 1/2 cups of wine).
Cook chopped onion in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add wine and chopped mushroom stems when onions are half cooked and then simmer until wine is cooked off.
Prepare rice; add onion/mushroom mixture to rice with pimento, almonds and soup.
Mix well. Turn mixture into a greased 2-quart shallow casserole dish.
Slice mushroom caps and place on top of rice mixture.
Then, remove fillets from wine and arrange them closely together on top (do not use wine).

title: coconut macaroon pie
directions: Lightly beat eggs in mixing bowl.
Beat in sugar, water, flour, salt and almond extract, until blended.
Stir in coconut and melted butter.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool.
Serves 6.

title: slow cooker casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in 3 quart casserole.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours or until vegetables are tender, stirring once after 20 minutes.

title: filofil
directions: Cut filo dough into 2 sections.
Melt butter or margarine in pan or microwave.
Pour it over dough.
Put dough on greased and floured pan evenly.
Spread crushed peanuts and almonds on dough. Put rest of dough on top of other section of dough.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until golden brown in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: zucchini and swiss cheese casserole
directions: Saute zucchini in small amount of margarine until just crisp-tender.
Pour off liquid.
Making several layers, use all the vegetables, seasonings and cheese, ending with cheese on top. Bake in a 325° oven for about 30 to 40 minutes until bubbly, hot and brown.

title: chicken wings
directions: Cut up wings; discard tips.
Heat oven to 375°.
Arrange wings in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan in single layer.
Cook 1/2 hour, drain fat, covered, repeat.
Cover with jam mixed with soy sauce.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes until brown and glazed.

title: fruit dip
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours. Serve with fresh fruit (bananas, strawberries, grapes, melon, etc.).

title: pecan pie cake
directions: To cake mix (reserve 2/3 cup) add egg and melted butter. Grease 12 x 9-inch pan; pour batter in and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until lightly brown.
Mix reserved cake mix with other ingredients (except pecans) and pour over baked crust.
Then sprinkle chopped pecans over top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: seasoned chicken coating
directions: Combine ingredients and store in a covered coffee can. (Because the oil may become rancid, store in refrigerator or freezer.)

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, then add beaten eggs.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: jim's potato casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes thin. Boil until done. Drain. Alternate layers of potatoes, onion, soup and cheese, ending with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ice cream crunch
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Put half of this mixture in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Then put 3/4-inch slices of ice cream over it.
Fit and press ice cream together so all of the bottom layer is covered.
Top with the remaining topping and freeze.

title: taffy
directions: Place sugar, water, corn syrup and salt in a saucepan.
Boil over medium heat until the mixture, when tested in a glass of cold water, forms a brittle ball like a marble.
Remove the mixture from pan and let it cool until you can comfortably handle it. Butter your hands and firmly grasp the ends of the taffy.
Pull it as far as it will go.
Fold the two ends together and pull again. Repeat this until the taffy becomes snowy white. Pull out and twist into a long thin rope.
Cut in bite size pieces.
Wrap each piece in wax paper or kitchen plastic.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Melt the butter, blend in the flour until smooth. Gradually stir in bouillon, cook and stir until thickened and smooth.
Stir in milk, chicken, mushrooms, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occassionally. Serve over noodles.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt morsels and peanut butter. Stir in potato sticks.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.

title: cheese cake
directions: Soften cream cheese and beat with mixer.
Gradually add sugar and then add vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill for 4 hours.

title: chocolate party cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add syrup and eggs. Blend in other ingredients.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Spread top of hot cake with marshmallow cream and drizzle with additional chocolate for decoration.

title: robust barbecue sauce
directions: Stir together all ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, stirring occasionally.
Cool to room temperature.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and green pepper until meat is browned.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer all day.

title: lay-a-bed-stew
directions: Combine ingredients.
Put in 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake about 5 hours at 275° or until meat is done.

title: texas fudge
directions: Shred cheese to spread in bottom of pan (ungreased).
Smooth beaten eggs over cheese.
Spread jalapeno relish on top.
Add half jar of picante salsa.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: aunt ethel's tea cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: crab imperial
directions: Mix gently and fill cleaned shells or casserole dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 450° for about 16 to 18 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix
together	oil,
sugar,
eggs
and
vanilla.
Sift together
flour, spices, salt and soda.
Add to first mixture. Fold in
apples
and pecans.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan or loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until pick comes out clean.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add the next 5 ingredients; fold in blueberries.
Spread in a 9-inch tube cake pan.
Cover with topping.

title: jalapeo potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in the jackets in salted water until tender, but not falling apart.
When cool enough to handle, peel and slice and layer in a buttered casserole dish with slivered bell pepper and pimiento.
Salt and pepper each layer.

title: cheese and bean dunk
directions: Cut cheese into chunks.
Place in top of double boiler with soup; heat.
Stir in sour cream and onion.
Heat gently.
Put in dish and serve with Tostitos or corn chips.

title: ham stroganoff("quick and easy")
directions: Saute the ham and onion in 2 tablespoons butter until onion is cooked.
Add mushrooms and soup; stir until heated through.
Add sour cream; heat thoroughly without letting it boil.
(If it boils, it will separate.)
Cook and drain noodles.
Toss immediately with remaining 2 tablespoons butter and poppy seed. Serve ham over noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: champagne sherbet punch
directions: Mix juices.
Add champagne or ginger ale and sherbet.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: biscuit bits
directions: Melt butter in pie tin.
Cut biscuits in quarters.
Sprinkle minced onions and parsley into butter.
Arrange biscuit quarters in butter mixture.
They will be crowded.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake according to the package directions.

title: shrimp and artichoke casserole
directions: Saute
onion, garlic and bell pepper in olive oil.
Add shrimp;
cover and cook 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour in casserole and top with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Beat butter until creamy. Add 1 egg at a time, beating well after each addition. Add coconut, sugar, flour, cocoa, vanilla and nuts. Stir well. Do not beat. Spread into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Spread marshmallow cream on top while hot, as soon as it is taken from the oven. Let cool 20 minutes, then add the frosting.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: Brown beef; drain.
In large pot, mix all ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Makes 3 quarts.
This soup can be frozen for later use.

title: tsukemono
directions: Combine all ingredients and soak any type of vegetable in this sauce.
Cut and serve with hot rice.

title: grilled vegetables
directions: Tear off four squares of foil.
Place 1/4 vegetable mixture in center of each square.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with combined seasonings and cheese.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs (a couple tablespoons each square).
Grill over medium hot coals about 15 minutes.
Turn and cook 20 minutes more or until tender.
Serves 4.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Dried beans may be cooked in the crock-pot without precooking, using a 3-10-1 ratio of water to beans.
Put water, beans and seasoning into crock-pot.
Cover and cook on high, setting 3 to 4 hours.

title: chicken and broccoli alfredo
directions: Grill breasts until cooked through. Cook linguine acccording to pkg. directions and drain. Vegetable can be stir fried along with the olive oil. Blend alfredo sauce into noodles and vegetable. Place onto a large serving platter. Dice or strip breasts and place on top of noodles.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Place 6 Ritz crackers on paper plate.
Put 1 teaspoon of pizza sauce on each cracker.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Put the plate with all 6 crackers and toppings in the microwave.
Cook for 25 seconds on High power.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Layer graham crackers in bottom of dish.
Mix instant pudding, sugar and milk; whip for 1 minute, then add Cool Whip and mix another minute.
Pour mix on crackers, then put another layer of crackers on top.
Heat the frosting mix for 35 seconds.
Be sure to take foil off the can before you put in microwave.
Chill for 1 hour.
Keep stored in refrigerator.

title: swiss steak
directions: Season meat in flour (add salt and pepper to taste), then cut meat into pieces.
Brown onion and green pepper in oil.
Add meat and brown.
Pour tomato sauce over meat and simmer on low heat for 1 hour.

title: fruit and veggie salad
directions: Bring pineapple, 1 cup water and sugar to a boil.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Stir well and let partially set-up.
Add Cool Whip. Stir and let set up overnight.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Drain strawberries; reserve 1/4 cup liquid.
Beat cream cheese, strawberry liquid, strawberries, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into pie crust.
Refrigerate.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown onion and beef together.
Mix all other ingredients in a bowl, then add beef and onion.
Stir together and pour in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: orange pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and oranges together well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Let cake cool.

title: tomato-zucchini scallop
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, layer half of the zucchini, onion, sliced tomatoes and croutons.
Season with half teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Repeat layers.
Top with tomato wedges.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Uncover and sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rose's banana pineapple-nut cake
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar.
Slice bananas.
Add to dry mixture.
Add oil, vanilla, eggs, pineapple and nuts.
Stir to blend.
Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: viola's breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Cut bread into squares (8 per slice). Beat eggs and mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight or for 12 hours.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: italian pizzelles
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix until smooth.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls onto center of preheated grid. Close lid and clip handles together. Allow to cook until steaming stops, about 30 seconds.
Remove with fork.
Allow to cool on wire rack or towels.

title: scallops wrapped in bacon(great for parties)
directions: Place skinned chicken pieces in a baking pan.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Add wine and sliced onion.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until golden brown. Serve with vegetables and rice.
Enjoy!

title: okra salad
directions: Salt and pepper okra; coat in meal and fry.
Crumble bacon; mix with all ingredients and toss.

title: wrapped smokies
directions: Take each biscuit and flatten it with a rolling pin or glass. Cut the biscuit in half.
Place a Smokie on the biscuit.
Roll it up.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Great for brunch or appetizer.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar for 10 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 5 minutes after each addition of egg.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add alternately with milk to mixture.
Blend in coconut.
Turn into well-greased and floured tube pan. Place in cold oven and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mango chutney(relish)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except mangoes.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat.
Simmer 1 hour or until thick.
Watch and stir frequently.
Add mangoes.
Simmer 30 minutes more.
Can or store in refrigerator.
Delicious on chicken and rice or turkey and dressing.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot English pea juice.
Cool.
Mix vegetables and mayonnaise into Jell-O.
Pour into mold.
Chill.

title: peach or cherry cobbler
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Melt oleo in quart Pyrex or casserole dish.
Add milk to dry ingredients; mix well.
Pour into Pyrex dish; do not stir.
Add peach or cherry pie filling to middle of batter; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: clam pie
directions: Simmer clams, juice and lemon juice in saucepan for 10 minutes.

title: oyster stew
directions: Heat oysters and add the rest of the ingredients.

title: yeast dinner rolls
directions: Sift flour, then measure. In a separate bowl, pour hot water over sugar, salt and butter and stir until the butter is melted. In a small dish, dissolve the yeast in the two tablespoons of lukewarm water and add to the butter mixture. Add 1 cup of flour, gradually beating until smooth. Add the egg and remaining flour to make a soft dough. Put in the refrigerator to rise for several hours or overnight. Take out and press down to release air. Shape into walnut size balls; place balls several inches apart on a cookie sheet and let rise until double in size (in a warm place). Brush with melted butter and bake in 350° oven for about 15 minutes.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pierce meat with fork.
Place meat in shallow pan and pour sauce over.
Marinate for 2 hours. Turn meat.
Drain and broil.

title: salsa casera
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate in glass or plastic container.
Refrigerate no longer than 7 days.
Makes about 2 cups sauce.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve the yeast and sugar in the warm water.
Sift the flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Add to dry ingredients the buttermilk, oil and yeast mixture.
Roll out on floured surface and cut.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Use this dough for biscuits, chicken pot pies, quick cinnamon rolls, etc.
This can be stored for a week in the refrigerator.

title: chicken wings
directions: Combine all ingredients and cover 5 pounds of chicken wings with mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 400°, stirring, after 30 minutes baking.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: Dissolve bouillon cube in water; let sit.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces and saute.
Remove from pan.
Saute onion and sliced mushrooms.
Stir in flour.
Gradually stir in bouillon water.
Cook until thickened, stirring often.
Stir in sour cream and chicken.
Heat thoroughly, but do not boil.
Serve over hot cooked pasta.
Serves 4.

title: monterey casserole
directions: Cook rice; place in buttered 13 x 9-inch casserole dish. Spread chilies and half of cheese; layer zucchini slices, then tomato slices.
Mix sour cream with rest of ingredients; pour over tomatoes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes; longer if it has been refrigerated.

title: oatmeal macaroons
directions: Beat thoroughly the shortening, sugars, vanilla and eggs. Sift flour with soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to mixture.
Fold in nuts, raisins and chocolate chips.

title: cornbread
directions: You will need an iron skillet.

title: mulled wine
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot and let simmer, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Remove cinnamon stick and cloves before serving.
Serve hot.

title: crumb cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add vanilla to mixture.
Add eggs to mixture, one at a time.
Beat good.
Mix together flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with milk.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Place cubed bread or croutons in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs; add milk and mustard. (Children cannot detect the mustard flavor.)
Pour egg mixture over the bread.
Crumble the sausage over the egg and bread. Sprinkle the cheese on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Put in cold oven.
Keep covered and bake at 350° for 45 minutes (325° for glass pan).

title: mock sour cream
directions: Put ingredients in blender; cover and run on high (6) until completely smooth, about 10 seconds.
Makes 1 cup.
Use same as sour cream, but low calorie.

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Take from oven; sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Return to oven and bake until cheese is melted.

title: jello lemon pie filling
directions: Mix sugar, 1/2 cup water, egg yolks in medium saucepan.
Stir in 2 1/2 cups water.
Bring to full boil.
Add 2 to 4 tablespoons lemon juice.
Cool some.
Pour in pie plate.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Boil broccoli; drain just as soon as it starts to boil.
Add rest of ingredients.
Microwave for 10 minutes.

title: pepperoni
directions: Mix all ingredients
together and thoroughly, and force into small casings.
Jab
holes
with
fork
one inch apart to allow smoking, curing and
drying.
Smoke
for
weeks
in a smokehouse or brush daily
with liquid smoke while hanging for at least 3 weeks.
If you are not using a smokehouse, cure the pepperoni in a barely warm oven for 24 hours.
Do not cook!

title: italian casserole
directions: Cook in skillet over medium-high heat the ground beef and onions for about 10 minutes until onions are tender, stirring occasionally.
Add spaghetti sauce, water, salt, basil, oregano, sugar and pepper.
Cook 2 minutes to blend flavors.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil and bone chicken.
Mix other ingredients; add enough broth from chicken for sauce consistency.
Add chicken and cook. Serve over rice.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown meat and onions. Add barbecue sauce and pork and beans into pot. Add browned ground beef. Cook 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: banana punch
directions: Bring water and
sugar	to a boil.
Boil a few minutes. Cool. Add
orange
juice	and
pineapple	juice.	Put bananas through blender.
Mix
all together and freeze.
Remove 1 hour before serving.
Add
1 quart soda to 2 quarts punch.
Makes 1 1/4 gallons.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
In 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layer ground beef, Cheddar cheese, green beans and Tater Tots. Beat egg, 1 can cream of chicken soup and 1 can milk.
Pour soup mixture over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until Tater Tots are brown.

title: taco soup
directions: In large pot brown ground beef and onion, drain.
Add all other ingredients except cheese and chips.
Bring to a boil and simmer 30 minutes.
Top with cheese and serve with chips.

title: swiss gruyere souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use a pastry brush to generously coat inside of a 1 1/2-quart souffle dish with additional soft butter; dust lightly with flour.

title: punch with jello
directions: Boil water and sugar into syrup.
Mix jello according to package.
Mix all ingredients and freeze.
At serving time, mash frozen mixture into mush (I use a potato masher).
Mix in punch bowl with 2 liters of ginger ale.
Serves about 25 to 30.
You can change color of punch by using different flavors of jello.

title: five minute ice cream
directions: Pour milk, sugar and vanilla in Ziploc bag.
Zip bag tightly and place bag inside a gallon Ziploc bag.
Put ice cubes around the bag until bag with milk is well covered.
Sprinkle table salt over ice.
Zip bag tightly.
Wrap a towel around the bag and take turns shaking bag gently for 5 minutes.
Remove small bag and rinse well under cold water to remove any salt water that may be on the bag.
Serve, eat, enjoy.....great with a chocolate chip cookie.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Break the uncooked noodles in small pieces and saute in a little oil. Add seed and set aside.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well and form into balls.
Dip into chocolate; place on wax paper to set.

title: stir-fry sauce mix(makes 4 cups)
directions: In 1-quart jar, combine first 5 ingredients.
Add soy sauce and vinegar; shake until blended.
Add broth, sherry and water; shake well.
Store covered in refrigerator up to 2 weeks.
Shake before using.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix all together well.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: one hour rolls
directions: Warm milk; add all the ingredients.
Your dough will be kinda thick.
Roll out; let rise 1 hour (or so).
Bake at 400° until brown.
Brush with butter.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange chicken and top with cheese.
Mix soup and wine together; spoon over chicken. Sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: india cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat well.
Separate whites and yolks, then blend together.
Cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and flavoring.
Add milk.
Beat well. Bake at 325° in tube pan for 1 hour or until done.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown ground chuck in skillet.
In a large saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Reduce heat to low and let simmer for 1 hour.
(Add additional water if more broth is desired or to keep from sticking.) Top with shredded sharp Cheddar cheese, if desired.

title: chopped ham cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Mix well with 3/4 of chopped ham and dressing mix.
Shape into ball.
Roll in remainder of chopped ham to coat.
Cover tightly and refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: apple pie
directions: Put the apples, 1/2 cup sugar, juice and margarine into a saucepan
and cook 5 minutes or until transparent.
Add 1/2 cup sugar
mixed with 2 tablespoons flour and the cornstarch. Cook only
until
thickened.
Cool.
Put
into a pastry-lined pan. Cover
with
the top crust and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: chow mein salad
directions: Just before serving mix soy sauce with mayonnaise and toss with all the mixed ingredients.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Drain English peas.
Mix peas and soup; heat over low heat. Pour in casserole dish.
Cover with onion rings.
Bake in preheated 300° oven until onion rings are golden brown.

title: sandwich main dish
directions: Cut buns in half. Put meat slice in center of bun. Place in Pyrex dish. Sprinkle cheese over and finely chopped onion. Mix eggs and milk together, then pour over buns and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes. Serve with salad and French fries.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter, cream cheese, and powder sugar together. Fold in cool whip.
Put in graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in order listed.
Form into egg shapes.
Melt Hershey bar and chocolate morsels in a double boiler. Dip eggs in the chocolate.
Place on waxed paper until set.

title: linda's chocolate meringue
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 large cookie sheets.
Set aside.
In a small mixer bowl, beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, and continue beating at high speed until smooth and glossy and sugar is dissolved. Fold in chocolate and vanilla.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheets.
Bake 15 minutes.
Remove to wire racks to cool. Do not freeze.
Makes 5 dozen, 25 calories each.

title: sweet muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Fill a 12-cup muffin pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Great as shortcake with peaches or strawberries.
Also freezes well.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown the ground beef and onions. Stir in the soup, 1/2 can of water, mustard, ketchup and sprinkle with brown sugar. Simmer for about 45 minutes or until mixture thickens. Serve on hamburger or hard rolls.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Place chicken in crock-pot for 8 hours.
Boil noodles as directed.
Remove meat from bones.
In a large pot combine chicken noodles and undiluted soup.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Serve with green salad and hot rolls.

title: raspberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spread 1 can raspberry pie filling over bottom of ungreased square cake pan.
Sprinkle 1 box yellow or white cake mix (dry) over filling.
Mix eggs, oil and nuts together and pour over dry cake mix.
Mix with a fork; it will be lumpy. Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Can vary pie fillings and cake mixes.
Apple pie filling with spice cake mix or any fruit pie filling with cake mix of your choice.

title: baked chicken in wine
directions: Mix and pour over cut up chicken and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Serve over rice.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Beat milk and 2/3 cup syrup.
Fold in whipped cream, 1/4 cup nuts and chips.
Pour into a 9 x 5-inch pan.
Cover and freeze 6 hours.
Combine crushed cones and butter.
Press into bottom and up sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Freeze 10 minutes.
Scoop ice cream into balls.
Arrange in crust.
Drizzle with remaining 1/3 cup syrup and sprinkle with 1/4 cup remaining nuts.

title: easy chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken (dice).
Cook broccoli (drain).
Prepare stuffing mix using chicken broth.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with fruits or crackers.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream well sugar, oleo and Crisco.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, then add flour, buttermilk, soda and coconut.
Beat in egg whites.
Bake in three 9-inch pans for 25 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: chicken with corn and tomatoes
directions: Brown the chicken breasts and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients together in skillet, heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 5 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serve over rice, if desired.

title: fried rice
directions: Prepare rice as directed, preferably 1 hour before preparation of rest of dish.

title: quickie peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix ingredients except peaches.
Pour into melted butter, then spoon peaches in middle of batter.
Do not stir.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: zesty meatballs
directions: Combine first seven ingredients; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Cook meatballs in hot oil until browned.
drain.
Place meat balls in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cook over low heat for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Pour sauce over meat balls.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: party cheese roll
directions: Let cheese soften.
Cream together.
Add Parmesan cheese, garlic, Worcestershire sauce and 1/4 to 1/2 cup mayo to make a spreading consistency.
Let harden in refrigerator; form into ball.
Roll in nuts or paprika.

title: christmas cutouts
directions: Mix all together.
Roll out on a floured surface.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: brer rabbit goodies
directions: Mix well together the syrup, shortening, sugar and egg.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Roll into logs.
Chill.
Slice and bake on a greased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all together and deep fry.
Batter should be stiff.

title: stuffed cabbage(hulupki or galumki)
directions: Combine tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce; set aside.
Prepare meat mixture: meat, onion, rice and 1/4 cup of the sauce. Prepare cabbage:
Take bad leaves off the outside and cut out a good portion of the core.
Put cabbage in a large pan with steamer rack (or just a couple inches of water).
Cover and steam until tender, removing outer leaves gradually so the inner leaves get cooked as well.
Lay leaves out on a plate.
Trim core part of the leaf flat.
Take leaf and spoon meat mixture into bottom side.
Tuck, fold and roll.
Lightly grease roaster.
Layer cabbage rolls tightly.
When complete, pour tomato sauce over rolls.
Cover rolls with any leftover leaves.
Cover roaster.
Bake at 300° for 4 hours.

title: blt pasta salad
directions: Combine mayo, chili sauce, lemon juice, broth and sugar.
Stir in cooked Creamettes. Add tomato and onion.
Cover and chill. Just before serving, add bacon and lettuce.

title: international boiled beef
directions: Dissolve beef broth mix in boiling water.
Add all remaining ingredients, but beef.
Bring to boil.
Add meat and lower heat. Simmer about three hours, or until meat is tender.
Chill meat in broth overnight.
Remove any fat that has risen to surface. Remove bay leaf.
Reheat.
Remove meat to platter and keep warm while making Horseradish Gravy.
Surround meat with mounds of well-seasoned cooked vegetables of your choice.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix and bake the first 3 ingredients at 325° for 10 minutes. Let cool.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar.
Then spread on cooled pretzel layer.
Mix strawberries, jello and water and chill a little.
Pour on cheese layer.

title: creamy chicken barbecue
directions: Cook the chicken breast; dice when cool.
Mix celery, parsley and 1 can cream of chicken soup.
If mixture is too thick, add another can of soup.
Spread barbecue on hamburger buns.

title: hot mushroom dip
directions: Saute
in
butter, the chopped onion until transparent; add cut
up
mushrooms	and
cook until tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add thyme.
Add flour to thicken.
Add sour cream and heat through.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Cook flour and milk together until thick.
Cool.
Beat Crisco, margarine, salt, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add to milk mixture and mix well.
Spread this mixture between layers of cake.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt chocolate and butter in large saucepan.
Stir in sugar, eggs, vanilla, flour and salt.
When completely mixed, add walnuts and chocolate chips.
Spread into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Add all other ingredients. (The amount of salt, pepper and garlic powder you prefer.)
Cook slow about 20 minutes.

title: m. t.'s crock-pot special(servings:  8)
directions: Remove all fat from roast.
Place in a crock-pot.
Put peppers on top of roast, juice and all.
Sprinkle dry salad dressing mix over roast and peppers.
Cover crock-pot and cook until roast is easily shredded.
Use your imagination.
Serve at a cocktail party or for Saturday lunch.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well and chill.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: italian beef sandwiches
directions: Roast rump roast in 325° oven, allowing 40 minutes per pound. Roast will be a little on the rare side.
Cool and slice very thin on a meat slicer or take back to butcher and have it sliced.
Save drippings in the pan and add 1 bouillon cube too every cup of water added.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes or until peppers are soft, then add beef and marinate for 4 to 5 hours or overnight.
When ready to serve, bring mixture to simmer. Do not boil, only heat through.
Serve on 3 or 4-inch pieces of Italian bread.
The long, thin Italian or French bread is best.

title: applesauce harvest bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir together thoroughly the flour, soda and 1/2 tsp. salt; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in applesauce, cheese and nuts. Turn into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes; cool 10 minutes in pan.
Remove bread from pan; cool on rack.
Makes one loaf.

title: spritz
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix butter and sugar.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Place dough in cookie press.
Form desired shapes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until set, but not brown, 6 to 9 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: monkey bread
directions: Blend white sugar and cinnamon.
Add quartered biscuits and shake to coat a few at a time.
Put in greased Bundt pan.
Melt butter and add brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel cucumbers; slice thin and salt them.
Put aside for 1/2 hour minimum.
Drain cucumbers.
Add vinegar; use more or less to your liking.
Add sour cream.
Mix.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch; add water and cook over moderate heat, stirring often, until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add jello and dissolve well.
Set mixture aside until it has cooled to a warm degree.
Add blueberries and coat well.
Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate until set.
Add Cool Whip topping.

title: amish friendship starter
directions: In a large, nonmetal bowl, add the ingredients to the remaining batter.
After mixing well, pour into 2 greased and sugared loaf pans and bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Mix onion, pineapple and cream cheese together.
Roll into ball and roll in chopped nuts.
Chill and refrigerate leftovers. Serve with crackers.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Mix well and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs and melted shortening; press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In a large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Toss 1/2 cup chocolate chips with flour to coat.
Stir into cheese mixture.

title: mom's beef stew
directions: In a large kettle place onion with butter and stew meat. Brown on medium heat until done.
Add tomato juice, carrots, celery, potatoes and cabbage.
Add corn and beef bouillon.
Salt and pepper to your taste.
Simmer on medium heat for 1 1/2 hours. Serve with thick crusty bread.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel and wash.
Cut eggplant into slices.
Dip in flour on both sides.
Fry in oil.
Drain.
Place a row in bottom of oblong pan, then cover with spaghetti sauce, then sprinkle with both cheeses. Do another layer.
Top off with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: turtle cake
directions: First, mix the cake as directed on the package.
Spread 1/2 batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Then melt caramels with milk and butter.
Pour the caramel mixture over cake.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Then pour the remainder of cake batter over top and bake 30 minutes.
There is no frosting necessary.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Stir in milk, eggs and melted margarine.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in an 11 x 13 inch Pyrex dish for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: poor man's pie
directions: Break crackers in fourths.
Place in bottom of pie shell.
Mix rest of ingredients; let it make a syrup.
Pour slowly over crackers; let soak awhile.
Place top crust on; bake at about 300°.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10-inch tube or Bundt pan. Mix margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add sour cream to first mixture, alternately with dry ingredients.
Stir in vanilla.
Mix pecans, cinnamon and brown sugar for topping.

title: snicker bar salad
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Stir rest of ingredients into mixture.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: stir-fry cabbage
directions: Put in capful of sesame oil in wok (allow to warm up).
Cut up scallions and peppers; lightly saute.
Add any herbs or spices at this time.
Add cut-up cabbage and curry powder; saute.
Add cut-up tofu.
Let simmer until vegetables are tender, but not too long.
Serve.
Enjoy.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix together powdered sugar, peanut butter, butter, vanilla and salt. Roll into one-inch balls.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream margarine, shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Shape into balls and roll into mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately.

title: favorite beef stew
directions: Coat beef with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in butter and oil mixture.
Brown onions; add carrots, garlic, 1 teaspoon salt, bay leaves, meat and vegetable juice.
Bring to boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Remove the meat; thicken liquid, then pour over meat.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Boil eggplant in salted water until tender.
Drain and cool. Remove skin.
Place in a bowl and chop.
Add egg, bread, salt and pepper.
Fry onion in butter until brown.
Mix all together well. Put in greased baking dish and top with butter and crumbs.
Add tomato slices before crumbs, if desired.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes or until brown.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Mix rice with 2 cups milk in top of double boiler.
Cook over hot water until rice is tender.
Add raisins and butter.
Combine eggs, sugar, vanilla, salt and remaining milk.
Stir into hot rice mixture.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg.
Set in pan and fill pan 1/2 full of warm water.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 30 minutes or until set. Makes 6 nice servings.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and 1 cup flour; mix well.
Put the other cup of flour over fruit and nuts.
Add to batter.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Line bottom of pan with wax paper.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.

title: chip dip
directions: Mix all together and then chill.

title: peanut butter cornflake bars
directions: Mix sugar and syrup and heat over medium heat until it comes to a boil.
Stir the entire time.
Add peanut butter and mix well. Pour mixture over cornflakes and mix at once.
Press into pan and cut into squares or make drop cookies.

title: waldorf slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients with just enough mayonnaise to moisten.

title: taco sauce
directions: Chop all ingredients and place in Dutch oven.
Cook 2 to 3 hours over low heat.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix together and chill.
Keeps great in refrigerator.

title: cheesy bacon burgers
directions: Fry bacon in large skillet until crisp.
Drain bacon; crumble and set aside.
Drain off all bacon drippings.
Add ground beef to skillet and brown; drain.
Stir in bacon, onion, catsup, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over top and heat until cheese melts.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; cut in Crisco with fork.
Add raisins, caraway seed and buttermilk.
Stir enough to hold together.
Knead on floured board a few minutes.
Bake in greased 9-inch iron skillet pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: how to make caramel apples
directions: Place some water in an ovenproof pan.
In a smaller pan, place the unwrapped caramels.
Place smaller pan in pan of water and place in the oven.
Warm until all the caramels have melted.

title: upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt
butter over low heat in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking
pan.
Sprinkle
with
brown	sugar.	Arrange pineapple, cherries
and
nuts
over
sugar.
Blend
Bisquick, granulated sugar, egg,
water,
shortening	and vanilla on low speed 1/2 minute, scraping bowl.
Beat 4 minutes medium speed. Pour over fruit in pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until wooden pick comes out
clean.
Invert
at	once
onto
serving plate. Leave pan over cake a few minutes.

title: wild rice and shrimp creole
directions: In a large skillet or stockpot, saute onion and green pepper in melted butter until tender; stir in remaining ingredients except shrimp.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat to simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.
Stir in shrimp and simmer 10 minutes longer.
Add water if necessary.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Serve with warm French bread.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Cut chicken up into tiny serving pieces; boil 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain.
Mix together brown sugar and the Sake.
Add garlic, ginger, green onions and soy sauce, then add chicken. Marinate 12 hours or overnight.
Barbecue or broil.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken normande
directions: Heat oil in frying pan over medium-high heat while you brown the chicken. Have someone peel and core and slice the apples. Remove chicken from the pan and add butter. Reduce heat to medium. Lay the sliced apple in the pan and add butter. Cook gently for five minutes. Sprinkle them with cinnamon and lay the chicken on top of the apples. Season with salt and pepper. Pour in the cream and cover the pan. Reduce heat to medium-low and let it simmer for fifteen minutes. Pour in the calvados and cook a further five minutes, covered.

title: yellow rice
directions: Put all but mushrooms, salt and pepper in pan.
Simmer until done.
Add mushrooms and season to taste.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Combine avocados (pitted and peeled), finely chopped onion, picante sauce and juice from lemon.
Stir and mash with potato masher until large lumps are gone.
Place in a serving dish and top with chopped tomato.
Serve immediately.

title: prune bread
directions: Cream
sugar
and
shortening.	Add
eggs.
Combine dry ingredients.
Alternate
dry ingredients and prune juice until it is all used up.
Add prunes and nuts and beat until smooth. Fill 8 empty
soup cans half full and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour. Easy to take out of can; slice and serve.
Interesting? You bet, and
it's
good too!
(Don't forget to wash and save your empty soup cans to make this delicious bread.)

title: curry soup
directions: Mix in blender, heat and eat.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and apples in a large bowl. Set aside for a few minutes.
Mix dry ingredients together and then into apples.
Add eggs, oil and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve as is or use favorite topping.

title: deluxe chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken pieces in bottom of deep pan.
Cover chicken with uncooked vegetables.
Add 1 or 2 bottles of Italian dressing (depending upon how much chicken and vegetables you have). Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and bake for another 1/2 hour.

title: best ever pastry
directions: Blend flour and Crisco.
(Do not use metal utensils.)
Add vinegar to salt, egg yolk and water mixture.
Makes 2 pie crusts.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Mix butter with cracker crumbs; pat evenly in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix coconut, pecans and chocolate chips; spread over crust.
Dribble milk over the entire mixture; bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: jo ann's strawberry pizza
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar together and put over crust.
Cover top with pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: aunt mildred's 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water.
Add cream cheese and beat with mixer.
Mix in other ingredients, adding 7-Up drink last. Chill.
Serves 9.

title: ultimate quesadillas
directions: Cook onion in 2 teaspoons hot oil over medium heat until onion is caramelized (about 25 minutes). Stir in sugar and cook 1 minute. Spoon 1/3 cup chicken, 1 tablespoon onions, 1 tablespoon tomatoes and green chilies and 1/3 cup cheese on each tortilla; fold in half. Cook in remaining oil from onions for about 3 minutes on each side or until browned and cheese is melted. The tortillas can be cooked several at a time.

title: orange doodads
directions: Mix thoroughly and shape into balls; roll in fine toasted coconut or nuts.

title: banana crunch cake
directions: Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
In saucepan melt margarine.
Stir in frosting mix and oats until crumbly; set aside.
In large bowl blend in sour cream, eggs and bananas until smooth.
Blend in cake mix; beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Pour 1/3 the batter (2 cups) into prepared pan.
Sprinkle with 1/3 the crumb mixture (1 cup).
Repeat twice with batter and crumbs, ending with crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.
Let cool upright in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan; turn over so crumb mixture is on top.

title: raisins and nut sandwiches
directions: Remove juice from oranges.
Grate the rind.
Combine with remaining ingredients.

title: strawberry bavarian
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries; stir until separated and gelatin begins to thicken.
Fold in thawed Cool Whip.
Spoon into dessert dishes.
Chill about 1 hour.

title: triple fudge cake
directions: Prepare chocolate pudding according to box directions.
Remove from heat.
Pour into pudding pot the chocolate cake mix.
Blend with wooden spoon until moistened.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with as many chocolate chips as desired.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs, then flour and soda (sifted together).
Add bananas and nuts.
Place in greased loaf pan (sprayed with Pam).
Bake in 325 degree oven about 55 minutes. It's simple and easy and freezes well.

title: citrus punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together except Sprite, 7-Up or ginger ale. freeze in plastic containers. When ready to use, place in punch bowl and pour Sprite, 7-Up or ginger ale over frozen mixture.

title: sour cream squash casserole
directions: Boil squash in small amount of water about 10 minutes or just until tender.
Drain off water.
Mix squash with next five ingredients.
Melt 3/4 stick oleo in pan.
Add stuffing mix and stir until browned.
Layer 3/4 stuffing in large 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add all of squash mixture, then other 1/4 stuffing.
Top with remaining oleo.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until edges turn light brown.

title: snappy ice cream sandwiches
directions: Place a large spoonful of ice cream on the flat side of one cookie, then gently press the flat side of a second cookie on top of the ice cream.
Repeat with the remaining cookies.
Serve immediately or store in the freezer for up to two weeks.

title: christmas waldorf salad
directions: Mix white cream cheese with Pet milk; beat in sugar, salt, pepper and vinegar; chill.
Chop or grind cranberries.
Fold cranberries into mixture of apples, celery and nuts.
Mix with chilled dressing.
Serve on lettuce.
Serves 4.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg.
Add flour, soda and salt. Add mashed bananas and nuts.
Bake in loaf pan at 300° for 1 hour. Cool on rack.

title: semolina gnocchi(a variation of the classic potato dumpling)
directions: Boil the milk with half of the butter, a little salt and a pinch of nutmeg.
Add the semolina flour a little at a time, mixing with a whisk.
Cook 15-20 minutes on low heat.
Add egg yolks and half of the parmesan cheese.
Mix well.
Pour into a pre-oiled sheet pan.
Use a wetted rolling pin to flatten down mixture to 3/4 inch high.
When cool, cut into rounds, approximately 1 1/2 inch in diameter.
Overlap discs on a buttered baking dish, so half of each disc is covered.
Sprinkle with the remaining parmesan cheese and butter.
Bake at 400 degrees until golden brown.
Serve while hot.

title: b.l.t.  dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Chill overnight. Serve on toast.
Cut into 1/4's.

title: festive carrots and pineapple
directions: Combine pineapple juice, sugar, butter, cornstarch and cinnamon.
Cook and stir until clear and thickened.
Add pineapple and carrots.
Heat and serve immediately.
Garnish as desired. Serves 4 to 6.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Put all ingredients in crock pot.
If desired tie whole spices in cheese cloth or put in a tea strainer.
If spices are added loose, strain before serving.
Cover and set on low for 2 to 4 hours.
Serve from the crock pot.

title: mandarin orange dessert
directions: Mix Jell-O, boiling water and juice until wiggly.
Beat with electric beater and add 1 pint vanilla ice cream.
Fold in mandarin oranges that have been drained.
Line a medium cake pan with whole vanilla wafers.
Pour mix on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with whipped cream and tinted coconut.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together until well blended.
Add a few drops of red food coloring, if desired (green for lime). Spoon into pie shell and freeze until firm.
Serve frozen.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients at low speed. Increase speed to medium when all combined, then increase the speed by half and beat 5 minutes, adding flour as/if necessary to achieve the consistency you want.
Cover the bowl with plastic and a towel and let rest for 20-30 minutes.
Punch down the dough. Form into 4 loaves.
Cover the loaves with plastic and a towel and let rise.

title: yeast muffins
directions: Place yeast in warm water.
Melt butter; cream with sugar. Add egg and yeast mixture.
Add flour.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Put in muffin tins and bake at 350°.
Will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: potato casserole(microwave)
directions: In casserole dish (at least 3 to 4 inches deep) place a layer of sliced potato.
Sprinkle with thin layer of chopped onion, then sprinkle with thin layer of grated cheese.
Grind pepper over cheese and pour over a little of the cream.
Repeat with another layer of potato, then onion, cheese, pepper, cream, etc.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used up, finishing with cheese and cream layer.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: After browning and draining meat, add next 7 ingredients (including tomatoes); heat through.
Cover bottom and sides of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with tortillas.
Pour meat mixture over tortillas.
Place another layer of tortillas over meat mixture and set aside.
Combine Monterey Jack cheese, egg and cottage cheese. Pour over tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Melt oleo and saute onions until tender.
Butter a casserole dish and line with crackers.
Add onions and soup in layers until full.
Beat eggs and add milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over top. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: banana nut bread 2
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add sour milk and baking soda.
Add bananas.
Add flour, one cup at a time. Add nuts.
Grease loaf pans.
This may all be hand-mixed in one bowl.
Bake in one large loaf pan or two small ones at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.
May be frozen.
Keeps well. Delicious sliced thin and spread with butter.

title: beans and burger
directions: Cook hamburger and onion until meat is done; drain excess fat. Mix with lima beans, kidney beans, pork and beans, catsup, sugar and salt.
Turn into 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake in preheated oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: busy day pork chops for a crowd
directions: Place lightly floured pork chops in a shallow baking dish.
On top of each chop, put:
1 slice of lemon, 1 slice of onion, 1 tablespoon brown sugar and 1 tablespoon catsup.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake for 1/2 hour more.

title: aja's shake 'n bake potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
Shake in the Shake 'n Bake.
Place in casserole dish.
Cut oleo over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Skin the chicken pieces.
Melt margarine in a medium frying pan.
Mix bread crumbs with spices, adding according to taste. Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken pieces in margarine, then cover with bread crumb mixture.
Place in a 10 1/2 x 15-inch pan that has been lined with aluminum foil.
Bake for 60 minutes or until well browned.

title: apple sauce bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°, grease and flour 13x9x2-inch baking pan. Mix ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Bake about 25 minutes.
Cool. Frost with Brown Butter Icing.
Cut into bars 3 x 1-inch.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion.
Drain.
Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Cover bottom with corn bread mix.
Save some to sprinkle on top of casserole.
Mix remainder of corn bread mix with rest of ingredients.
Sprinkle top with corn bread mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown on top.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except bananas.
Before serving, mix in bananas.

title: do-not-peek chicken
directions: Sprinkle rice evenly over 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan. Pour melted butter and milk over rice.
Mix the 2 cans of soup together and spoon over rice.
Lay pieces of chicken in rows over rice and sprinkle with the onion soup mix.
Seal well with foil and bake for 2 1/2 hours at 325°.
Do not peek during baking time.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix together everything except grated cheese and pour into a greased casserole or a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Cover with foil to bake.

title: chocolate covered cherry cake
directions: Mix well with spoon and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix meat with all ingredients except the chili sauce, brown sugar, cranberry sauce and lemon juice.
Mix well and roll into golf size balls.
Make a sauce from the mixture of chili sauce, cranberry sauce, lemon juice and brown sugar.
Place meat balls into a baking dish and pour sauce over meat balls.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken and spinach enchiladas
directions: Place chicken in pot and add water to cover.
Add onion, garlic, cumin and coriander and cook 1 to 2 hours or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken and discard skin and bones.
Reserve the cooking broth and keep warm.

title: seafood quiche
directions: Line crust with double thickness aluminum foil.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes.
Remove foil.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes more.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread crumbs, in a small mixing bowl.
Beat until well blended.
Coat a 22 ounce casserole dish with vegetable cooking spray.
Pour mixture into the casserole dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over the top, covering the entire surface.
Microwave at Medium (50%) for 10 to 12 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in bread and drained pineapple.
Bake in buttered 1-quart casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.
This is a great complement for a baked ham.

title: sugarless bars
directions: Boil raisins, dates, pineapple and water for 3 minutes.
Add oleo and let cool.
Mix flour, soda, eggs and vanilla; add to cooled fruit mixture and nuts, mixing well.
Put in 13 x 10-inch pan.
Bake in 325° to 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese, whipped with honey.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all of the ingredients together, except ice cream.
Spread 3/4 on bottom of pan.
Cut ice cream in thick slices to lay over crumbs.
As it softens, blend squares together.
Sprinkle rest of crumbs on top.
Freeze.

title: hot drink
directions: Dissolve water and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer for 15 minutes.
Do not boil.
Strain.
Serve.

title: spinach dip(an "ohio thing")
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Serve in the center of a loaf of round white bread.
The center of the bread should be cut out and torn in pieces, served on the sides of the bread.

title: down home kentucky dirt cake
directions: Supplies:
1 large plastic flower pot, 1 dirt or garden shovel and 1 cluster artificial flowers.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear bread into small pieces and place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Brown and drain sausage.
Beat together eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Stir in sausage and cheese.
Pour over bread.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
The cheese will rise to the top.
May be prepared and refrigerated until ready to bake.

title: italian goulash
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Place in casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 375° oven until cheese is melted.

title: chocolate peanut buddy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl beat peanut butter and butter until smooth, about 1 minute.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla extract; beat until creamy.
Blend in flour and salt. Stir in 1 cup chocolate bits.
Spread into ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until edges begin to brown. Immediately sprinkle milk chocolate bits over cookie layer.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spread morsels evenly over top.
Cool completely.
Cut into 1 1/2 inch bars.

title: black midnight cake
directions: Grease and flour pans.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Add everything, alternating with water and vanilla.
Bake at 350°, 2 layers for 35 minutes or 9 x 13-inch for 40 to 45 minutes.
Frost with White Mountain Frosting.

title: water chestnuts
directions: Wrap chestnuts in bacon and bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until bacon is cooked.
Use toothpicks to secure bacon, spearing through bacon and water chestnut.
Drain fat and mix ketchup and brown sugar.
Pour mixture over chestnuts and bake for 20 minutes at 300°.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook meat in Dutch oven with water for about 1 hour.
Add all of the ingredients and enough water until the desired consistency is reached.
Cook for another 45 minutes to 1 hour, until potatoes are tender.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; stir until blended.
Add peanut butter and flour.
Mix well.
Lightly grease a cookie sheet.
Roll in small ball and press (crisscross) with a fork dipped in sugar.
