Bake at 350° approximately 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.

title: snappin' turtle cookies
directions: Cream
butter;
gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add
1 egg, 1 egg yolk, and vanilla, beating well. Combine flour,
soda
and
salt; add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Arrange pecan halves in groups of 5 on ungreased
cookie
sheets,
resembling head and legs of turtles. Shape dough into 1 inch balls, and dip bottom edges into remaining egg
white.
Press
gently
onto
pecans to resemble turtle bodies.
Bake
at
for
to
minutes; cool. Spread chocolate
frosting
on
tops
of cookies.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: wonderful shrimp
directions: The amount of shrimp you need in this shrimp dish depends on whether served as appetizer or main dish.
Shell and clean large shrimp, leaving on tail.
Dip into melted butter; dip into bread crumbs.
Bake for 10 minutes in a 400° oven on cookie sheet.
Can be dressed with chopped garlic and parsley.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix and simmer for 30 minutes.
While cooking, stir with a wire whip or slotted metal spoon until well blended.

title: peach dessert
directions: Put peaches and juice in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
sprinkle dry cake mix and nuts over peaches.
Drizzle melted margarine on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool and serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: parsleyed potatoes
directions: Put cold water in large pot.
Add salt and potatoes.
Bring to boil and lower heat.
Simmer until tender but not cracking or crumbling.
Drain potatoes.
Add margarine and parsley flakes and toss until evenly coated.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt stick (cube) margarine* in baking dish in oven.
Mix soup and rice mixture and put in dish.
Layer chicken on top.
Lightly salt and pepper and pour melted margarine over*.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: creamed cabbage
directions: Melt butter in wok or deep skillet.
Saute red pepper for 2 minutes.
Add cabbage and cook for 4 minutes longer, stirring frequently.
Add seasonings and cream; heat for 1 minute.
Serves nicely with corned beef brisket.

title: chili
directions: Brown onion and meat; drain. Add all other ingredients and cook until thick and done.

title: gingered pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple and set aside in refrigerator to chill. Combine sour cream, honey and candied ginger.
Chill.
Spoon over chilled and drained pineapple chunks in individual serving dishes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.
A nice dessert.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Bring stock to a slow boil.
Mix water and cornstarch in a small bowl.
Stir into stock and simmer for 2 minutes.
Add pepper, sherry, onion and soy sauce mixture.
Remove from heat and slowly add in egg whites.
Let stand 1 minute, then serve.
Makes 2 servings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients well by kneading.
Form into small balls. Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Grease and flour 4 loaf pans. Mix all dry ingredients together; mix all wet ingredients and combine with dry ingredients. Bake at 375° for 40-60 minutes (until cracking on top). Remove from pans while still hot. Pierce tops with fork and dribble with glaze.

title: date log
directions: Add sugar to well beaten eggs.
Fold in flour.
Add vanilla, dates and nuts, mixing thoroughly.
Bake in loaf pan at 325° until firm on top.
This freezes well.

title: round steak goulash
directions: Cut strips of steak and flour and brown in butter. Add seasoning, water and mushrooms and soup (all except sour cream). Cook gently until beef is tender, 45 minutes to 1 hour. Turn off heat and add sour cream. Serve on rice or noodles. Serves 8 to 10.

title: vegetable or chip dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: tomato curry  soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Add in curry powder, stirring over low heat for a few minutes to blend flavors.
Add tomatoes and chicken stock.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: audra's chicken pot pie
directions: Combine chicken, gravy and mayonnaise and heat thoroughly. Boil carrots and potatoes in salted water until tender.
Drain. Add peas, corn and chicken mixture and place in deep baking dish. Top with pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Make
pudding
as
directed
using only 3 cups of milk. Fold in	Cool
Whip.
Layer a 9 x 13-inch dish with crackers. Make
a layer
of pudding mix; repeat.
Top with crackers and frost with frosting.
Refrigerate and chill until firm.

title: johnny cakes
directions: Combine egg, sugar and 1 tablespoon plus 1 teaspoon butter flavor Crisco in medium bowl.
Stir in sour milk and baking soda. Add flour, cornmeal and salt.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Cover.
Let stand in cool place for 30 minutes.
Pour remaining shortening on griddle or in large skillet.
Heat on medium heat.
Spoon tablespoonfuls of batter onto griddle.
Brown on one side.
Turn.
Brown on other side.
Serve with syrup, jam or honey.
Makes 18 Johnny Cakes.
Contains 115 calories, fat 4 g (32 cal or 28% of total calories), sat fat 1 g (8% of total calories), carb 19 g, protein 2 g, chol 15 mg and sodium 175 mg.

title: jambalaya
directions: Saute onions, green pepper, celery and garlic in butter.
Add shrimp and meats, about 5 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes and cook 10 minutes.
Stir in rice and seasonings and liquids.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer until rice is done, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: california chicken casserole
directions: In a saucepan, put carrots and onions with water and boil until carrots are tender (15 minutes).
Add cubed potatoes and cook until potatoes are partially cooked.
Make a white sauce with flour, butter and milk.
When thick add cooked chicken.
Drain carrots, onions and potatoes.
Alternate vegetable mixture with white sauce/chicken mixture.
Cover with rest of sauce.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: eggnog cranberry salad
directions: In saucepan combine pudding mix, lemon gelatin and 2 cups water.
Cook and stir until mixture boils, stir in lemon juice, chill until partially sets.
Dissolve raspberry gelatin in one cup boiling water, cook and stir until dissolved, beat in cranberry sauce.
Fold in nuts and celery.
Chill until partially set. Prepare dessert topping according to package directions, add nutmeg.
Fold into pudding mixture.
Pour half the pudding into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Carefully pour cranberry layer over.
Top with remaining pudding mixture.

title: old kentucky onion soup
directions: In bottom of a saucepan, saute onions in butter and olive oil. Sprinkle flour over the onions and stir until coated.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for an hour.
Sprinkle grated cheese on toast slices.
Float a slice of toast on top of each bowl.
Place bowls on a cookie sheet under a broiler until cheese bubbles.
Serve immediately.

title: butter toffee
directions: Use heavy pan.
Combine sugar, butter, half and half, corn syrup and salt in large heavy saucepan.
Bring to boil over low heat, stirring until syrup reaches 300°.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool until firm. Spread chocolate on top of candy.
Sprinkle with nuts and break into bite size pieces when chocolate hardens.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add buttermilk with soda and the vanilla.
Add flour and salt; mix thoroughly.
Stir in bananas.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased and floured bread pan and bake 1 hour (or until done) in 350° oven.
This bread is very moist and freezes well.

title: corn casserole
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Pour in baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Brown hamburg and onion.
Add salt, pepper and desired seasonings.
Add water.
Peel potatoes and cube.
Add potatoes and mixed vegetables.
Cook until tender.

title: mammaw's deviled eggs
directions: Hard-boil the amount of eggs you need.
Crack and peel eggs, rinsing off all shell pieces.
Cut eggs lengthwise and scoop the yellow middles out into a bowl.
Mash yellows with a fork.
Add mayonnaise, mustard and sweet salad cubes to taste (mixture should be slightly thick and creamy, not runny).
Also add a little of the pickle juice for a little extra flavor (a few drops for regular batches and about 1 teaspoon for a large batch).
Fill each egg white with filling.
Top off each egg with a good sprinkle of paprika.

title: lazy day salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients by hand.
Fold in Cool Whip. Refrigerate for about 2 hours.
Add marshmallows if you like. Will keep 2 weeks or more in the refrigerator.

title: rocky road cake
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch cake pan or 12-cup fluted cake pan.
In small bowl mix together nuts, raisins, marshmallows and chocolate pieces.
In large bowl mix at low speed cake mix, eggs, mayonnaise and water until blended.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in nut mixture and pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done (toothpick inserted into middle of cake will come out clean).
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Fluted pan cake should be removed and cake cooled on wire rack.

title: spicy oyster crackers
directions: Mix oil
with seasonings.
Add crackers and shake until covered thoroughly.

title: grandma krivacek's brom bodi
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Saute mushrooms.
Add potatoes, carrots, celery, cauliflower, caraway seed, salt, pepper and beef bouillon.
Add water to cover.
Add butter and flour.
Stir with a wooden spoon.
Cook slowly.
Serve with fresh chives on top.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 45 minutes.

title: $1000 frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat at "frosting speed" for 10 minutes (flavor if desired).

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in 9 x 9-inch square pan (ungreased). Mix milk, oil and vanilla into dry mixture with a fork.
Mix together brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa and sprinkle on top.
Pour hot water over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Serve topped with ice cream.

title: bev's homemade rolls
directions: Put warm water in a large mixing bowl. Add yeast, sugar, salt, shortening and beaten egg and mix well. Add about 4 cups of flour and mix in with a large spoon. Gradually add the rest of the flour and mix by hand until mixture is neither sticky nor dry. Cover and allow to rise until double in size. Punch down and make into rolls approximately 1 1/2-inches in diameter; allow to rise again. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. Best served warm.

title: ham cheesies
directions: Grind ham, cheese, onion, green pepper and pickles.
Mix together.
Spread open-face on potato buns.
Put under broiler. When hot, put tops of rolls on and brown some more. Serve while hot.

title: kansas city dump cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread ingredients in pan in listed order, except butter.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake 60 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate pie filling(diabetic, sugar-free)
directions: Combine first six ingredients and cook until filling comes to a boil.
Add vanilla when filling is removed from fire.
When cool, add NutraSweet and pour in cooked pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip, whipped cream or meringue.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Cream together cream cheese, dressing and mayonnaise.
Peel and slice cucumbers.
Spread cheese mixture on the party rye.
Top with cucumber slice.
Sprinkle dill weed on top.

title: german chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening and add eggs, flavors and buttermilk.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Then add German chocolate that has been softened in warm oven or in double boiler.
Blend together well.
Cook in 9-inch stem pan that has been well-greased and dusted with flour.
Cook about 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Remove cake from pan while still hot and place under a tight fitting cake cover and leave until cold.

title: individual baked alaskas
directions: Place pineapple slices
on
a Pam-sprayed baking sheet. Freeze until firm.
After frozen,
top each slice with a scoop of sherbet and freeze again
until
firm.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until
foamy
(using
high
speed
on electric mixer). Gradually add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, and beat until stiff peaks form and
sugar
is
dissolved
(2 to 4 minutes).
Fold in extract.

title: sesame ginger chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl.
Stir well and set aside.
Place chicken on grill over medium to hot coals.
Cook 4 minutes on each side, basting frequently with mixture.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: meat sauce for spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, celery, and tomatoes. Add remaining ingredients and simmer 2 1/2 hours. Stir frequently. If sauce becomes too thick, add small amount of water. Serve over hot cooked spaghetti. Serves 6.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and onions until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place chicken and vegetables in small baking dish.
Sprinkle with spices and bake for 1/2 hour.

title: mom's butter scotch pie
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar; then add milk and remaining ingredients.
Cook until thick; cool.
Fill baked pie shell and cover with meringue.

title: bhagaray baigan
directions: Wash and slit the eggplants into quarters without removing the stem.
Deep-fry in medium-hot oil until brown in color.
Drain on paper towels. Lightly roast the peanuts and sesame seeds. Grind peanuts, sesame seeds and red chilies to a smooth paste in a small coffee grinder.
Slit green chilies and cut into one inch long pieces.
Boil tamarind in 1 cup of water for 5 minutes and strain to get pulp.

title: cottage cheese croquettes
directions: Combine cottage cheese, crumbs, nut meats and seasonings.
Add milk and mix well.
Form into croquettes and dip into mixture of egg and 2 tablespoons milk, then dip into crumbs.

title: beef and broccoli
directions: In a skillet, in hot oil, brown beef with garlic.
Add onion and broccoli, cook until tender-crisp.
Stir in soup, water and soy sauce.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Serve over noodles.
Serves 4.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg, beating well. Beat in dry ingredients that have been sifted together alternately with the milk.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round pans and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely.
After you have stacked and spread the jam between layers, sift powdered sugar over top layer.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Fill bottom of crust with peaches. Cream butter and sugar. Add flour, egg and vanilla. Spread over peaches. Bake at 300 degrees for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt oleo and peanut butter together.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in powdered sugar.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch or larger pan.
Cool and cut.

title: yam 'n cranberry casserole
directions: Combine cranberries, sugar, orange slices, pecan halves, orange juice and spices in 2 quart casserole.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 30 minutes.
Stir yams into cranberry mixture; bake until hot through, about 15 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: rick's favorite cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Pour into 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: creamy onion dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well and chill.
Serve with assorted vegetable dippers or potato chips.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix everything together, except jello.
When mixed well, fold in jello.
Chill and serve.

title: essie's cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream together butter and sugar until fluffy. Stir sifted dry ingredients in alternately with milk. Beat until smooth. Pour into loaf pan or casserole.
Spoon fruit over batter; sprinkle with sugar.
Pour fruit juice over top. Bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all and mix.
Chill for 1 hour.
Makes six servings.

title: missy lemon marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients in a glass bowl.
Mix well.

title: curry muffins
directions: Mix together; spread on muffins.
Broil until bubbly.
Cut into fourths and serve.

title: frozen pie
directions: Fill pie crust with softened ice cream.
Cover with whipped cream.
Place walnuts, pecans or other fruit or nuts that are suitable for your selection of ice cream in the whipped cream. Keep in freezer until ready to serve.
This is an easy and popular summer dessert!

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Mix all ingredients well and pour in a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cassoulet
directions: Soak beans overnight in large kettle in water to cover (or cover with water, bring to a boil, simmer 2 minutes, remove from heat and let stand 1 hour).
Add all other ingredients and more water if needed to cover beans about 1/2 inch.
Partially cover and simmer slowly until beans are almost but not quite done.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place hash brown potatoes in large, flat (about 9 x 12-inch) baking dish.
Mix next 6 ingredients and pour on top of potatoes. Top with bread crumbs, mixed with 1/4 cup oleo.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: 7 layer mexican dip
directions: Mix taco seasoning with sour cream; put on last.
In spring-form pan, layer in order.
Chill for few hours.
Remove side of pan and serve with tortilla chips.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles as directed; rinse, drain and set aside. Using a large skillet, brown onion and then brown ground beef. Stir in celery salt, sweet basil, garlic powder and pepper. Then add tomato sauce and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: butterfinger bars
directions: Mix on low speed until crumbly.
Press into buttered 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool slightly. Frost.

title: dean's mom's pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices.
Blend.
Add eggs and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: In 9 x 11 inch cake pan, chop lettuce, green onions and bell pepper.
Mix together and layer on bottom of pan.
Spread layer of thawed peas on lettuce.
Spread thin layer of mayonnaise onto peas.
Top with shredded cheese and bacon bits.
Cover and chill 1-2 hours before serving.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, vanilla and lemon extract until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour, salt, cream of tartar and baking soda.
Combine preserves and sour cream.
Add this to dry ingredients alternately with creamed mixture, beating well after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans (5 small or 2 large pans).
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool on wire racks.

title: yum-yum cake
directions: Mix together ingredients and bake 20 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Drain spinach and artichokes.
Cut artichokes in half and place them in a flat baking dish.
Saute onion in oleo.
Add cream cheese and cook on medium heat until melted.
Add spinach and mix well.
Pour over the artichokes and top with bread crumbs.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Casserole can be made ahead of time and refrigerated until ready to be cooked.
If it is very cold, cook about 5 minutes longer until hot and bread crumbs are browned.
We fine it almost as good as when the artichokes are eliminated and the canned spinach is just as good as frozen.

title: chili
directions: Put all ingredients in slow cooker; stir thoroughly.
Cover and cook on low, 6 to 8 hours.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hungry jack casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain well.
Add salt, pork and beans, brown sugar, barbecue sauce and onion (as much as you like).
Mix well; pour into a casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Cut the biscuits in half and place, cut edge down, all around and over the mixture.
Top this with grated cheese (as much as you like). Place in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes, or until biscuits are brown and cheese is melted.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix well bananas, sugar and Crisco.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into baking loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Cook chicken until tender, debone chicken breasts.
Roll and wrap with bacon.
Mix sour cream and mushroom soup.
Pour over chicken in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until tender.
Serve with rice.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Cream the cream cheese and milk. Dilute chicken bouillon cube in water.
Put all ingredients together.
Add chopped broccoli, lemon juice, salt and pepper. Cook for about 30 minutes.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Combine and put in buttered casserole.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of grated cheese and 1/2 cup French fried onion rings on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Spray inside of slow cooker with cooking spray.
Pour pie filling into cooker.
Beat remaining ingredients with spoon until smooth.
Spread batter over pie filling.
Cover and cook on high for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: "chinese mushroom soup"
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients into a small Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add bamboo shoots and peas.
Continue cooking for 4 minutes.

title: chocoholic brownies(heart safe)
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, cocoa and salt.
Add the rest of the ingredients and stir until just mixed.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 20 to 25 minutes. While still warm, prepare icing.

title: lemon bread(prep:  20 minutes.  bake:  45 minutes. makes:  12 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease three 5 3/4 x 3 1/4-inch metal mini loaf pans.

title: chicken spaghetti for 20
directions: Boil fryers, bay leaves, celery and onion in salted and peppered
water.
When
meat
is done, skin and cut into small pieces.
Reserve the broth.

title: caramel nut acorns
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, heat margarine and brown sugar until margarine melts; stir until smooth.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, syrup, flour, salt, vanilla, butter and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: drop cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop onto baking sheet from teaspoon.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Place water and chocolate in small saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until melted.
Remove from heat; stir in sugar and salt.
Return to medium heat and cook for about 8 minutes or until thick, stirring constantly.
Move from heat and stir in margarine and vanilla.
Serve warm over ice cream.

title: pommes au four(potatoes au gratin, french way)
directions: Pare potatoes; slice thinly and cook in small amount of salted water until tender. Warm cream on low heat and add instant beef broth and 1 clove crushed garlic. Place layer of potatoes in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole and cover with 1/2 of cream mixture. Repeat layers and top with cheese. Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes or until cheese is golden. Serves 4 to 6.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to box directions.
Add the shrimp, onion and pickles.
Add celery seed, dill weed, salt and pepper to taste.
Add enough mayonnaise to hold together; toss gently.

title: oatmeal buttermilk pancakes
directions: Combine oatmeal, buttermilk and egg whites and let stand for at least 1/2 hour or refrigerate up to 24 hours.
Add remaining ingredients and stir the batter just until the dry ingredients are moistened.
Bake on a hot, lightly oiled griddle.
Makes 16 pancakes (4-inches each).

title: autumn bisque
directions: Saute vegetables and apples in butter.
Stir in flour and cook.
Add stock and simmer 10 minutes.
Add squash and cook.
Add seasonings.
Add cider and cream; heat through.
Remove from heat. Stir in cheeses.
Garnish with croutons.

title: walnut pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in saucepan over low heat until butter is melted.
Beat eggs with vanilla.
Let hot mixture cool, then add beaten eggs.
Mix well; pour into pie plate.
Top with nuts. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: honey buns
directions: Bring milk to boiling point; remove from heat. Add the 2 tablespoons sugar, shortening, salt, egg and yeast. Stir and mix well; turn out on well floured board and knead lightly until smooth. Cover and let stand 10 minutes.

title: reese's squares
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter and chocolate.
Melt butter; add to mixture.
Mix and pack in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Melt chocolate bars in double boiler.
Pour over mixture. Refrigerate until chocolate hardens.
Cut into bars.

title: quiche
directions: Cut butter in 1/2-inch cubes.
Place butter, shortening and flour in bowl.
With your hands, rub together to pea size. Dissolve salt and sugar in water and add to flour mixture, one tablespoon at a time.
Add up to 1 tablespoon more to gather into a ball, if necessary.
Give final blending of fat and flour by kneading.

title: vicki's beef rolls
directions: Brown hamburger meat
Then add Beefy Onion soup mix and mustard. Mix well and continue to cook until meat is thoroughly done.
Add jar of sauerkraut and mix well.
Heat until sauerkraut is warm
Open crescent rolls and break apart.
Put filling in center of each crescent roll and seal sides.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 375 degrees for 11-15 minutes.
Makes 10-12.

title: orange cake
directions: Squeeze juice from orange and save it for glaze.
Grind the rest of the orange and raisins.
Cream brown sugar and shortening. Add eggs, milk, flour, soda, vanilla, nutmeats and ground orange and raisins.
Bake about 30 minutes at 375° or until test done. As soon as baked, pour glaze over cake and return to oven for a few minutes.

title: zucchini fry
directions: Saute oil, butter and garlic.
Add onion and pepper.
Add salt and pepper to taste, then stir in zucchini and tomato.
Simmer (keep stirring until zucchini is tender).

title: easter eggs
directions: Fork mix and roll into balls.

title: chicken stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops off green peppers; remove seeds.
Saute onion in small amount of tomato liquid.
Add tomatoes, rice, Tabasco, chicken and 1/2 of the cheese.
Stand peppers upright in an 8-inch square baking dish.
Stuff peppers.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until hot.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: quilters' brew
directions: Pour 9 cups water into 12-cup percolator.
Put in basket tea bags, allspice, cloves and orange peel.
Perk through one complete cycle.
Remove basket and add remaining ingredients.
Stir and heat thoroughly.
Yields 13 cups.

title: tangy cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cranberry sauce until well blended.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Remove and beat on high speed until foamy.
Fold in yogurt, celery and nuts.
Pour into a 6-cup mold; refrigerate overnight.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: dried beef log
directions: Blend together cream cheese (softened), grated Parmesan cheese and horseradish.
Stir in chopped olives.
On waxed paper shape mixture into two 6-inch rolls, 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Wrap and chill several hours or overnight.
Roll log in finely snipped dried beef.
Serve with crisp crackers.

title: homemade venison italian soup
directions: Brown venison and drain.
Add venison to large pot; pour in V-8 juice and all veggies.
Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, Italian seasoning and onion as veggies are added. Serve with Italian sweet bread.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream the cheese and sugar.
Add milk and peanut butter.
Stir until well blended.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust. Refrigerate.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli until tender.
Prepare stuffing as directed on box.
Mix broccoli-cheese soup with 3/4 cup of water and heat until soupy.
Place chicken in bottom of casserole dish.
Add chopped, steamed broccoli.
Add soup.
Top with prepared stuffing mix.
Bake in a 350° oven until stuffing mix has browned (approximately 20 minutes).
Very good!

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix together.
Add a little sugar, if desired.

title: layered salad
directions: Thinly slice all vegetables.
Layer in order.
Refrigerate overnight.
Toss well before serving.

title: bill's tangy roast
directions: Make a bowl out of aluminum foil.
Leave enough that can be folded together to cover roast.
Place roast in aluminum foil. Pour beer over roast and fold aluminum foil to cover.
Place roast in 350° oven.
Cook as usual.
Mix barbecue sauce, catsup, mustard and soy sauce together to your own taste.
Pour over roast during last hour of cooking.
Tastes great cooked over the grill.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Brown first 5 ingredients until meat is separated.
Cook noodles in salted water; drain.
Add both soups and Parmesan cheese.
Mix thoroughly with meat.
Pour into dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or less.
(May be prepared a day ahead of time, then baked just before needed.)
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fruit tart (pizza)
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in flour.
Press into a 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned and cool.
Can use Boboli prepared crust instead of making one.

title: strawberry snowball salad
directions: Pour boiling water on gelatin in bowl; stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in cranberry juice and cold water.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened.

title: lemon-glazed blueberry rolls
directions: Combine in a small bowl; blend well.

title: boiled custard
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar and part of milk and heat on stove.
Add rest of milk.
Stir constantly until thickens.
Take off stove.
Put in a pan of water to speed cooling.
Add vanilla. When cool, pour through cheesecloth.
Keep chilled until ready to serve.

title: cheese cranberry bread
directions: Mix cranberries and 1/2 cup sugar.
Blend together flour, remaining sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix in sugared cranberries, nuts, orange peel and cheese.
Beat the egg, milk and butter; add to mixture and stir until just moistened.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In a large saucepan over medium heat, bring water and butter to a boil.
Quickly add flour, stirring until mixture forms a ball. Remove from heat.
Add eggs, a little at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add 1/2 cup cheese and save 1/2 cup for topping.
Drop mixture by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet, 1 1/2-inches apart.
Top each puff with a pinch of cheese (1/2 cup).
Bake 20 minutes. Turn off oven. Pierce sides of each puff in a few places and return to turned off oven for 5 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 3 dozen puffs.

title: oatmeal-fudge bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Mix sugar, 3/4 cup butter, the eggs and vanilla.
Mix in baking mix and oats; reserve.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix chicken, broccoli and next 3 ingredients.
Place in casserole.
Melt margarine.
Sprinkle stuffing on top and margarine over all.
Bake at 350° from 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.

title: baptist pie
directions: Mix together and fold in 1 (8 ounce) Cool Whip.
Top with frozen coconut.
Makes 2 pies.

title: angel fluff
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Immediately add berries. Fold in Cool Whip.
Blend cake pieces and jello mixture carefully. Pour into 1 (9 x 13-inch) and 1 (8 x 8-inch) cake pans.
Can serve with more Cool Whip on top.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add milk and lemon; blend.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Add one egg at a time and beat after each addition.
Put in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pound flour into steak; cut into serving size pieces.
In skillet, brown steak in 2 tablespoons of oil; pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours or until done. Stir occasionally.
May be served with cooked rice.

title: *lasagna
directions: In a skillet, brown the ground steak.
Add the tomato sauce, tomato paste and package of sauce mix.
Stir and mix well.
In the meantime, cook the lasagna according to directions on package; drain.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift and measure flour.
Add soda and salt and sift again.
Add sour cream and flour alternately to the above mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then fold into batter.
Blend in flavorings and pour into a 10 x 4-inch tube pan. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: vanilla bean ice cream
directions: Pour extracts and sprinkle nutmeg over ice cream.
Fill with milk.
Stir and serve.

title: german pancakes
directions: Mix flour, milk, salt and vanilla.
Beat egg and add to mixture.
Beat entire mixture until smooth.
You can add fruit, jelly, jam, etc. to taste.
Makes 1 pan size pancake.

title: apple pie
directions: If apples lack tartness, sprinkle with about 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt; mix with apples.
Line 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Fill with apple mixture.
Adjust top and flute edges.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in 400°
oven for 50 minutes.
Great when served hot topped with ice cream!

title: sweet-sour beef 'n cabbage
directions: Cook meat, onion, celery and pepper until brown; drain off fat.
Sprinkle oats, parsley, first salt, garlic and pepper over meat mixture.
Core cabbage; cut into wedges and place on meat. Mix remaining ingredients together in a bowl; pour over cabbage and meat.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes, or until cabbage is tender.
Serve at once.

title: pink stuff(jello salad)
directions: Mix together and cool and eat away.

title: red cheese ball
directions: Mix with electric beater in a large bowl the cheeses, sherry, Worcestershire sauce, onion, Accent and salts until thoroughly blended.
Shape into ball; wrap in foil.
Refrigerate overnight. Shape ball with hands, then roll in dried beef.
Serve with crackers or party rye.

title: fried bananas
directions: Cut bananas in half and then cut each half lengthwise.
In a nonstick frypan, melt margarine over low heat.
Add bananas to margarine, heat about 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Place bananas on serving tray or flat surface.
Allow them to cool slightly. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and nuts.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together (may add small amount of milk, if needed).
Pour in hot skillet with bacon drippings.
Cook a little longer than regular cornbread.
Cook until done at 350°.

title: sesame chicken with noodles
directions: Cut chicken into 3 x 1/2-inch strips; set aside.
Combine brown sugar and the next 8 ingredients in a 2-quart shallow casserole. Add chicken; toss gently to coat.
Cover and chill 30 minutes. Drain chicken, reserving 1/4 cup marinade.
Return chicken to casserole.
Combine reserved marinade and cornstarch; pour over chicken and toss.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap, turning back one corner to vent.
Microwave at High 5 minutes.
Stir in sweet red pepper and scallions.
Cover with plastic wrap, venting corner.
Microwave at High 2 to 3 minutes, or until chicken is done.
Stir in cabbage and remaining ingredients, except noodles. Cover; let stand 1 minute.
Serve over noodles.
Yields 4 servings.

title: montana steak
directions: Dust meat with flour, salt and pepper, brown the meat and remove from skillet.
Put potatoes in skillet and brown; remove to plate.
Brown onions; add meat and potatoes and mix.
Add soup and water and stir.
Add tomato sauce, if you desire, and cook until meat is done.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix all together and bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: remember when sugar cookies
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream together margarine, shortening, sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Add egg; cream until mixture is fluffy. Stir in dry ingredients until mixture is smooth.
Blend in milk. Roll dough into balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of water glass, which has been first dipped in water and then in sugar.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 12 minutes. Cool.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: biscuit bake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cook sausage links and drain on paper towels.
Split biscuits in half and pat out half of biscuits in a greased muffin pan.
Cut sausage link in half, put both halves on dough.
Add grated cheese and cover with remaining dough.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes and serve.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: vienna tarts
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter, flour and sugar; chill 30 minutes.

title: chicken soup
directions: Boil fryer and debone. Chop chicken in pieces. Add back to broth. Add rest of ingredients and cook until macaroni is tender. Add milk and enjoy.

title: cherry angel dessert
directions: Place half of cake pieces in bottom of large bowl.
Spread all but 1/4 cup of cherry filling onto cake.
Cover with remaining cake.
combine pudding mix with milk and sour cream; beat smooth. Top cake with pudding mixture.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours.
Top with remaining cherries.

title: sausage egg casserole(low-fat version)
directions: Mix cheese, bread and flour.
Add cooked and drained sausage. Put in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Beat eggs; add milk and condiments.
Pour mixture over ingredients in casserole.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 325° for one hour or until set in middle.
Let cool 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: never fail gravy
directions: In 1 qt. glass measure, combine 3 T. fat from turkey drippings or margarine and 3 T. flour.
Gradually stir in 2 c. chicken broth or turkey drippings (2 c. total).
Cook on high 6 to 9 minutes until boiling and thickened.
Stir twice during cooking.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
1/2 tsp. browning sauce (optional).
Makes 2 cups.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients except cheese and chips.
Place in a 2-quart casserole. Top with cheese and chips and bake 15 minutes. Makes about 8 servings.

title: deer stew
directions: Brown meat.
Put in oven.
Cover with potatoes, carrots and onions.
Mix soup with a can of water; pour over meat.
If it doesn't cover, add more water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in oven for 2 hours at 350°.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with Karo syrup and vanilla.
Drain and mash with maple syrup and butter.
Spread in casserole.
Put nuts on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook potato in broth. Add vegetables, soup and chicken.
Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch casserole. Add chicken mixture. Mix Bisquick and milk thoroughly (in separate bowl). Pour on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until topping is brown.

title: reese's peanut butter cookies (finger cookies)
directions: Slice cookie dough into 1-inch slices and then quarter each slice.
Press each piece of cookie dough in the bottom of miniature muffin tins.
Unwrap and press one peanut butter cup in the middle of cookie dough.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: baked barbecue beans
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: strawberry cake in a bowl
directions: Mix strawberry Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water; mix well. Add 1 cup of cold water and frozen strawberries; set aside.
Pinch angel food cake in pieces.
Pour Jell-O mixture over cake pieces. Set aside.
Mix pudding with milk.
Add Cool Whip.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour hot water over oats.
Set aside.
Cream margarine and sugars.
Add 1 egg, at a time and beat.
Add oatmeal mixture to cream mixture.
Then add dry ingredients.
Mix.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sift flour and salt together in a large bowl.
Beat eggs and add milk and shortening or margarine.
Place a dot of margarine in each cup of muffin pan.
Heat in oven until melted and hot.
Make a well in flour mixture.
Pour in egg mixture.
Beat with egg beater until smooth.
Pour batter into sizzling pans.
Fill 1/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes. Reduce heat to 325°.
Continue baking 15 minutes or until after "popped over" and firm.
Turn off oven.
Leave popovers in oven long enough to get crisp.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine bell pepper, onion and margarine and cook together until onion is clear.
Add remaining ingredients to this.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish and cover with grated cheese.
Heat for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Put together quickly; mix, but don't stir.
Roll half of dough between 2 crossed pieces of wax paper to full size square formed by wax paper.
Bake at 400° until light brown, if for shell.
Makes 2 shells.

title: pizza muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Blend together the egg, tomato sauce and buttermilk or yogurt in a medium bowl.
Add cheese and spices. In another bowl, mix flour, wheat germ, baking powder and baking soda.
Spray 12 regular size muffin cups with vegetable spray such as Pam.
Combine two mixtures into larger bowl.
Mix until no flour is visible.
Spoon batter equally into 12 wells.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven at 400°.
Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 50 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between the center and the edge of the filling comes out clean.

title: bacon rounds
directions: Lay rolls out flat.
Spread with sour cream.
Sprinkle with onion salt and bacon bits.
Roll up like jelly roll.
Chill and slice.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Pour sugar in a large bowl.
Cream butter in sugar.
Add Eagle Brand milk and mix well.
Add coconut and pecans.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Dip in chocolate.
Place on wax paper.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine sugar and flour in mixing bowl.
Heat butter, cocoa and Coca-Cola to boiling and pour over flour-sugar mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, vanilla and marshmallows; mix well.
This will be a thin batter with marshmallows floating on top.
Bake and ice while hot.

title: custard pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Slowly stir into eggs.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut blossoms(cookies)
directions: Beat first 6 ingredients in large mixing bowl until fluffy. Then beat in next 4 ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Place each ball on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Press Hershey's Kisses in center of each cookie and place back in oven for a couple of minutes.
Cool.

title: shrimp creole(serves 10)
directions: In heavy 8-quart pan heat oil and gradually add flour, stirring constantly until roux is color of a penny.
Remove from heat.
Add fresh vegetables and parsley.
Stir and return to low heat.
Cook, stirring constantly, until vegetables begin to brown. Mix in tomatoes and tomato sauce; add wine and seasonings and mix well.
Raise heat and bring to boil.
Mix in water.
Reduce heat and simmer for 45 minutes. Add shrimp; bring to a boil and simmer 20 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes, covered.
Serve over rice.

title: salad supreme
directions: Drain pineapple.
Save the juice.
Mix jello according to box. Pour in 8 x 12-inch dish.
Put in refrigerator.
Allow to almost congeal.
Add pineapple.
Sprinkle 1/2 of nuts on top. Return to refrigerator.

title: quiche
directions: Bake pie crust according to package directions.
Mix remaining ingredients together; pour into baked pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 20 minutes or more, until set.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl with a lid. Best if refrigerated overnight, but let it cool and sit for at least 2 hours.

title: sausage roll-ups
directions: Separate crescent rolls and cut in half.
Sprinkle a bit of cheese in center of each.
Roll 1 sausage per crescent half, starting at narrow end.
Bake according to biscuit can directions. Serve warm with assorted dipping sauces (mustard, barbecue, ketchup, Ranch, etc.).
Great party appetizer!

title: how to bag your deer
directions: Place flour into oven roasting bag and shake around.
Lay bag flat in pan with at least 1-inch high sides.
Rinse steaks and place them, side by side, in bag.
Add carrots, potatoes, celery and mushrooms to bag.
In a saucepan, heat golden mushroom soup, water and dry onion soup until melted.
Spread evenly over steak and vegetables.
Use tie provided with bag to tie bag shut.
Using a sharp knife, place 6 slits, 1-inch long, in top of bag for venting (or follow manufacturer's directions for bag usage).

title: coconut pecan bars
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar, add eggs one at a time beating well after each addition. Beat in vanilla. Combine dry ingredients, gradually add into mixture. Stir in coconut and pecans. Spread into 9 by 13 inch pan.

title: stir-fried cabbage and zucchini
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven, over high heat, in hot oil, cook garlic until brown.
Discard garlic.
Add cabbage and zucchini, stir-frying until well coated with oil.
Add salt and sugar. Reduce heat to medium high.
Continue stir-frying 7 to 8 minutes until vegetables are tender-crisp.

title: overnight pecan rolls
directions: Grease angel food or Bundt pan.
Add rolls.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over rolls.
Let rise 8 hours or overnight. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, last 10 minutes cover with foil.

title: beer batter for vegetables
directions: In bowl, combine flour, salt and beer.
Mix well (it will be fairly firm).
Stir in beaten egg whites, small amount at a time, folding to combine thoroughly.
In deep pan or wok, heat enough oil to cover vegetables (375°).
Dip vegetables, one at a time into batter, then drop into oil until puffed and golden.
Use this light and crisp batter to coat onion rings, stemmed green beans, green pepper, mushrooms, broccoli, etc.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Mix together first three ingredients.
Sift together the salt and flour.
Mix in 3/4 cup chopped pecans.
Mix all together and chill dough.
Roll into 3/4 to 1-inch balls.
Bake until set, not brown.
While still warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Cool.
Roll in sugar again.
Bake in a 400° moderate oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: mexi-chili casserole
directions: Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook bacon; drain on paper towel.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons of pan drippings.
Add onion; cook over medium heat until tender.
Add bacon, broccoli, broth, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 5 minutes (for frozen broccoli) or 10 minutes (for fresh broccoli), or until tender.
Stir cornstarch into a few tablespoons of milk. Reduce heat to low; gradually stir milk into soup.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens, about 10 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat 1 egg white until stiff.
Fold into condensed milk, egg yolks and lime juice.
Put lime mixture into baked pastry shell. Top lime mixture with meringue.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes until egg whites are golden brown.

title: chicken-stuffing casserole
directions: Prepare chicken stuffing mix as directed on package.
Boil boneless chicken in water until done.
Cool and dice up in small pieces.
In bowl, mix both cans of soup with milk.
Add pepper, salt, parsley flakes and garlic to taste.
Stir in chicken.
Pour cream mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, then spoon prepared stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes to bubbly.

title: easy filled cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, brown sugar and eggs.
Stir in water and vanilla.
Sift together and stir in flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.

title: dutch bacon peas
directions: Add to the peas the sugar and bacon, diced (not fried) and the onion, diced.
Cook until tender in just enough water to keep them from sticking.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a Bundt baking pan.
In a bowl, stir together flour, baking powder and salt.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix Raisin Bran, sugar, flour, baking soda, pumpkin pie spice and salt in large bowl.
Add buttermilk, eggs, margarine and vanilla to dry ingredients and stir to blend.
Drop into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Store in refrigerator 3 weeks.

title: wedding fruit punch
directions: Lemonade, pineapple and orange juice, all frozen type.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except coconut, in electric blender container.
Process for 10 seconds.
Stir in coconut.
Pour into a buttered 9-inch deep dish pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until set (pie will puff, then fall slightly).
Cool and chill thoroughly.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream sugar, ole, and shortening.
Add egg yolks one at a time and mix well.
Add vanilla.
Mix together flour, soda, and salt add to mixture.
Alternating with buttermilk, add chopped pecans and coconut.
Beat egg whites and fold in last.
Bake in four 8-inch pans at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli divan
directions: Place broccoli in 2 qt. shallow baking dish. Top with chicken. Mix soup and milk. Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese. Mix bread crumbs and butter and sprinkle on top. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Allow butter and cream cheese to stand at room temperature at least 1 hour.
Cream together cheese and butter.
Add sugar and vanilla; blend well.
Add nuts.
Frost cooled Carrot Cake layers.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil oleo, syrup, sugar and cream of tartar 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add soda and pour over popcorn (in a big roaster). Bake in 200° oven for 1 hour; stir every 10 minutes.

title: ham casserole
directions: Butter a shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Combine butter and stir into cornflakes crumbs until evenly coated.
Set aside. Combine soup, milk, ham, mushrooms and noodles.
Turn into baking dish.
Sprinkle with crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Steam broccoli for 5 to 6 minutes.
Cook the rice according to package directions.
Spread the cooked rice over the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with broccoli and set aside. Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in medium skillet over low heat.
Over medium heat, beat in flour with a whisk until the mixture is smooth and bubbly, then whisk in the boiling water, salt, soy sauce, garlic powder, onion powder and turmeric.
Cook until thick and bubbling, then whisk in the yeast.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour the sauce over the broccoli and rice; sprinkle the top with paprika and bake for 15 minutes.
If desired, place the baking dish under the broiler for a few minutes until the sauce is browned and crusty.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut butter play dough
directions: Mix until well blended.
Add more dry milk if texture feels sticky.
Let children use as play dough and eat their creations.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 40 to 60 minutes at 350° in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Grate cheese and put on top; return to oven to melt.

title: neil's cinnamon shortbread(makes 1 cookie sheet pan, 12 x 16)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Blend together butter, sugar, vanilla and salt in a bowl using fork until combined well. Sift flour into butter mixture and blend until it becomes a soft dough.

title: chicken and angel hair pasta casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
In broth from chicken, put in onion, green pepper, celery and angel hair.
Boil until pasta is done; drain.
Add mushrooms, black olives and Ro-Tel; season with garlic powder, salt and oregano.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
May be kept warm in low temperature oven.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk and salt.
Fold in flour.
Hand whip until batter is smooth.
Pour into well-greased muffin pans, about 1/2 full.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes or until a golden brown.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together over low heat.
Separate eggs; set aside whites and beat egg yolks well.
Add sugar slowly to eggs, then add to chocolate mixture which has cooled slightly. Add nuts and flour.
Beat egg whites to a stiff froth and add last. Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan at 335° for 40 minutes.
Do not overbake!
These are moist and chewy brownies; freeze beautifully.

title: granny welbourn's chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken meat as pie dough; roll on well floured board; cut into 2-inch squares.
Bring chicken broth to rolling boil.
Drop squares in; stir frequently to prevent sticking, 30 to 45 minutes, then add meat.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: grandma maeker's 1933 old fashioned homemade noodles
directions: Mix all ingredients.
When mixed, turn onto floured board and roll thin.
Cut into strips and pieces.
Let dry.
Cook in boiling water, seasoned with salt.

title: pickled okra
directions: Boil vinegar, water and salt for 10 minutes.
Pack okra in clean jars with 1 teaspoon dill seed and 1 clove garlic for each jar.
Bring vinegar mixture to a boil and pour over okra.
Seal jars.
After 3 weeks, the okra is ready to eat.

title: blueberry cream cheese bars
directions: Crush graham crackers and mix with melted butter. Spread half in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill. Combine water, cornstarch, sugar and blueberries. Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened. Cool. Mash the cream cheese until soft. Beat in sugar and vanilla. Gradually add whipped topping. Drop by spoonfuls over crumbs. Spread carefully. Cover with blueberry filling. Spread remaining crumbs. Chill overnight.

title: our favorite pound cake
directions: Thoroughly mix the first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well, then add vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and milk, alternately.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours for pound cake or until done for a 3-layer cake.

title: chicken and cheese burgers
directions: Mix the chicken, cheese, green pepper, salt and pepper together.
Place a spoonful of the mixture in the center of each hamburger bun.
Replace bun tops and wrap each bun in a square of foil.
Place in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve piping hot. Garnish with dill pickles.

title: streusel filled coffee cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Blend in melted butter and chopped nuts; mix well.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and salt.
Pour boiling water over mixture and cool to lukewarm.
Add liquids to 3 1/2 cups flour. Add egg.
Mix and add more flour and yeast until dough is stiff. Beat well and pour into greased bowl.
Cover and put in refrigerator overnight or at least 2 hours.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Melt margarine and stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil, without stirring, for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in baking soda and vanilla. Gradually pour over popped corn, mixing well.
Turn into a large baking pan (I use large broiler pan lined with foil).
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool completely.
Break apart.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Combine dressings and cheese; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill.
Serve with freshly ground black pepper, if desired.

title: lindsey's fried rice
directions: In a skillet or wok over medium heat, brown the onions with 2 tablespoons butter. Toss in the cooked rice. Crack and mix the eggs into mixture until the eggs have completely cooked. Mix in the soy sauce and salt and pepper to taste.

title: keebler pecan sandies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add potato chips and pecans. Stir in flour.
Form into small balls (use tablespoon).
Put balls on cookie sheet and press flat with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 16 to 18 minutes.

title: gelatin jigglers
directions: Stir boiling water or juice with powdered gelatin in a large bowl.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan. Refrigerate at least 3 hours or until firm.
Dip bottom of pan in warm water about 15 seconds.
Cut into decorative shapes with cookie cutters.
Lift from pan.
Makes about 24 pieces.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Put rice in baking dish.
Add cream of mushroom soup and water. Add butter; stir well.
Lay boneless chicken breasts on top of rice.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix until consistency you need.
Roll out real thin and cut. Drop into boiling broth.

title: grilled kodiak scallops
directions: Heat grill or broiler. In heavy saucepan, melt butter and add flour. Cook for 5 minutes over low heat, stirring constantly. Do not allow to brown. Add wine and cream and bring to boil. Reduce heat and allow sauce to simmer 10 minutes or until it thickens slightly. Add the cheese and stir until melted. Remove from heat and strain. Keep warm. Bring large pot of water to a boil. Add pasta. Cook until pasta is done and drain. While pasta is cooking, grill scallops 3 to 4 minutes on each side. Toss pasta in some of the sauce and divide onto 4 heated plates. Arrange scallops over pasta and sprinkle pasta with bergamot flowers.

title: kielbasa appetizer
directions: Melt butter in frying pan; add garlic powder and vermouth, then the thin sliced kielbasa or whole tiny franks.
Serve hot before or with cocktails.

title: beetnick cake or bars
directions: Mix all together and pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan or jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: kool-aid pie
directions: Mix milk, sugar and Kool-Aid in medium mixing bowl; place in freezer until ice crystals form around edges of mixture.
Chill mixer beaters.
Whip mixture on high speed until peaks form.
Put in graham cracker crust.
Top with whipped cream.
Garnish with strawberries or other fresh fruit, depending on flavor of Kool-Aid used.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Place in crock-pot.
Cook on low.
Serve over prepared rice.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Slice zucchini into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Place in shallow round glass baking dish.
Sprinkle with oregano, salt & pepper. Cover with wax paper and microwave 5 minutes until partially cooked.
Top each zucchini slice with a tomato slice, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and microwave another 2 minutes.

title: reuben casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, layer all ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream the cheeses and add the other ingredients. Shape into a ball and refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: sanford house french dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil and vinegar alternately, beating well between additions.
Add onion last.
Refrigerate.

title: cheese gems
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and egg yolks well.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into this mixture.
Bake in small muffin pans that have been buttered and lightly coated with graham cracker crumbs for 15 minutes at 350°.
They will fall when removed from oven, creating a slight depression in center to fill with frosting given below.
Cool in pans then gently remove before frosting.

title: busy day beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in deep, heavy skillet.
Add onion and cook until tender, but not brown.
Drain off excess grease.
Add tomatoes, water, noodles and seasonings.
Stir to moisten noodles. Cover. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Stir in mushrooms and olives.
Heat thoroughly.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cream cheese ham spread
directions: Mix together; refrigerate until ready to use.
Wonderful on bagels.

title: mushroom broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in casserole dish.
Pour soup over broccoli. Add mushrooms.
Crumble the crackers on top.
Place the cheese on top and pour the milk over it.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until most of the milk is gone.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix squash, onion, sugar, salt and pepper.
Let set 30 minutes; drain.
Stir in flour and eggs.
Melt margarine in a skillet.
Drop squash mixture into the skillet by spoonfuls.
Cook until golden brown, turning once.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks, jam and buttermilk.
Sift together the spice, soda and flour.
Add alternately with milk and nuts. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour into 4 prepared 8-inch cake pans and bake at 350° until done.

title: peanut butter parfait
directions: Mix crust mixture and press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°; cool.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in blender.
Cook in boiler over medium-high heat until thick.
Set aside and add margarine and vanilla.
Pour in pie shell.
When cool, top with whipped cream.

title: chinese stir-fry chicken
directions: Pour a little vegetable oil in wok; add chicken strips and cook until done, stirring often.
Remove from heat.
In saucepan, combine soy sauce and cornstarch over low heat; stir to mix.
Add oyster sauce, broth, chili oil, chili powder and sugar.
Heat and stir until slightly thickened; remove from heat.
Now return wok with cooked chicken to heat.
Over medium heat, add carrots, zucchini, water chestnuts, bamboo shoots, red pepper and green onions; stir and cook until the vegetables are tender-crisp.
Pour on sauce; toss well to coat meat and vegetables.
Cook another minute or so.
Serve hot over rice.

title: savoy cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in four to six pieces, according to size.
Pour the oil into a deep pot or Dutch oven.
First, add onions and garlic, then half of cabbage together with the carrots and potatoes.
Place the rest of the cabbage on top and add water, herbs and seasonings.

title: lemon cake
directions: Beat ingredients for 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Test for doneness.
Remove cake from oven and while still hot, poke holes in cake with a fork.
Pour on the frosting.

title: grandma's chocolate cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut into large rounds.
Trim on top with M&M's.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: salmon-broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Blend in flour, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Add milk and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add tomatoes and lemon juice and cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Arrange broccoli on bottom of casserole.
Cover with salmon and top with sauce.

title: stuffed crabs
directions: Saute vegetables in oleo.
Add Worcestershire sauce, crabmeat, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat for 15 minutes, stirring constantly.
Soak bread or buns in evaporated milk and add to crab mixture, along with onion tops, parsley and eggs.
Mix well.

title: grandma's date and nut bread
directions: Mix together the dates, water and baking soda; let stand until cool.
Mix all other ingredients together, then mix in cooled date mixture.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, or when toothpick comes out clean.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Fry onion in small amount oil until

translucent. Drain. Add drained green beans and corn. Mix together. Mix soup and sour cream and add to vegetable mixture. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch casserole. Top with cheese, then crushed cracker crumbs. Drizzle with melted butter. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pan brownies
directions: Grease and flour a large cookie sheet with sides.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift flour and sugar together in a large bowl.
In a 2-quart saucepan, melt margarine, cocoa and water.
Bring to a rapid boil.
Pour over flour and sugar mix. Add buttermilk with soda.
Mix. Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix and pour into prepared cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: yuletide minty fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In medium saucepan, combine sugar, butter and water; bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add the mint-flavored chocolate morsels and vanilla extract; stir until morsels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Transfer to large bowl. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Gradually blend in flour mixture.
Stir in the nuts.
Spread into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until tests done.
Cool; cut into 1 1/2-inch squares. Makes 4 dozen.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix all
the
ingredients
in a crock-pot and simmer on low for 6 hours.
This is a very thick sauce.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sour cream.
Add dressing mix; mix in shrimp and lemon juice.
Refrigerate.

title: baked onions
directions: In buttered casserole, place alternate layers of thinly sliced onions, crushed potato chips and grated cheese.
Pour soup over top and sprinkle with cayenne pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mom's fast baked beans
directions: Dice onions.
In microwave-safe bowl, mix together beans, sugar and onions.
Pour catsup over the top, then mix in.
Cover with plastic wrap or wax paper.
Cook on High 8 minutes in microwave.
Test, then cook longer, if necessary.
I often double the recipe for a larger dish and cook for 16 to 20 minutes.

title: west indian fish cakes(by sonja jackson)
directions: Mash white potato in mixing bowl (large).
Drain water from cod fish and stir into fine pieces.
Add all other ingredients to bowl. Add 2 cups of cold water.
Mix.

title: foil wrapped dinner
directions: Put meat, potatoes and carrots on aluminum foil.
Put mixture of cream of mushroom soup and dry onion soup and some water over top of meat, potatoes and carrots, then put corn on top.
Fold up foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar and oil together.
Add slightly beaten eggs. Beat mixture with electric mixer until creamy.
Add oats.
Sift dry ingredients (flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices) and add to mixture.
Mix well.
Add nuts, raisins and vanilla.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with spoon and chill.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: pumpkin dream bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Beat margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add oats and flour.
Mix well. Spread evenly onto bottom of prepared pan.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes until light golden brown.
Cool slightly.
Beat cream cheese and sugar at medium speed of electric mixer until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Pour over crust.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes until center sets.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 20 bars.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix flour and sugar into beaten eggs; add pineapple and pour into buttered dish.
Toss bread cubes into butter and pour on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain. Layer in crock-pot: meat, mushrooms, pizza sauce, noodles, pepperoni, cheese. Repeat and end with sauce. Cook on low for 3 hours or high for 1 hour. Makes full pot.

title: bread pudding
directions: Put leftover bread in bowl.
Pour milk in.
Let stand until bread is soft (add more milk if needed).
Add eggs and sugar to your taste; be sure no lumps are left.
Melt margarine and mix well.
Pour into pan and bake at 325° until brown.

title: german potato salad
directions: Slice potatoes.
Fry diced bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon fat from pan, except for 3 or 4 tablespoons.
Saute 1/2 of onions lightly
in bacon fat; add to potatoes.
Add cut up eggs, green pepper, pimiento, 1/2 onion and about 3/4 of bacon.

title: low-fat sweet and sour green beans
directions: Drain and rinse green beans.
Combine with bacon, onion, vinegar, sugar and water in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer until liquid evaporates.
Yields 3 servings.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Combine pepper, vinegar and sugar. Bring to rolling boil.
Add Certo and bring back to boil.
Boil 3 to 4 minutes.
Add food coloring.
Take off stove and stir several minutes.
Strain, pour into jars and seal.
Serve with meat or on crackers with cream cheese.

title: date pudding
directions: Pour hot water over dates and soda; let stand until cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Let cool.
Cut cake into squares and serve with whipped cream.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix pecans and coconut; spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cake mix per directions on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut. Melt margarine and cream cheese on low heat until smooth.
Mix in powdered sugar.
Spoon over cake mixture.
Do not stir or spread. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs lightly.
Warm milk and butter in a pan.
Add sugar to eggs and beat.
Add milk, vanilla, salt, cinnamon, raisins and bread.
Place in
pan of water and bake.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate egg nog
directions: In blender, combine 1 cup milk, egg yolks, cocoa, sweetened milk, vanilla and salt. Cover and blend on high 30 seconds. Pour into large mixing bowl. Stir in remaining 3 cups milk and extracts.
Blend well. Beat egg whites until peaks form.
Gently fold into milk mixture. Chill thoroughly. Stir well before serving. Sprinkle with grated chocolate.
Makes 3 (8 ounce) servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Place in oblong cake pan the ingredients in the order listed. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: mexican dinner
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Brown onion in hot fat; add meat and brown until crumbly.
Add seasonings, soup and water.
Bring just to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Pour into casserole dish.
Make 2 cups of self-rise cornbread batter and spread over top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: frozen popsicles
directions: Dissolve Jell-O, Kool-Aid and sugar in boiling water.
Stir well.
Add cold water.
Pour into ice cube trays, small paper cups or frozen pop molds.
(Or you can save 6 ounce orange juice cans and use them.)
Freeze until partially firm, then insert wooden sticks, paper spoons or plastic knives, forks or spoons.
Freeze overnight.
When ready to eat, just tear off the orange juice can!

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Pierce skins of potatoes with a fork.
Cook potatoes, 2 at a time, in microwave for 4 minutes.
Turn potatoes and cook for an additional 4 minutes or until tender.
When all potatoes are done, slice top from each potato and scoop insides into a mixing bowl. Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Beat until smooth. Spoon mixture back into potato shells.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Return to microwave for 2 to 3 minutes or until heated.

title: carol's molasses candy crisps
directions: Cream butter, salt and cinnamon, adding sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend molasses, flour and coconut.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until edges are slightly brown.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in small dish or cup.
Put berries in baking dish (approximately 9 x 13-inch).
Add 1/2 cup water to berries. Pour dry cake mix over berries.
Spoon melted margarine over dry cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts over casserole and bake about 1 hour in preheated oven at 350°.
Bake until casserole bubbles well in center.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken,
mushroom	soup,
chicken soup, sour cream and chicken broth.
Water
chestnuts and pimento may be added. Put 3/4 cracker crumbs
into
a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Place the chicken mixture
on
top
of the crumbs.
Add remainder of crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with salad or fresh fruit.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together; set aside.
Cream butter; add 1 1/2 cups sugar gradually, creaming until fluffy. Blend in eggs.
Add dry ingredients gradually, mixing well.
Chill in refrigerator.
Shape dough into small balls, using
1 tablespoon dough for each ball.
Combine remaining 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon; roll balls in sugar mixture.
Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake about 10 minutes.
Store in covered container.
Yield:
2 to 3 dozen.

title: peanut butter reese cup
directions: Melt margarine and mix with sugar, peanut butter and vanilla (will be very stiff), and pat out into greased platter.
Melt Hershey bar and spread on top.
Cut into squares before hard.

title: world's best cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add egg and mix well.
Then add oil and mix well.
Add oats, flakes, coconut and nuts; mix well.
Mix together flour, baking soda and salt. Add to oat mixture and stir in vanilla.
Mix well and form into balls the size of small walnuts. Place on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake in preheated 325° oven for 12 minutes.
Allow cookies to cool on sheets for a few minutes before removing.
Yields 8 dozen.

title: mexican apple pie
directions: Heat sugar and water in a saucepan until sugar is melted. Pour oleo into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Toss apples in the cinnamon to coat.
Place 1/2 cup apples down center of each tortilla.
Roll and place seam side down in pan.
Pour sugar water over the top. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients and nuts.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in another mixing bowl.
Add this to the dry ingredients.
Stir until moistened.
Spoon into oiled and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Cool; remove from pan.
Bread freezes well.

title: purple pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat 4 minutes.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes in a preheated oven at 325°.

title: big mac attack sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients using a fork rather than a mixer.
Keep refrigerated in a covered container until time to serve.
Makes 2 cups.
Sufficient to spoon over a dozen double patties on buns.

title: apple crunch
directions: Sprinkle apples with 1/2 cup sugar.
In a bowl, mix egg, flour and 1 cup sugar.
Sprinkle this mixture over apples and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Good with ice cream!

title: perfect chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk in a large saucepan, stirring. Bring to a rapid boil.
Boil 5 minutes; remove from heat and stir in chocolate morsels, nuts, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Have several large plates or cookie sheet buttered as mixture sets up quickly.
When mixture begins to thicken, pour onto buttered plates or pans.

title: praline shortbread cookies
directions: Cream butter and add sugar.
Beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour and pecans.
Dough will be stiff. Press onto bottom of greased and floured 15 X 10 X 1 inch pan. Score into 2 inch squares.
Bake 20 minutes at 325 degrees.
Break into wedges.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Butter hands.
Roll into ball. May roll in crushed pecans or grated dried beef.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Wash pods. Cut off stems.
Cook, covered, in small amount of boiling salted water, 8 to 15 minutes.
Cook onion and green pepper in oleo until tender, but not brown.
Stir in sugar, flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Add tomatoes. Cook and stir until slightly thickened and bubbly. Add cooked okra.
Heat through.
Yields 6 servings.

title: diet ground beef casserole
directions: Cook beef in heavy skillet and drain off all fat.
Combine beef and other ingredients and bake in oven until carrots and cabbage are tender, about 1 hour at 350°.
This recipe serves 1 for dinner.
Use any spices or herbs that you wish, such as bay leaves, garlic powder, etc.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Beat cream cheese and Cool Whip well with mixer.
Spread pie filling over cream cheese mixture.

title: no peep beef stew
directions: Place all ingredients in large pot. Stir well. Cover and bake 4 hours at 250° and please do not open oven until 4 hours have passed by. May have more vegetables than what is called for.

title: baked pork and beans
directions: Mix beans, onion, ketchup, mustard and brown sugar together. Pour into 1-quart casserole dish and lay bacon on top.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: quick and easy casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown beef with salt, breaking into small pieces.
Drain.
In a bowl, mix potatoes, soup, sour cream, cheese, chopped onion and beef.
Mix well.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes.
Top with fried onions. Bake 15 minutes more or until bubbly.
Makes 8 servings of about 555 calories each.

title: italian beans
directions: Fry together ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Add spices and tomato paste and 1 can water.
Add sauce and beans.
Cook until tender (add enough water to cover beans).

title: easy oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix margarine, brown sugar, white sugar, eggs, water, vanilla, baking soda and salt until fluffy.
Add flour, oatmeal, chocolate chips and chopped pecans all at once.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Blend peppers with vinegar
and Tabasco.
Mix this with pectin in large pan.
Bring
to
hard
boil
over
high
heat, stirring. Stir in sugar and
bring
to
rolling boil and boil hard 1 minute. Remove from heat, skim foam, add several drops of green food coloring.
Stir.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° approximately one hour and 15 to 20 minutes until browned on top.

title: baked split pea soup
directions: Slice sausage 1/4 inch thick.
Add this after the first 2 hours of baking.
Bake above ingredients 2 hours at 350° in covered Dutch oven (not necessary to stir at all).
Bake 30 minutes more after adding sausage or until peas are tender and sausage heated through.
(You may use fresh onion and chicken broth for part of liquid.)
Could also use ham bone and chunks of cooked ham.

title: hardee's biscuit recipe
directions: Add all dry ingredients together.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to buttermilk and oil.
Add milk mixture to flour mixture and stir.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Take out what is needed at a time.
Grease pan and put a little butter on top of biscuits and bake at 450°.
Dough will keep for 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: caribbean fish fritters
directions: Cook salted cod fish for 20 minutes in large frying pan.
Drain and add fresh water.
Let fish soak for 15 minutes.
Drain.
Mince fish in small pieces.
