Add beaten eggs in medium bowl with fish, flour or mashed potatoes.
Add onions, black pepper, baking powder and scallions.

title: oven barbecued steak
directions: Combine all ingredients, except steak, salt and pepper, in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 5 minutes over low heat.
Keep sauce hot.
Cut steak into serving size pieces; season generously with garlic, salt and pepper.
Place pieces in casserole or baking dish.
Pour hot sauce over steak.
Bake in a 325° oven for about 1 1/2 hours, or until fork-tender.
Garnish with bell pepper rings, if desired.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: orange salsa
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.

title: sicilian meat loaf
directions: Combine beef with eggs, crumbs, juice, parsley and spices. On wax paper, shape meat mixture into rectangle.
Arrange thin slices of ham on meat; sprinkle with shredded Mozzarella. Carefully roll up; seal seams.
Put in 13 x 9-inch baking pan, seam side down.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add Mozzarella on top to melt a few minutes.
Good company dish.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, salt and milk.
Bring to rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and peanut butter; mix well.
Pour into 13 x 13-inch pan.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: easy oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine Bisquick mix, sugar and quick oats.
Combine milk, egg and salad oil.
Add at once to dry mixture. Stir just enough to moisten. Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
You may want to add half cup of raisins.

title: homemade bisquick
directions: Using large container, mix all ingredients together.
Blend shortening into dry mixture until the texture of coarse meal. Store in covered container at room temperature.
Makes 25 cups. Will keep 4 to 6 months.

title: shortbread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat butter with confectioners sugar until light and creamy.
Add vanilla.
Beat well.
Sift together salt and flour and fold into butter mixture.
Put dough on unbuttered baking sheet.
Pat into circle 3/8-inch thick.
Score into 8 or 10 wedges with sharp knife.
Mark edges decoratively with fork.
Bake 25 minutes until pale brown at edges.
Remove from oven.
Let cool. Sprinkle with sugar on top.
Break into wedges.
It's bad luck to cut shortbread.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream sugar with softened butter; mix in other ingredients and mix well.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Let cool a little, then roll in confectioners sugar.

title: velvet sponge cake(1906)
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar till stiff. Sift 1/4 c. flour,
and sugar and beat into egg whites. Add the egg
yolks. Mix in 1 c. flour and the
vanilla. Beat lightly. Bake at 325 degrees for 45 minutes. Serve with fresh fruit.

title: banana split brownie pizza(from pampered chef)
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to package directions.
Using parchment paper on 15-inch baking stone, pour mixture on paper and spread into 14-inch circle.
(Do not bake without paper, or batter will run off.
If not using baking stone or paper, use a shallow pan.)
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, or until set.
Cool to room temperature.

title: ranch oyster crackers
directions: Combine Hidden Valley Ranch powder with dill weed and garlic; add oil.
Pour over crackers and stir to coat.
Place on a cookie sheet in a warm oven, 250°, for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir gently halfway through baking.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in 13x9 pan.
Top with bread crumbs.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and 2 teaspoons paprika. Melt butter or margarine in skillet. Add chicken, skin side down. Saute until golden brown. Turn pieces and add onion. Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon paprika. Simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes. Add 2 cups of water; cook slowly until tender. Remove chicken. Blend sour cream or half and half, 3/4 cup water and flour until smooth. Add to the broth in skillet; cook until thickened. Bring chicken back to skillet; keep on low heat until serving time. May serve over top of rice or wide egg noodle dumplings.

title: agnes' relish
directions: Cook for 15 minutes at a rolling boil, then simmer uncovered for 1 hour or until thickened.
Put in a quart jar.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sour cream and soup in a bowl. Drain mushrooms and add to the mixture.
Spoon over chicken breasts and make sure to cover chicken and bottom of the dish with the mixture.
Sprinkle paprika over chicken.
Cook, uncovered, for 45 minutes to an hour.
Chicken is done when sides of dish are brown and the mixture bubbles.

title: children's play doh
directions: Mix flour, salt and cream of tartar.
Pour in boiling water. Stir with spoon until cool enough to handle.
Knead until smooth. (If using food coloring, add to water before mixing with other ingredients.)
Store in refrigerator for months in airtight container.
Not harmful if ingested.

title: "speedie" roll dough
directions: Combine water, sugar and yeast; stir until dissolved.
Add salt and 2 cups sifted flour.
Beat 2 minutes with electric mixer. Add eggs and Crisco and beat for 1 minute.
Work in remaining flour.
Cover and let rest in bowl for 20 minutes (this makes dough easier to handle).

title: kim's fruit dip
directions: Fold all ingredients together.
Serve with fruit as dip.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Place thawed hash browns in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt remaining ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Let stand 1 hour before baking.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until done.
Beat potatoes, sour cream, margarine and salt; mix well.
Add 1/3 cup chopped chives.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole (buttered).
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ritz cracker fruit cake
directions: Cook marshmallows and milk until melted.

Pour over other ingredients that you have mixed together in a very large bowl. Mix all together and mash down in an oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 3-inch pan lined with waxed paper or into paper-lined loaf pans. Refrigerate one week, then can be frozen in slices.
Good and easy!

title: baked eggs and cheese brunch casserole
directions: Cover bottom of 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish with half of the cheese sliced 1/2-inch thick. Mix seasonings with sour cream and pour half of this over cheese. Follow with sausage. Break eggs over this and cover with remaining sour cream mixture. Grate remaining cheese and sprinkle on top. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes until cheese is melted and eggs are set. Good for brunch.

title: lyonnaise potatoes
directions: Dilute beef bouillon cubes in water.
Slightly saute onions in butter.
Add beef bouillon.
Cut potatoes about the size of hashed browns and add to broth, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover.
Cook about 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves about 4.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Boil and cube potatoes.
Mash and mix ingredients.
Add Cheddar cheese after other ingredients are mixed.
Place mixture in buttered (or Pam) 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Can be cut and served in squares.

title: christmas candle
directions: Mix cheeses, Worcestershire and garlic salt thoroughly with an electric mixer.
Shape into a candle.
Roll in parsley or paprika. Make a flame from the carrot.

title: chili con carne with beans
directions: In a large skillet, brown onion and garlic (use olive oil), then add meat to skillet and brown it, too.
Put meat mixture into a large saucepan, rinsing the skillet with a cup of water and adding it also.
Add tomatoes and seasonings; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, until thick as you like.
(Two or three hours doesn't hurt.)
Before serving, add the drained beans and heat them through in the chili.

title: macaroni ham casserole
directions: Sauce:
Fry chopped onion in small amount of olive oil.
Add cut up ham pieces and fry with onion.
Add salt, pepper, oregano, and tomato sauce.
Cover and cook on low heat.
Boil macaroni for 6 minutes.

title: yam towne(sweet potato casserole)
directions: Mix all ingredients well; pour into buttered baking dish.

title: chuck teriyaki
directions: Mix marinade ingredients. Add chuck steak or small roast, turning occasionally.
Grill over charcoal. Baste with marinade, if desired.

title: raisin sandwich filling
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients until thick.
Add raisins, pecans and mayonnaise.
Store in refrigerator.

title: ham loaf(microwave)
directions: Combine brown sugar and dry mustard in small bowl.
Stir to blend.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in large bowl. Mix thoroughly.
Pat meat mixture into 9 x 5 x 2-inch loaf dish. Cook on full power for 5 minutes.
Spoon sugar mixture over meat. Continue cooking on cook level 3 for 25 to 30 minutes or until meat is thoroughly cooked.

title: triple chocolate brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch pie plate.

title: egg foo yong
directions: Combine and make into patties.
Fry slowly in olive oil.

title: carrot cake
directions: Grate carrots.
Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture.
Beat good.
Add carrots, mix by hand.
Use 2 (9-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: "more"
directions: Brown onions, peppers and meat and add everything else except noodles.
Salt and pepper to taste. Prepare noodles according to directions and then add them to mixture.
Pour into baking dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: "cheese cake"
directions: Mix graham crackers, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter together.
Put in a long glass pan.
Save some for topping.

title: shrimp macaroni salad
directions: Cut up shrimp.
Toss with macaroni, cheese, celery, green pepper and onion.
Blend remaining ingredients.
Toss with shrimp mixture.
Cover and chill.
Before serving, stir salad.
Good for hot summer days!
Serves 4 to 6.

title: apple pie pizza
directions: Combine 1 1/4 cup flour and 1 tsp salt in bowl.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Add cheese.
Sprinkle water on top. Shape into ball.
Press into greased 12 inch pizza pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil sliced squash and onion until tender.
Drain off water. Place in casserole dish.
Add soup and stuffing mix.
Mix well. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: oriental cole slaw
directions: In a skillet, melt a few Tbsp. margarine.
Crush Ramen noodles (without flavoring), put noodles, almonds & sesame seeds in the pan & stir until browned.
In a large bowl toss cabbage & green onions.
In a container mix oil, soy sauce, vinegar, sugar, pepper and chicken packets.
Mix crunchy mixture, dressing and cabbage mixture just before serving.

title: duchesse potatoes
directions: Put potatoes through a rice.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until mixture is fluffy.

title: ginger pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers and soak 24 hours.
Wash good; soak 1 hour in alum and 1 gallon water; rinse.
Soak 6 hours in 1 gallon water and ginger; drain.
Do not rinse.

title: creamy smoked salmon sauce
directions: Soften cream cheese; beat smooth.
Whisk in milk and add other ingredients.
Toss with hot fettucine or other pasta of choice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Melt margarine; add flour and salt and cook until bubbly.
Add milk and cook until thick.
Add nutmeg, lemon juice and broccoli.
Cool slightly and add beaten egg yolks. When broccoli mixture is cool, beat egg whites until stiff and fold in.
Pour in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place in pan of hot water and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla in a large bowl.
Add the flour, cinnamon, salt and soda; stir well.
Add the apples and nuts and mix well.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle with sugar when removed from pans.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: healthy heart chili
directions: Brown meat with favorite spices (salt and pepper).
Add chili mix and canned items.
Simmer and serve with crackers, tortilla chips, corn bread, etc.

title: green beans and pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops. Spread rice in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Next add green beans and onions.
Layer pork chops.
Add mushroom soup and seasoning. Add enough water to mix with soup and to cook rice. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bunny biscuits
directions: Separate biscuits, place 5 of them on a greased baking sheet about 2-inches apart.
Cut remaining biscuits in half.
Shape biscuit halves to form ears and firmly attach to whole biscuits. On each biscuit, press 2 raisins for the eyes, 1 candy or cherry for nose and 4 almond slivers for whiskers.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until biscuits are browned.
Cool slightly, frost ears with icing.
Makes 5 biscuits.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix together cream cheese and boiling water.
Drain corn and add cheese mixture to corn in a casserole dish.
Mix crackers with melted butter or margarine; sprinkle on top of corn mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple whole wheat rolls
directions: Drain pineapple and combine the reserved juice with the milk; heat adding brown sugar, oil and salt just until warm.
Combine the white flour and yeast in a bowl and add the liquid.
Beat this for 3 minutes on high speed.
By hand, add pineapple and stir in rest of whole wheat flour.
Turn onto a board and knead on floured surface, then place in greased bowl; cover and let rise to double and punch down.
Rest it 10 minutes, then divide in desired roll shape.
This one suggested dividing into 1/3 and make 15 small balls placing 3 to a muffin cup; let rise until almost double in size.
Then bake in 375° for 15 minutes.
Brush with combined honey and butter.

title: spinach soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Add flour and blend well.
Continue cooking 2 minutes.
Whisk in stock and wine. Add carrots, zucchini and parsley.
Cover and simmer until carrots are soft, about 20 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil Karo syrup, sugar, butter, water and salt, stirring constantly, until 250°.
Immediately add nuts and boil until 300°. Quickly add soda and pour on greased slab.

title: baked beans
directions: Pour can of pork and beans in large baking dish.
Mix tablespoon syrup, brown sugar, ketchup and onion together in with the beans.
Cover with desired amount of bacon.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until bacon is done.
Microwave 10 minutes or until bacon is done.

title: fettuccini
directions: Melt butter over low heat. Remove from heat.
Stir in cream that has been whipped. Blend well. Return to heat.
Add cheese and cook until cheese melts.
Pour over cooked linguine noodles.
Mix well.

title: baklava
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In bowl mix together the walnuts, sugar and cinnamon.
In baking pan, place 1 sheet phyllo, allowing it to extend up sides of pan; brush with butter or margarine.
Repeat to make 5 more layers and sprinkle into approximately 13 x 9-inch rectangles.
Preheat oven to 300°.

title: sweet and sour pork with rice
directions: Brown pork; drain.
Add all ingredients together.
Simmer until pork is tender.
Serve over rice.
Serves 5.

title: potato puffs
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix eggs and potatoes.
Add dry mixture and mix.
Drop by teaspoonful into deep fat (385°). Fry until golden brown.

title: ice cream cupcakes
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour mixture into ice cream cones 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and frost as desired.

title: stasia's favorite meat loaf(complete dinner)
directions: Combine meat, milk, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper, onion, garlic, parsley and celery leaves.
Add bread crumbs evenly.
Add eggs.
Handle mixture lightly.
Pat into loaf.
Place in a greased (Pam sprayed) covered casserole.
Place meat in center. Bake, uncovered, for first 1/2 hour.
Then add drained potatoes, all around meat loaf.
Add tomato soup mixture (gravy) over potatoes and meat.
Cover and bake about 1 hour more.
Add drained peas the last 15 minutes.
Serve with favorite tossed salad or greens.

title: noodles romanoff
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Stir together sour cream, half the cheese, chives, salt, pepper and garlic in a bowl.
Drain noodles and return to pan.
Stir in butter.
Fold in sour cream mixture. Place on a serving platter and sprinkle with the remaining cheese.

title: arlie rae's mexican cornbread
directions: Mix milk, eggs, shortening (drippings), bacon and corn.
Add dry ingredients; stir to blend.
(Add or omit hot peppers or chili powder; may want plain pepper to taste.) Pour 1/2 into oblong baking pan; sprinkle with 1/2 cheese and pour rest of corn over cheese.
Sprinkle on rest of cheese.
Bake approximately 35 to 40 minutes at 400° (preheated oven).

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle Fritos on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix and cook sugar, flour, cocoa, milk and egg yolks until thick over medium heat. Add butter and vanilla. Remove from heat. Pour into pie crusts. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add flour sifted with baking powder, 1 spoonful at a time, alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Stir in crushed pineapple and juice and blend well.
Pour batter into well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Place in cold oven. Turn oven to 325° and bake for 1 1/2 hours, or until top springs back when touched lightly.
Let stand for a few minutes in pan. Run knife around edges and remove carefully to rack or plate.
Now combine butter, powdered sugar and 1 cup drained pineapple.
Pour over cake while still hot.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Mix eggs, milk and flour with wire whisk or rotary beater until mixed well, but not foamy, then mix cheese and ham with egg mixture. Pour into pie shell.
Bake from 35 to 40 minutes on moderate temperature until puffy and golden.

title: oven brown potatoes
directions: Put oil into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Roll potatoes in the oil.
Top potatoes generously with garlic powder, salt, pepper, onion powder and paprika.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in pineapple.
Fold in bread cubes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crunchy cucumber salad
directions: In large bowl, combine soup, sour cream, celery, red onion, vinegar and parsley; stir well.
Add cucumbers, stir to mix. Cover; refrigerate until ready to serve, at least 4 hours.
Spoon into lettuce-lined serving bowl.
Makes about 4 cups, 8 servings.

title: pineapple-orange salad
directions: Drain pineapple; take juice and bring it to a boil.
Add Jell-O to dissolve it; add cheese, milk and mayonnaise.
Whip until blended, then congeal in refrigerator.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add pineapple and lemon juice.
Add beaten eggs; continue cooking until thick.
Add drained fruit, bananas and pecans.
Fold in whipped cream.
Put in quart milk cartons.
Store in freezer 24 hours or use as a dessert without freezing.
Yield:
3 1/2 quarts or 21 to 28 servings.

title: mother's cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, combine Crisco and sugars.
Mix to grainy paste, scraping down the sides of the bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add the flour mixture.
Mix on medium speed until well blended.
Add chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful or tablespoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.
May use M&M's, coconut, any flavor chips. Good plain.
Yields 6 or 7 dozen.

title: zucchini lasagna(microwave)
directions: Place zucchini in 2-quart casserole.
Cook, covered, on Full power for 7 to 10 minutes or until zucchini is thoroughly cooked. Stir halfway through cooking time.
Drain.
Set aside.
Place ground beef in 1-quart casserole.
Cook on Full power for 4 to 5 1/2 minutes or until beef is no longer pink.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Drain.
Add tomato paste, basil, oregano, salt and garlic powder to beef.
Set aside.
Combine cottage cheese and egg in small bowl.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Mix together all ingredients and spread on ham.
Roll up and refrigerate overnight.
Slice; if desired, secure the rolls with toothpicks.
Serve.

title: penuche
directions: Melt butter; cool.
Add sugar and Karo; mix.
Add milk; mix well and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cook to a soft ball stage.
Cool; add vanilla.
Beat and add nuts.
Pour into buttered pans.
This recipe makes 5 pounds.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Refrigerate.
Use to dip strawberries, cantaloupe, honeydews, watermelon or fruit of your choice.

title: deviled crabs
directions: Combine eggs, bouillon, melted butter, onion and seasonings; mix well.
Stir in crabmeat and half of crumbs.
Fill crab shells or casserole with mixture and top with remaining crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until crumbs are lightly browned.

title: herby biscuits
directions: Preheat 9-inch glass pie pan at 425° for 10 minutes.
Melt butter and add dry ingredients.
Cut biscuits in quarters and dip in mixture.
Place in preheated pan.
Pour remaining mixture over top and bake at 425° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients, making sure to add melted butter last so that if it is hot, it will not cook eggs.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Center of pie should shake slightly when it is done but it will firm up as it cools.

title: crawfish etouffee and dumplings
directions: Saute until clear.
Drain.
Add 3 to 4 tablespoons flour to make roux.
May have to add more butter.
Brown to medium dark. Add Tony Cachere while browning.
Then add onions and peppers. Cook 1 minute.
Add 1 pound crawfish tails.
Stir and simmer a few minutes (will be real thick).
Add 2 cups chicken broth.
Simmer until thick.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half, lengthwise, remove yolks and put in a bowl. Add all ingredients except paprika.
Blend until smooth.
Fill egg whites.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Chill.
Yields 12 pieces.

title: jelly roll
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 3 ingredients.
Pour into 11 x 14-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle towel with powdered sugar.
Turn cake out on towel, spread with jelly, then roll up in towel.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place into a greased casserole dish.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken; debone and shred meat.
Divide meat into 12 equal portions.
In saucepan, mix together soup, sour cream, green chilies and onion and warm over low heat.
Warm tortillas one at a time in a greased skillet.
Fill tortilla with chicken and 2 tablespoons sour cream mixture and cheese.
Garnish with green chilies or black olives.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This can be made up ahead of time and refrigerated.
Bake 35 minutes.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Two and half hours before serving, heat undiluted soup and broccoli until broccoli thawed.
In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, cook carrots and onion in 1 tablespoon oil until lightly browned.
Reduce heat to low.
Stir in 1/4 cup water. Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until veggies are tender.
Remove to bowl.

title: butter baked chicken
directions: Take 4 skinned chicken breasts, dip in milk and roll in flour. Melt the oleo in a large dish.
Place breasts, bone side up, in oleo.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400° until browned.
Pour over chicken the soup that has been mixed well with 1 can of milk or water.
Bake 30 minutes longer.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Place drained pineapple in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix sugar, flour and cheese with the reserved pineapple juice.
Layer on top of pineapple.
Melt butter and mix with crushed cracker crumbs.
Layer mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add melted margarine and vinegar, then raisins, coconut and pecans.
Pour into unbaked shell and bake at 325° until top is brown.

title: special k bar cookie
directions: Heat Karo and sugar until dissolved.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until creamy and blended.
Add cereal.
Mix and pat into pan.
Melt chips and spread over top.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Sift together flour, bran, sugar, baking powder and baking soda into a large bowl.
Combine buttermilk and egg whites in a small bowl.
Add to flour mixture; stir until smooth.
Pour 1/4 cup batter on hot griddle coated with cooking spray.
Over medium heat, pour batter to make 6-inch cakes; brown and turn over to brown on opposite side.
Serve with fresh fruit, sugar or syrup.

title: easy microwave potatoes
directions: Scrub and dry potatoes.
Pierce each potato with a fork 3 or 4 times.
Arrange potatoes in a circle on a microwave-safe plate. Cook in microwave oven on High power for 12 minutes, rotating every 4 minutes.

title: great potato soup
directions: In large pot, cover vegetables and potatoes with water and chicken broth.
Simmer until tender and stir in potato flakes and cream cheese.
Then add evaporated milk.
Heat and stir until cheese melts, but don't boil.
Makes 4 servings.
One serving = 1 pro, 1 bread, 1/2 milk, 1/2 vegetable and 5 optional.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix by hand the sugar, flour, eggs and margarine, then add the nuts, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix
cream
cheese
and
sour cream in a separate bowl. Mix first
5 ingredients and pour 1/2 in bottom of bowl (congeal). Then
spread cream cheese mixture on top and add other half.

title: beef taco dip
directions: Cook beef until browned.
Drain the beef and add the taco seasoning, tomato paste, beer and cheese.
Cook for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: pumpkin stack-ups
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices.
Add nuts.
Stir ice cream to soften.
Fold into pumpkin mixture.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix thawed potatoes with melted margarine in large bowl.
Add all other ingredients, mixing well after each addition and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch or 10 x 15-inch baking dish.
Cover with additional crushed corn flakes and bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Mix together zucchini, shortening, eggs and sugar.
Add spices and soda to flour and blend into zucchini.
Stir in oatmeal, nuts and raisins.

title: earnest rohrer's blueberry cream pie
directions: Mix all together. Bake pie crust. Let cool. Slice 1 banana in pie crust. Add pie filling and refrigerate until cold.

title: taco salad
directions: Fix salad, then add Ranch Style beans (drained).
Smash up bag of Doritos.
Add cooked hamburger meat.
Add enough dressing to taste.
Mix together.
Top with cheese.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with 1/4 cup margarine and sugar; whip until a cream.
Set aside.
Crumble Oreos in a food processor or blender to the consistency of dirt.
Mix the pudding with the milk.
Add cream cheese mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Mix all ingredients except oil.
Heat oil in skillet;
fry patties approximately for 2 minutes on each side.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rich and charlie salad(same as pasta house)
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and put in refrigerator.
When ready to serve, pour over lettuce and onion.

title: vegetarian italian meatballs
directions: Beat eggs with salt.
Saute onions in oil; cool.
When cooled, add onions to egg mixture.
Add walnuts, seasoning and enough oatmeal to make mixture into round balls.
Let mixture stand for 10 minutes.
Form mixture into round balls and brown in 1/4 cup oil. Put meatballs in casserole dish and pour mushroom soup over meatballs; simmer for 30 minutes (on top of stove).
Serves 10.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer 20 minutes.
Add 2 teaspoons bitters.

title: creamed broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes and drain.
Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Top with Cheez-Its crackers (crumbled). Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: elephant's jug
directions: You crack 2 eggs open.
Put them in a pan to cook it for 1 minute and put it on a plate.

title: fluffy white icing
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Very slowly add sugar syrup to two unbeaten egg whites; beat constantly with electric mixer until soft peak forms, about 7 minutes.
Beat in 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: pink divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in a 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Cook over high heat without stirring until mixture reaches hard ball stage (260°).
Place egg whites (at room temperature) in a large mixing bowl.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Pour hot syrup mixture in a very thin stream over egg whites while beating constantly at high speed of an electric mixer.
Continue beating for 3 to 5 minutes or until mixture holds its shape.
Add food coloring and vanilla while beating with mixer.
Quickly drop mixture by heaping teaspoonful on waxed paper.
Press a pecan half on top of each. Cool.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli, drain; reserve 1/3 cup liquid, adding water if necessary.
Stir bouillon into reserved liquid.
In a blender container, combine broccoli, reserved liquid and sour cream. Cover; blend until smooth, stopping to scrape down sides of container as necessary.
Pour broccoli mixture into a saucepan. Stir in Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder; heat through. Transfer to a fondue pot; place over a fondue burner.
Serve with raw veggies, crackers or breadsticks.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream oleo, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add one teaspoon vanilla and butter flavoring.
Add 1 cup 7-Up.
Add flour and mix well.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump cherries and crushed pineapple in 9 x 12-inch cake pan. Sprinkle box of dry cake mix on top.
Slice the margarine to cover top of mix.
Sprinkle pecans over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: milky wonder cake
directions: Melt bars and 1 stick margarine in saucepan over very low heat.
Beat 1 stick margarine (soft) and 2 cups sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs to butter-sugar mixture, one at a time and beat well.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, flour and salt in saucepan.
Add milk and margarine.
Cook to boiling; lower heat and cook 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add vanilla.
Serve as topping for ice cream or desserts.
Half recipe for smaller amount.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, sugars, vanilla extract, eggs and water until fluffy.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool slightly and remove to rack.

title: my favorite beef stroganoff
directions: In frying pan, brown floured cubes of beef.
Add onion and 1/4 cup of water and 1/4 cup butter or margarine and bouillon cubes. Simmer until onions are tender.
Remove from frypan, removing all brown particles too.
Put meat, onion and juice in roast pan, adding mushrooms and mushroom soup and 1 cup water.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add sour cream and noodles cooked according to package directions.
Cook 10 minutes longer.
Serve hot.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mash beans well. Use the juice.
Beat eggs.
Add all the ingredients; mix well.
Pour in unbaked pie shells (thin shells). Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 300°.
Tastes like a pecan-coconut pie.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: In large bowl, mix by hand or electric mixer on medium speed all ingredients except zucchini.
Fold in zucchini.
Turn into buttered 10-inch deep dish pie pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Boil 2 or 3 chicken breasts.
Cut up in cubes or strips.
Melt butter; brown mushrooms.
Add broth, chicken, salt, pepper and pimientos, stirring constantly until thick.
Add a little sauce to egg yolks.
Blend and return to mixture.
Continue over heat 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve hot over hot biscuits.

title: russian salad
directions: Mix jello, cream cheese, marshmallows and boiling water and bring to a boil over medium heat until melted.
Mix remaining ingredients and add all together.
Pour in 8 x 8-inch dish and allow to jell for 3 or 4 hours.

title: squash casserole (yellow)
directions: Combine stuffing with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until top is golden brown around edges.

title: tomato, cucumber and onion salad
directions: Combine vegetable oil, vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and parsley
into
jar;
shake
well.
Combine vegetables in bowl; pour marinade
over them.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: grapefruit pineapple shake
directions: In a blender container, process grapefruit juice, pineapple and ice cream until smooth and frothy.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheesy chicken rolls
directions: Mix
chicken
and
1/2 of cheese in bowl.
Separate and roll out
crescent rolls.
Put 1 tablespoon of chicken-cheese mixture in	each
roll, roll up the crescent roll and place in baking dish.
In
pot, mix soup, milk and rest of cheese until cheese
is melted.
Pour
soup
over crescent rolls.	Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until brown on top.

title: our favorite hot dish
directions: Brown beef in a skillet. Drain off grease. Add approximately 2 cups water and soup mix. Bring to a boil and add rice. Stir well and simmer with lid on skillet. Add additional water, as needed, if it gets too dry
while cooking. It takes about 15 minutes for the rice to cook. Serve with catsup or tomato sauce. Top with cheese if desired.

title: pralines cookies
directions: Break graham crackers apart at seams and place side by side on a cookie sheet.
Boil the butter, oleo and sugar together for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Sprinkle generously with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: frosted cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 cup liquid and heat to boiling.
Dissolve Jell-O in this liquid and cool.
Gently stir in ginger ale.
Blend in pineapple, cranberry sauce and 1/2 cup pecans.
Pour into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch casserole and refrigerate until firm.
Beat cream cheese and Cool Whip together with electric mixer.
Spread on top of set gelatin. Sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: pickle sticks
directions: Place turmeric, mustard seed, salt, vinegar and sugar in a saucepan.
Bring to rolling boil.
Pack 6-quart jars full of cucumbers cut lengthwise.
Pour solution over cucumbers and seal.

title: beef and vegetable soup
directions: In large pot, put soup bone, meat, one tablespoon salt, peppercorns, bay leaf and two quarts water.
Bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer in a covered pot for one hour.

title: easy make dills
directions: Scald 6 quart jars.

title: eiou gumbo(you invite everyone over)
directions: In large gumbo pot, cook chicken in water with seafood seasoning.
When tender, remove chicken, cool, debone and chop. In skillet, make a roux.
Slowly brown flour in oil to a dark chocolate color, stirring constantly.
Add all vegetables, except okra and tomatoes.
When vegetables are clear, add to stock water. Add okra and tomatoes.
Remove seasoning packet; add remaining seasonings.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Add cooked chicken, fish and seafood to mixture.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.
You need a big gumbo pot for this.

title: miniature cheese cakes
directions: Line muffin pans with liners, then fill with vanilla wafers. In small bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Fill liners 3/4 full of mixture. Bake in oven at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until mixture is set. Serves 24.

title: homemade buttermilk biscuits
directions: Add everything together.
Stir with a fork until the dough is together.
Add flour if the dough is too moist.
Roll the dough out and get a small cup to cut out the biscuits.
Put the biscuits in the oven at about 375°.
It will be done in about 20 to 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Reserve 2/3 cup dry cake mix.
In large bowl, combine remaining cake mix, butter and 1 of the eggs; mix well.
Pat into well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Combine reserved cake mix, pumpkin, sugar, eggs and dash of salt. Beat at medium speed for 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour over partially baked layer.
Top with nuts.
Bake at 350° until set, 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars.
Refrigerate.
Makes 32.

title: mary's french peppermint
directions: Cream butter, sugar and melted chocolate to eggs. Beat mixture with rotary beater. Add peppermint and pour into crust.
Chill for 1 hour. Top with whipped cream.

title: shipwreck
directions: Place potatoes in casserole dish.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Spread over potatoes.
Put pinto beans over meat.
Mix soup and water and pour over beans.
Salt to taste.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, stir first 5 ingredients until will blended. Stir in pecans, pour into pie shell and bake at 350 degrees for 50 to 55 minutes.
Until a knife inserted half way between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool.
Serves 8.

title: easy drop danish
directions: Mix baking mix, margarine and sugar until crumbly.
Stir in milk until dough form.
Beat 15 strokes.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls, about 2-inches apart, onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Make a shallow well in center of each with back of spoon. Fill with 1 teaspoon preserves.
Bake until golden, 10 to 15 minutes.
While warm, drizzle with glaze.
Makes 12 danish.

title: pork chop supreme
directions: Place browned pork chops in a casserole.
Place onion ring and pepper slice on each pork chop.
Put 1 tablespoon rice on each. Add tomatoes with seasoning and sugar.
Spoon juice from tomatoes on each rice chop.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: butterscotch marble cake
directions: With beater, mix and combine first 5 ingredients until all lumps are gone.
Pour 2/3 mixture into greased and floured tube pan.
Set aside.
Add the Hershey's chocolate syrup into other 1/3 remaining batter.
Pour over top of butterscotch layer.
Do not stir or mix.
Leave chocolate on top. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool slightly (20 to 25 minutes), inverting pan.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over top of cake while still warm.
Serve warm.

title: strawberry cream cake
directions: Bake cake.
Store in refrigerator uncovered overnight.
Mix berries and ice cream into Jell-O and water.
Set in refrigerator until stiff enough to spread.
Cut cake in 3 rings.
Put bottom layer in cold pan.
Spread with mixture.
Repeat other 2 layers. Mix whipped cream; add sugar.
Unmold cake.
Frost with whipped cream, filling hole until flat across top.
Leave in refrigerator until serving.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring together the first 3 ingredients for 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Blend in next 3 ingredients.
Pour over popped corn. Mix well.
Bake in two 9 x 13-inch pans at 250° for 40 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes from bottom.
Spread on wax paper to cool.

title: canned green beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and boil for 15 minutes.
Pack beans, boiling hot, in boiling hot jars and seal immediately with hot lids.
When opened, these beans require longer cooking time, but have a better flavor than cold packed beans.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Combine water, shortening, sugar and salt in a small saucepan. Cook, stirring constantly, until shortening melts.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in mixture.
Add egg; mix well.
Stir in flour.
Spoon dough into greased muffin tins.
Fill half full. Cover and let rise in warm place (85°), free from draft for 1 hour, until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 14 minutes or until golden brown.

title: easy southern corn custard
directions: Combine eggs, corn, butter, milk, seasonings and sugar.
Blend well.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with crumbs mixed with butter.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 40 minutes or until firm.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Then add eggs, vanilla, salt and molasses.
Sift together flour, baking powder and soda.
Mix into creamed mixture.
Add oatmeal, coconut, pecans and Rice Krispies. Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: molasses shoo-fly cake
directions: Make crumbs by combining flour, sugar and shortening.
Line pie plate with pastry.
Dissolve the soda in the hot water and combine with the molasses.
Pour into the pastry lined pan; top with the crumbs and bake in moderate oven at 350° until firm. Save some of the liquid to put on top of crumbs.

title: canned okra
directions: Put salt, vinegar and water in large pan and boil for 1 minute.
Add okra and cook until okra changes color.
Set off the stove and dip the okra into hot canning jars with a slotted spoon. Seal.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix top 5 ingredients together.

title: feathery cheesecake
directions: Beat 1/2 cup butter with cream cheese and egg yolks until smooth and creamy.
Add sugar, cornstarch, baking powder, lemon rind, lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Beat egg whites with salt until soft peaks form.
Fold egg whites into creamed mixture and turn into pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until center feels firm to the touch.
If desired, fill with pie filling of your choice.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Cream together cream cheese and Cheddar until well blended. Add other ingredients, except pecans. Mix well. Shape into ball and rollin chopped pecans. Wrap and chill for 24 hours in refrigerator. Serve with crackers or chips. Yield: 1 1/2 pounds cheese ball.

title: yuletide toffee squares
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan. Combine oats, brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Firmly press mixture into prepared pan.
Bake for about 18 minutes, or until mixture is brown and bubbly.
Remove from oven immediately.
Sprinkle chocolate chips evenly over toffee; let stand 10 minutes.
Spread chocolate evenly with knife; sprinkle with nuts.
Cool completely.
Cut into squares; store, lightly covered, in a cool, dry place.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent biscuits into and halfway up the sides of 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan. Bake at room temperature given on biscuit can. Let cool. Blend Hidden Valley Ranch salad dressing mix until smooth, then spread on cooled crust. Put finely chopped vegetables, meat and cheese on top. You can use broccoli, cauliflower, fresh mushrooms, green onion, radishes, pepperoni, cooked sausage, ham and shredded cheese. Just use your imagination. Chill before serving.

title: shrimp and crab salad
directions: Mix pasta, shrimp and crab.
Add all other ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Bake pie crust; cool.
Mix peanut butter and confectioners sugar until crumbly and light brown.
Sprinkle some of the mixture in crust.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Line cupcake pans with liners.
Place vanilla wafer in bottom of each liner.
In small mixer bowl beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Fill the liners 2/3 full with cheese mixture.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until set.
Remove from oven and top each cheesecake with a spoonful of pie filing.
Chill.
Makes 24 cheesecakes.

title: fudgie scotch squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Grease well a square 9 x 9-inch pan.
Spread mixture into pan and press down.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown on top.
Remove and let stand 1 to 2 hours.
Cut into squares.
Makes approximately 24 squares.

title: five hour stew
directions: Mix all of ingredients in casserole to be covered, sprinkling bread crumbs on last.
Cook stew in oven 5 hours at 250°.
Can dress this recipe up with a little Burgundy wine, mushrooms, potatoes or dumplings added near end of cooking time.
If using potatoes, add at beginning.

title: snowballs
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten egg yolks, crushed pineapple, nuts and lastly, the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Take 3 or 4 vanilla wafers and put together with filling between.
(This makes one snowball.)

title: lib's pineapple cake
directions: Prepare cake:
Blend cake mix, orange sections (use liquid), eggs and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Divide batter among 3 greased and floured 9-inch layer cake pans.
Bake in 350° oven only 17 minutes.

title: no fail fudge(microwave)
directions: Blend powdered sugar and cocoa in mixing bowl.
Add milk and butter.
Cook on High for 2 minutes (in microwave).
You do not need to mix these ingredients thoroughly before microwaving. Remove bowl from microwave and stir just to mix ingredients.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir until blended.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Place in freezer for 20 minutes.

title: gravy baked pork chops
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with salt and pepper.
Brown in hot shortening.
Pour off drippings.
Pour around the chops a mixture of soup, evaporated milk and water.
Cover and bake at 350° about 1 hour or until chops are tender.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together and let set for 20 to 30 minutes in refrigerator. Pour over cheese mixture and refrigerate.

title: southern pralines
directions: Note:
Real butter is a must for this recipe.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Arrange potatoes, onion and cheese in greased baking dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° until tender.

title: wonderful carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Slowly beat in oil.
Add dry ingredients slowly, beating until smooth.
Mix in carrots and raisins.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round baking pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Allow to cool before removing from pans.
Frost with coconut cream or cream cheese frosting.

title: blue cheese dip
directions: While mixing cheeses and seasonings, add vinegar and buttermilk; blend well.
Slowly pour in oil; chill and serve.

title: grandma cotter's breakfast
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Whip eggs and add milk, mustard, cheese and salt.
Break bread into small pieces and add to egg mixture.
Fold in sausage.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch greased casserole or pan.

title: french quarter cheese
directions: Combine cream cheese, garlic and onion with a fork. Shape into 6 x 1 inch disk, place on a serving plate and refrigerate. Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan, heating until butter melts. Cover chilled cheese with nut mixture. Wrap and chill. Serve at room temperature with crackers. Serves 10-12.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crumbs.
Put crumbs on top or a can of French fried onion rings.
Bake at 350° about an hour.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: no cook million dollar pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Drain and mash peaches.
Add well drained pineapple.
Mix condensed milk, juice from lemons, coconut, pecans and Cool whip. Add to fruit mixture. Put into pie shells.
Freeze 1 hour before serving or store in refrigerator overnight.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef and pork sausage together.
Add eggs, milk, catsup, sage, salt and pepper. Also add onion soup mix, chopped green pepper and crushed crackers.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Spoon mixture into 2- 9x13 inch pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Freezes well.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese and add rest of ingredients except nuts. Roll in chopped nuts.
This improves in flavor if made several hours in advance.

title: our favorite meatloaf
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, eggs, garlic, salt, pepper with 1 cup of tomato sauce.
Shape into loaf on broiler pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Pour remaining Hunt's sauce on top of loaf spreading over entire top with back of spoon.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: one dish pork chop bake
directions: Cut pork chops into bite size pieces.
Place in greased casserole.
Place cut up onions and potatoes over chops.
Mix soups together and pour over.
Do not stir.
Bake at 400° until done, about 1 hour.
Before baking, cover with cracker crumbs or crumbled potato chips.

title: chili meatball soup
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, egg and 2 tablespoons chili mix; mix well.
Shape into tiny meatballs; fry in oil until brown.
In pan, combine remainder of seasoning mix, water, tomatoes and macaroni.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Add meatballs to sauce; heat a few more minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: japanese salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl. Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables, tossing gently. Cover and chill 8 hours or overnight.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add water and vanilla.
Mix well. Blend in flour and nuts.
Shape into balls or fingers.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for about 20 minutes.
Remove from pan; roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: marinara sauce
directions: In saucepan, heat oil and add onion, mushrooms and garlic. Saute until tender. Add tomatoes, Splenda, basil, oregano, butter, salt and pepper. Simmer 30 minutes.

title: rice pancakes
directions: Cook rice, soak in milk overnight.
Sift together, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
In separate bowl, mix eggs, milk, shortening and rice mixture.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix well. Fry in nonstick frying pan, turning once to brown.
Makes enough pancakes for 25 people.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Saute onion and margarine until golden.
Add flour and water gradually, stirring constantly until thickened.
Blend in cheese. Add spinach.
Fold in eggs until well blended.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until knife inserted comes out clean.
(The mixing is done in skillet; onion is browned in as you are stirring while heat is still on.)

title: italian baked haddock
directions: Lightly oil fillets and place in baking pan.
With fork, crush together tomatoes and spices and pour over fish.
Drizzle with olive oil.
Cover dish tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until fish is flaky.
Serve with fine spaghetti and steamed broccoli.

title: egg and sausage souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours. Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Pour mixture into casserole.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: caesar salad ala new york times(serves 6)
directions: Sprinkle bowl with salt; rub with garlic.
Add mustard, lemon juice and Tabasco; stir until the salt dissolves.
Add olive oil; stir rapidly until the liquid blends.
Wash romaine well; dry the leaves with a towel.
Tear the leaves into small size pieces; add to the bowl.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Add the anchovies and break the egg over the salad.
Sprinkle croutons and mix gently, but thoroughly, through.

title: trish's 7 layer salad
directions: Arrange vegetables in layers.
Do not toss.
Spread Miracle Whip salad dressing on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Sprinkle bacon on top before serving.

title: popcorn holiday style
directions: Roast nuts in a 350° oven for 15 minutes; stir once.
Cook the brown sugar, margarine and salt.
Mix popcorn and nuts.
Pour melted ingredients over top; stir good.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Stir once during baking.
Cool in pan.
Use large roasting pan to make.

title: alice's sugar cookies
directions: Beat sugar into soft butter.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, sifted together.
Mix well; chill at least 1 hour.
Roll out a small portion of the dough at a time.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool cookies on wire racks or cutting boards before storing in tins with tight lids.

title: chicken and sausage risotto
directions: In a large pot on medium heat olive oil, salt, pepper, crushed red pepper, crushed garlic for 2 minutes (do not burn garlic). Put in onions, stir, and cook until clear. Toss in meats; stir constantly until partially cooked thru. In a separate pot (or tea kettle works great) bring chicken broth to boil. Pour rice into pot, stir. Add enough broth to cover ingredients, increase heat to bubbling stirring constantly. Can also be made with any meat or vegetable. Use as a meal or side dish.

title: christmas punch
directions: Pour juice and ginger ale over ice in punch bowl and serve. Makes 25 to 30 servings.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pie filling, Cool Whip, pineapple, marshmallows and pecans.
Mix well and chill.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Place layer of vegetables in order given in crock-pot.
Season with salt and pepper.
Brown hamburger.
Put on top of last layer of vegetables.
Mix soup with water and pour over hamburger.
Cook on low heat for 6 to 8 hours.
If you want to use high heat, cook for 2 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Mix shortening with sugar and cream well.
Add salt, extract, flour and nuts.
Chill dough until easy to handle.
Make dough into small balls and place on cookie sheet or flatten bottom of floured tumbler before baking.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.

title: dinosaur s'mores
directions: Place cookie picture side down on microwave-safe plate.
Place marshmallows and chocolate chips on cookie.
Top with another cookie (picture side up).
Cook on High.
Heat for 30 seconds to 1 minute (until marshmallows melt).
Yields 6 S'mores.

title: tomato preserves
directions: Scald, peel and chop tomatoes.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Measure 3 cups into 6 or 8-quart pan.
Add lemon juice, oleo, Sure-Jell, allspice, cinnamon and cloves.
Bring to boil.
Add sugar.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Put in pint jars and seal by inverting jars for 5 minutes.

title: pizza biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger meat and onion in skillet.
Roll out biscuits onto greased pan.
Spread spaghetti sauce over each biscuit.
Sprinkle hamburger and onion mixture on biscuits.
Sprinkle biscuits with cheese.
Cook at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pink stuff
directions: Combine pineapple and jello, boil one minute.
Stir and let chill in refrigerator until soft set.
Then fold in cottage cheese, Cool Whip and pecans until smooth.

title: baxter's chess pie
directions: Melt the margarine.
Add the remaining ingredients; beat well. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Coat each biscuit piece in mixture of 3/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Place in a cake pan or Bundt cake pan.
Melt the butter, brown sugar, 3/4 cup granulated sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon together.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Pat hamburger into a 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with onion flakes and drained peas or green beans.
Cover with undiluted soup.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together
sugar, flour, cocoa, margarine, egg yolks and milk; mix well.
Pour into uncooked pie crust.
Cook until set at 350°.

title: mardi gras salad
directions: Drain juices from beans, peas and pimento.
Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl with cover.
(Plastic is best.) Let marinate in covered bowl in refrigerator 12 hours.

title: creamy cole slaw
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Mix remaining ingredients well and pour over cabbage.
Mix lightly and refrigerate.

title: linda's tuna salad
directions: Mix together tuna and other ingredients.
This is great on pita bread!

title: mexican chicken
directions: Line a baking dish, 9 x 13-inch, with the package of small egg noodles.
Pour chicken broth over.
Add chicken.
Saute onion, green pepper and celery in butter.
Add cumin and curry powder to vegetables.
Pour this over chicken.
Mix tomatoes and soups together.
Pour mixture over all.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 300° for one hour.
Serves 8.

title: guessies spaghetti goulash
directions: Brown ground meat.
Add soup, spaghetti, chili sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Put in casserole and lay cheese on top. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: cheese stuffed pecans
directions: Cream cheese together; spread mixture on flat surface of one nut half and top with another half, sandwich fashion.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields about 120 stuffed pecans.
Great for a party.

title: flubber
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup soda.
Bring other 1/2 cup soda to a boil.
Mix soda/gelatin mixture with the hot soda; add dry milk and mix well.
Add extracts and sweetener.
Place over ice and whip until fluffy.
Chill until set and cut into squares.

title: baked squash(serves 6-8)
directions: Wash and cut up squash.
Boil until tender, drain and mash. Add all ingredients, except 1/2 butter to the squash.
Melt remaining butter.
Pour mixture into 2 quart casserole.
Top with butter and sprinkle with extra bread crumbs.
Bake at 375 for one hour.

title: golden punch(golden anniversary punch)
directions: Stir Jell-O and boiling water until Jell-O dissolves.
Add sugar and stir until sugar melts.
Add the juices and 8 quarts of water.
Put in containers and freeze.
Add 1 quart of 7-Up or ginger ale to 2 quarts of frozen punch.
(I freeze only half the punch, when ready to serve, slightly thaw punch, then add 1 quart 7-Up or ginger ale to 1 quart frozen punch and 1 quart unfrozen punch.)
Serve as slush type consistency.

title: rhubarb pudding
directions: Cut rhubarb in 1-inch pieces.
Place in bottom of well-greased 9 x 10-inch or 10 x 12-inch pan.
Cover with remaining ingredients.
Bake for 34 to 44 minutes in 350° oven or until brown.

title: stew meat
directions: Brown stew meat.
Combine all other ingredients.
Cook, covered, in oven for 3 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with noodles with butter and garlic added to noodles first.

title: whole wheat rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 cups warm water.
Mix in Wesson oil, brown sugar, granulated sugar, eggs and salt.
Mix well and add whole wheat flour and Occident or high gluten flour.
Let rise in warm place for 2 hours.
Punch down and let rise 1 hour.
Shape in small balls and place in cake pans (ice cream scoop works great).
Let rise 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Season flour with salt and pepper.
Cut the tomatoes into thick slices and coat on both sides with seasoned flour or corn meal.
Melt butter in an iron skillet until it is sizzling hot, but do not let it brown.
Re-flour the tomatoes and place in skillet in one layer.
When golden brown, turn and brown the other side.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve immediately.

title: bacon and tomato potato skins(microwave)
directions: Scrub potatoes thoroughly and prick with a fork.
Arrange on a microwave-safe plate.
Cook on High for 17 to 22 minutes, rearranging once (or bake in a 425° oven for 40 to 45 minutes). Cool.
Halve each potato lengthwise.
Scoop out the inside of each potato half, leaving about 1/4-inch thick shell.
Cover and chill the white part of potatoes for another use.
Combine the cooking oil, chili powder and Tabasco sauce.
With a pastry brush, brush the insides of the potato halves with the oil mixture.
Cut the potato halves in half lengthwise and return to the baking sheet. Sprinkle potato quarters with bacon, tomato and green onion.
Top with cheese.
Microwave until heated through and cheese is melted (or bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes).
Serve with sour cream.

title: walnut fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
In small bowl of electric mixer at medium speed, beat butter, sugar and eggs until mixture is light and fluffy.
Beat in melted chocolate and vanilla. At low speed, blend in flour mixture.
Fold in chopped walnuts. Spread evenly in prepared pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. With sharp knife, cut into squares.
Let cool completely in pan. Makes 16.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour 3/4 full into greased muffin tins.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Beat eggs and water together just to blend; set aside.
Heat oil until hot in large frying pan or wok over medium heat.
Add green onions and stir-fry 30 seconds.
Add eggs and scramble. Stir in rice and cook until heated, gently separating grains.
Add shrimp and soy sauce; cook and stir until thoroughly heated. Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased tube pan lined with wax paper.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: apple dip
directions: Blend together all ingredients except apple and orange slices. Wash and slice apples; dip in orange juice.
Drain.
Arrange in concentric circle on plate and place.
Put dip in center in a bowl. Sprinkle dip with additional chopped peanuts.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: corn and wild rice risotto
directions: Melt unsalted butter and saute onion and red and yellow bell peppers.
Add the corn and rice and then the cream.
Stir well. Cook down a bit until slightly thickened.
Add the Parmesan and season with salt and pepper just before serving.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; fold in 1 cup miniature marshmallows. Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and 1/2 cup pecans and dot with butter.
Bake on 350° until the marshmallows are melted.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar, softened oleo and milk.
Put flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add flour mixture to the first mixture. Put batter in pan and cover as follows: sour cherries, 1 cup sugar and water or juice from can.
Bring cherries to boil.
Let cool before putting on top of batter.
(Bake in moderate oven from 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.)

title: basil, walnut, garlic pesto sauce
directions: Combine the basil, parsley, walnuts, cheese, olives, olive oil and garlic in a small bowl.
Stir to blend.
Toss hot pasta with the sauce and serve at once.
Yields 1 cup, or enough sauce for 1 pound of pasta.

title: one dish meal cinnamon pie
directions: Brown and season meat. Place in a casserole. Drain English peas and pour over meat.
Drain corn, pour over peas. Place mashed potatoes over entire casserole dish.
Dot with butter and pour 1/4 cup milk over all.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
This will be lightly brown.

title: chocolate chip muffin mix
directions: In a large bowl, combine first five ingredients.
Mix well. Add next five ingredients individually and mix together each time until combined.
Fold in chocolate chips. Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups two-thirds full.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool for five minutes before removing from pans Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: raspberry chiffon marble
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add ice cubes and stir constantly until gelatin starts to thicken.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Remove 3/4 cup gelatin mixture; set aside.
Fold Dream Whip into remaining gelatin.
Alternately spoon plain gelatin and whipped topping mixture into 4 dessert glasses.
Carefully zigzag spatula or knife through mixture to marble.
Chill.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients and set aside; combine eggs, oil, carrots and pecans until well blended.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Mix at a low speed until sugar dissolves (approximately 2 minutes).
Bake at 300° for 50 minutes or until cake begins to pull away from sides of the pan.

title: sensational salsa
directions: In a medium size bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well. Cover and let stand in refrigerator at least 2 hours.
Salsa will get hotter the longer it stands.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: bewitching blueberry pancakes
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Stir in all liquids.
As you stir in the blueberries (this is the magic part), say three times:

title: prune breakfast muffins
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, spices, prunes and walnuts.
Set aside.
Mix oil, eggs and vanilla.
Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk.
Pour all liquid ingredients over dry ingredients. Stir until just blended.
Spoon into muffin cups.
Makes 16 to 18 muffins.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening thoroughly.
Add sugar gradually, then beaten eggs and peanut butter.
Sift flour, soda and salt several times. Add gradually, mixing well.
Shape into balls the size of a walnut.
Place on cookie sheet and flatten with fork to about 1/4-inch.
Bake until brown at 400°.
Makes 100 cookies.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
Cook carrots and celery until tender; set aside.
Cook macaroni and cheese according to directions on box.
When macaroni and cheese is done, add chicken and vegetable. Mix well and serve.

title: big red meat loaf
directions: Mix; press into greased bread pan. Top with sauce.

title: coq au vin
directions: In Dutch oven over medium heat, cook salt pork until golden and crisp, stirring often.
With slotted spoon, remove pork to paper towels to drain.
In drippings, cook chicken until browned, about 20 minutes.
Remove to medium bowl.
Spoon off all but about 1/4 cup fat; add mushrooms, onions, shallots, and garlic.
Cook until just wilted, about 5 minutes.
Stir in wine, water, thyme, pepper, bay leaf, and parsley.
Place chicken and salt pork over vegetables.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover; simmer 20 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.
In cup, blend butter and flour.
Remove chicken and vegetables to platter; discard bay leaf and parsley.
Blend flour mixture into pan juices. Heat to boiling, stirring.
Spoon over chicken.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; put in a baking dish and cover with the following:

title: peter's favorite carrots
directions: Use sliced and cooked carrots or baby carrots, cooked.
Cook a diced onion with the carrots.
Mix all ingredients except vegetables.
Cook on top of stove for about 5 minutes to thoroughly combine ingredients.
Mix with vegetables and simmer for a few minutes.

title: julie's chili(chili cook off entry - 1994)
directions: Cook ground chuck with onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
(For the chili powder, red pepper, black pepper and salt, add as much as your heart desires.)
Simmer.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mash sweet potatoes. Add butter, sugar, milk and juice.
Spoon up mixture.
Shape around marshmallows.
Roll ball in crushed cornflakes.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until marshmallows begin to ooze. Makes 8 balls.

title: blt dip
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients except lettuce; chill if desired. Garnish with lettuce and serve with your favorite dippers. Makes 3 cups.

title: old fashioned chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut up fryer. Cover with water in large Dutch oven. Salt. Boil until tender. Remove chicken from broth; set aside to fry.

title: trail mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together and keep in an airtight container.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Mix soda and vanilla in buttermilk.
In a separate bowl, cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and mix.
Add flour and rest of ingredients with milk mixture.
Put in a 9 x 13 or Bundt pan and bake at 325 degrees for 40 minutes.
Do not ice, but sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and cream cheese until smooth. Add other ingredients. Pour into pan and freeze. Cut into squares to serve on lettuce.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: easy taco casserole
directions: Cook beef and drain.
Mix taco seasoning with beef according to directions.
In meantime, cook spaghetti (broken in 2 to 3-inch pieces) and drain.
Mix beef mixture with spaghetti.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with spaghetti beef mixture.
Top with sour cream, cheese, lettuce, tomato and onion (or any other of your taco favorite additions).
Top with Fritos.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix cake as directed. Add other ingredients. Bake in 2 loaf pans or a 9 x 13-inch pan at 300°.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, Accent salt, Worcestershire sauce and onions.
Add 1/2 package of beef to mixture.
Roll into a ball and roll in rest of beef.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Sprinkle apples with cinnamon.
Roll apples up in the crescent roll dough.
Bring water, brown sugar and margarine to a boil. Pour over apples in a glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes covered with foil.
Bake an additional 10 minutes uncovered.
Serve with ice cream.

title: quick and easy french bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Beat egg; add oil, sugar and salt.
Add yeast, dry milk and cheese.
Add flour.
Knead approximately 5 minutes.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Dough will be quite soft.
Form loaf; brush with egg yolk and sprinkle with sesame seed (optional).
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
One medium loaf.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Boil together over low flame the sugar, milk and butter for 18 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and place candy and chocolate chips in large bowl.
Pour sugar mixture over.
Beat well.
Add Marshmallow Creme and nuts.
Beat until mixed and cool. Pour into pan and cut in squares.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together in large bowl.
Spread into greased pan and bake.

title: butter spritz cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Beat in egg and almond extract.
Blend in flour.
Divide dough into groups. Add a few drops of food coloring, depends on season or leave plain.

title: hunters stew
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet without shortening.
Combine other ingredients with meat.
Simmer until frozen vegetables are cooked.

title: corn relish
directions: Cut corn from cob.
Place in large stainless steel, glass, ceramic or unchipped enamel saucepot.
Cover with boiling water and boil for 5 minutes.
Drain off liquid and add remaining ingredients.
Have jars ready to fill.
Simmer relish for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Bring to boil.
Carefully pack relish boiling hot into pint jars.
Leave 1/4-inch headspace. Remove air bubbles with nonmetal utensil.
Wipe jar rim clean, place lid on jar and screw band down evenly and firmly.
Process 15 minutes in boiling water.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix butter, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Stir in flour, salt and nuts.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: fettuccine with shrimp and broccoli
directions: In large frying pan, heat olive oil over low heat.
Add and saute garlic, very careful not to burn.
Add broccoli and cover; stir occasionally until crisp-tender.
Raise heat and saute shrimp until pink.
Add the wine and season with salt, pepper and parsley or basil.
Cook for about 2 more minutes.
Add cooked fettuccine and cook over low heat for 2 minutes longer.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: 20 minute chicken parmesan
directions: With hand, flatten chicken; dip into egg, then bread crumbs. In skillet, melt butter and brown chicken.
Add spaghetti sauce. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese; cover and simmer 5 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Oil pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Melt oleo and pour over cornbread mix. Add eggs.
Mix well.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake at 400° for about 1 hour or until done.
Check at 45 minutes.
I like to use fresh broccoli when I have it.

title: german christmas cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Sift cinnamon with flour.
Add to creamed mixture.
If this is too moist, add more flour.
Roll out to 1/4 to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut in desired shapes.
Bake until golden brown, 350° for 20 minutes.
Fill with jam (2 cookies) and roll in sugar while still warm.

title: low-fat carrot cake
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes.
Add pineapple, spices, eggs and oil.

title: crock-pot stuffing
directions: Mix all, except crumbs, then add the crumbs.
Cook in crock-pot on high 45 minutes.
Reduce heat to low for 6 hours.

title: fantastic vegetable dip
directions: Steam carrots, broccoli and cauliflower briefly 3 minutes in lightly salted garlic water (refrigerate separately for 2+ hours.)

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Fry bacon. Tear into small pieces. Cut cauliflower, green pepper and onions into small pieces. Mix with bacon. Mix together Miracle Whip and sugar. Add to vegetables. Add shredded cheese. Refrigerate.

title: chicken and biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Saut chopped onion in butter.
Combine soup, onion, sour cream, milk and salt and pepper in medium bowl.
Spoon into baking dish (prepared). Bake 15 minutes and remove.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup cheese. Arrange biscuits in a single layer over top and sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake until biscuits are golden brown and sauce is bubbly (about 20 minutes).

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Fold in corn flakes and oatmeal.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: grannie's gunk
directions: Mix Jell-O (dry) with pineapple in bowl.
Add cottage cheese and Dream Whip or Cool Whip.
Blend together by hand.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Finely
chop the onion, cucumber and tomatoes.
Mix all ingredients with the cooked spaghetti.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cassava cake #2
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients thoroughly. Pour mixture into foil-lined 8-inch layer pan.
Bake for about 20 minutes or until mixture is almost firm.

title: hot shrimp dip
directions: Soften cheese and butter.
Mix in drained and rinsed shrimp. Add seasoned salt.
Mix all together.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour. Serve with crackers.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Cream together oleo, butter, oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla, then add flour, cocoa, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add 1/2 cup sour milk and mix with creamed ingredients.
Add 2 cups shredded zucchini and 1 cup chopped nuts.
Pour into lightly greased long cake pan and sprinkle 12 ounce bag of chocolate chips on top. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: new england chowder
directions: In large heavy skillet, saute bacon until brown and crisp. Remove; drain on paper towels.
Dice or crumble.
In same skillet, saute chopped onion and potatoes for a couple of minutes.
Sprinkle with flour.
Add broth and stir to combine.
Bring to a boil. Simmer, stirring from time to time, until potatoes are soft, about 15 minutes.
Add half and half; season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add minced clams or slightly cooked shrimp, scallops or any fish of your choice.
Continue to heat just until warm for clams or until shrimp and scallops are firm.
Do not boil.
Add whipping cream.
Sprinkle with parsley and/or diced bacon and serve immediately.

title: crawfish dip
directions: Saut chopped seasoning in butter until clear.
Add in crawfish tails and simmer.
In a mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Add to crawfish mixture and simmer until warm. Serve with "dippables".

title: grandmother's spoon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add liquids and mix thoroughly.
Melt Crisco in Pyrex dish.
Pour in corn meal mix.
Cook in hot oven for half an hour.
Will be consistency of thick pudding.

title: blade steak
directions: Marinate beef in soy sauce and oil at least one hour, turning frequently.
Place all in a frypan and add chopped onions, peppers and celery.
Cook 1 1/4 hours, covered, and stirring frequently.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: county potato and ham chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, combine potatoes, celery, onion, bouillon and water. Cover and cook on medium heat for 20 minutes until potatoes are almost tender. Combine milk, flour, salt and pepper. Slowly add to potatoes along with ham. Cook, stirring, until thickened, about five minutes. Add cheese and stir until melted. Serve hot.

title: cheeseburger chili
directions: Saute beef and onions until beef has lost its pinkness. Add tomatoes, kidney beans and liquid, salt, chili powder and curry powder.
Stir
until
thoroughly
blended.
Simmer over moderate heat
for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot, topping each serving with 1/4 cup shredded cheese.

title: kisses
directions: Heat oven to 225°.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Continue beating until stiff and glossy.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Drop heaping teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet that has been lined with brown wrapping paper.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Serve with any fresh vegetables.
Will keep in refrigerator for up to two weeks.

title: peanut butter and corn flake balls
directions: Cook sugar and syrup to boiling.
Turn off.
Add peanut butter.
Stir until smooth.
Mix in corn flakes and roll mixture into small balls.
(Double this recipe for a larger crowd.)

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Make graham cracker crust per directions on package.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip together.
Spoon into pie crust.
Spread blueberry pie filling over top.
Refrigerate.
Serves 24.

title: aunt mary's cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, vanilla and salt.
Dough may be crumbly.
Let stand a few minutes until it holds together.
Chill.
Roll or press.
Bake at 350° until barely brown.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together in a bowl; blend well.
Drop by spoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes until edges are golden brown.

title: "pumpkin face" cheese puffs
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread and mix well.
Cut bread into pumpkin shapes with a cookie cutter.
Spread each slice with cheese mixture.
These may be frozen at this point.
Bake fresh or frozen at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 36 (3-inch) pumpkins.
Makes 100 (2-inch) rounds.

title: cream puffs
directions: In medium saucepan, place water, oleo and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour all at once; beat well until mixture leaves the sides of the pan.
Cool for 1 minute, add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Mixture should be smooth and glossy.
Make 1 1/2-inch mounds on greased baking sheet, 2 inches apart.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking 30 minutes or until shells are golden brown.
Make a slit in side, cool and fill with filling.

title: strata
