directions: Spread bread cubes in a greased 8-inch square casserole pan. Add shredded cheese on top of bread. Beat egg and milk together. Pour over cheese and bread.
Let stand for 2 hours (make sure casserole is placed in refrigerator).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: creamy tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package; drain.
Mix noodles, tuna, mushrooms, pimentos, sour cream, milk, salt and pepper in a 2-quart casserole.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese and margarine; sprinkle over tuna mixture.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven until hot and bubbly, 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: chocolate wacky cake(no eggs)
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients. Add vanilla, vinegar and oil.
Pour water over top and stir quickly. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cool and dust with confectioners sugar sifted over a doily stencil. Remove stencil. Enjoy the pattern on your cake.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine ingredients, except bacon.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Arrange bacon slices over beans.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Uncover; bake 20 minutes longer. Serves 4.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs.
Add as much flour as you can.
Add vanilla and apples.
Add rest of flour and nuts.
Bake in angel food cake pan (do not grease pan) at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients; stir in shortening, egg and milk just until blended.
Fold in berries last.
Fill greased or paper lined muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: graham cracker torte
directions: Set aside.
Beat 2 egg whites till stiff.

title: different chicken salad
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions without salt. Meanwhile, combine yogurt, mayonnaise, curry powder, salt and ground ginger in a large bowl.
Add chicken, oranges, grapes, celery and onion to dressing mixture.
Drain noodles and add to chicken mixture; toss gently to combine.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour before serving.
Makes 8 (1 cup) servings.
Contains 305 calories and 8 g fat per serving.

title: one skillet spaghetti
directions: To ground beef add onions and peppers.
Stir in tomatoes, green beans and mushrooms.
Add rest of ingredients, breaking up the spaghetti.
Stir well to separate spaghetti.
Cook in covered electric skillet until spaghetti is tender.

title: christmas candy
directions: Melt all 3 chocolates together in a warm oven or in the top of a double boiler.
Just get warm, not hot.
Keep stirred.
When all is melted and stirred smoothly, add nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let cool and set.
Makes a lot of clusters.

title: sweet and sour sauce(for stuffed egg rolls)
directions: Combine ketchup, sugar, water and vinegar in wok and bring to a boil. Add dissolved cornstarch and stir constantly until thickened.

title: spanish casserole
directions: Brown the meat over high heat.
Add sliced onions, peppers, salt and pepper and tomatoes to meat.
Lower temperature and cook slowly until meat is tender.

title: taco potatoes
directions: Peel and dice potatoes into large microwave-safe dish. Sprinkle salt and garlic salt over potatoes.
Cook on High 20 minutes or until tender. Dot with butter pats and cook until melted. Stir in the shredded cheese until melted.
Serves 6 to 10.

title: wild rice and chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions and set aside.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add flour.
Stir until smooth.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute the onion and garlic.
Add the meat and brown.
Drain, then add the salt, oregano, fennel, basil, sugar, puree and paste. Simmer on low 1 hour.
Beat the eggs and combine with the Ricotta cheese.
Cook the lasagna noodles as directed with a little oil. Drain, wash and cool to handling.
Put in layers in pan the noodles, sauce, Mozzarella, dots of Ricotta and Parmesan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes and cut.

title: margarita pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium bowl; press onto bottom and up side of 9 inch pie plate.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Mix all items together by hand.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken-macaroni salad
directions: Prepare elbow macaroni according to package directions; drain. In medium bowl, combine macaroni, chunk chicken and next 4 ingredients.
Mix well.

title: creamy italian baked ziti
directions: Cook ziti and set aside. Cook spinach just until thawed and drain. Combine dressing, Ricotta cheese, Parmesan, milk, nutmeg and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese. Stir in noodles, spinach and all other ingredients together in a large casserole and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350° until lightly browned.
Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella cheese and let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix onion, water, salt and pepper in blender.
Add to meat, bread crumbs and eggs.
Prepare into walnut size balls.
Bring cranberries and tomato puree to a boil.
Add meatballs.
Simmer about 1 hour.
Shake pan during cooking.
Serve over rice.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, brown sugar, eggs, salt, oleo, milk and vanilla.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In large saucepan, cook sugar, syrup and water until it reaches hard ball stage.
Add peanuts and cook until golden brown. Add butter and vanilla.
Stir until mixed well.
Add soda.
Stir well and pour onto buttered cookie sheet.

title: sausage egg casserole
directions: Slice 2 eggs into a 1 1/2-quart dish.
In saucepan, melt butter; blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk all at once. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles. Stir in sausage and corn; pour over sliced eggs.
Slice remaining 2 eggs.
Arrange eggs over top of sausage mixture.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add egg, vanilla and milk.
Blend in flour.
Mix together well.
Roll out on floured table and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for about 7 to 9 minutes.
(Put on ungreased cookie sheet.)

title: mandarin souffle
directions: Put mandarins in blender and process until smooth.
Add enough sugar to sweeten.
Whip egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, continue beating until whites form soft peaks.
Melt the margarine in a saucepan, stir in the flour.
Blend mandarins into the margarine and flour.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, add the egg yolks, grated mandarin peel and liqueur.
Carefully fold the whites into the souffle.

title: "dump-it" cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and stir well.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
When cooled, cut into squares and top with Cool Whip.
Especially good if served when slightly warm.

title: homemade jelly rolls
directions: Place dough in bowl and cover.
Place it in a warm place until it rises.
Spread melted butter or margarine on waxed paper. Stretch the dough out into a loaf, then flatten enough to spread some of the butter or margarine onto it, then spread jelly on this.
Cut into small strips and twirl them into rolls. Sprinkle sugar on top before baking. Bake at 350° until golden brown. Yields 2 dozen.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Soak rice overnight. Mix soups and milk. Put rice in bottom of large baking dish. Pour enough soup mixture to moisten rice. Place chicken over rice and pour remaining soup over chicken parts. Sprinkle onion soup over top. Cover with foil. Bake at 300° for 2
to 2 1/2 hours.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mash bananas; add sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients, butter (melted) and raisins. Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Combine beans and seasoning mix.
Spread mixture evenly in a 9x13-inch dish.
Layer the remaining ingredients as follows: sour cream, olives, tomatoes, onion, green chilies and cheese. Top with salsa.

title: hawaiian smoothie
directions: Blend all ingredients in a blender. Makes 2 servings.

title: amish dressing
directions: Mix uncooked sausage and rest of ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Soak slices in salt water for about one hour.
Drain slices and pat dry.
Dip slices in beaten egg and roll in crumbs until well coated.
Fry in hot fat (or deep-fry) until well browned on both sides.
Serve with catsup and tomato sauce.

title: french shortcake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and egg yolks.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture with milk and 1 teaspoon vanilla; mix well.
Pour batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar and 1/4 teaspoon vanilla.
When whites reach a peak, fold in 1 cup sugar. Spread on top of unbaked cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with strawberries or any fresh fruit.

title: roux
directions: Melt lard in large kettle over fairly high heat.
Blend in flour and lower heat and keep stirring and working the roux about 1/2 hour.
It will mellow and brown slowly, so raise and lower heat as needed.
Keep eye on roux but don't have to stir non-stop. Roux will mellow as honey color to butterscotch to rich rust brown and have a "halo" sheen.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook rice separately according to directions on package.

title: simple salisbury steak
directions: Mix 1/4 soup and add meat, bread crumbs, egg and onion.
Shape into 6 oval patties.
Brown.
Add remaining soup and mushrooms. Cover and simmer until done.

title: charcoal grilled swordfish(mediterranean style)
directions: Make a marinade of ingredients.
Wipe steaks with marinade. Let them soak 2 to 3 hours refrigerated or 45 minutes at room temperature.
Turn several times to make sure steaks are well coated.
Cook about 4 inches above coals for 5 to 6 minutes. Turn; baste and cook another 4 to 5 minutes.
Baste again with pastry brush before removing from grill.

title: amaretto mousse cheesecake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs with melted butter.
Press into bottom and up sides of 9-inch spring-form pan; chill.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Put ingredients in a large pot in the order listed.
Boil on low for 20 to 25 minutes.
Very easy and very good.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Brown okra in a little butter until light brown.
Place okra in a deep cooker.
Brown the flour.
Add salt and pepper.
Add water to make a gravy; mix with okra.
Add onion, diced bell pepper and the ham.
Add tomato paste and 3 cups water.
Cook on low for 2 hours, then add shrimp.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Serve over rice with bread.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Wash and skin chicken breasts.
Stir diluted cream of chicken soup and water until smooth.
Pour over chicken breasts placed in a rectangular baking dish large enough so pieces of chicken aren't crowded.
Sprinkle paprika on top; bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.
Serve with rice.
You have your chicken, plus your gravy from the soup.

title: sausage rice soup
directions: Brown sausage, onion, pepper and celery.
Drain. Add kidney beans, tomatoes, juice and cooked rice.
Let simmer.

title: oatmeal no-bakes
directions: In a large pan, boil first 4 ingredients for 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper and allow to cool.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Mix together beef, bread crumbs, salt, pepper, eggs, onion and 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Form into loaf and bake in 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Grease baking dish.
Brown bread in margarine.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Then mix all together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: white trash
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate chips.
Stir in peanut butter, mix well.
In a large bowl, mix cereal with peanut butter/chocolate mixture until cereal is well coated.
Let stand in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Put cereal mixture and powdered sugar into a large bag and shake until well mixed.

title: potato casserole
directions: Wash potatoes and slice; do not peel.
Boil until slightly tender, but do not overcook.
Drain potatoes and pour melted margarine over potatoes.
Layer in casserole dish the potatoes, cheese and bacon bits.
Cook in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening. Add rind of 1 lemon. Beat in eggs one at a time.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder and add to mixture alternately with milk. Add nuts.
Pour into 9 x 5 greased pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place 6 slices of bread in bottom of casserole; dot with margarine.
Brown 1 pound of sausage.
Drain and sprinkle over bread.
Sprinkle 2 cups grated cheese over sausage.
Mix 6 eggs, 1 pint half and half (2 cups) and dash of salt and pepper.
Pour over cheese.

title: strawberry christmas salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add strawberries and pineapple.
Chill until thickened.
Add bananas.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into a 9 x 11-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Spread with sour cream.
Pour remaining gelatin mixture on top.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares to serve.
Yield:
9 servings.

title: kraut salad
directions: Drain kraut and cut up with scissors.
Mix all ingredients and place in covered bowl.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving. Keeps indefinitely when refrigerated.

title: 5-layer casserole
directions: Break ground beef (uncooked) into pieces and spread into 9-inch baking dish.
Spread mushroom soup over meat; sprinkle onion soup mix over mushroom soup; sprinkle Cheddar cheese over onion soup mix.
Place Tater Tots on cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pat's squash garden
directions: Cut squash approximately 1/8-inch thick.
Chop or cut onion. Add garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Saute in large covered skillet until tender.
Add V-8 juice.
Do not cover.
Simmer until V-8 juice has cooked into the squash.
Remove from heat.
Place on serving dish and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese as little or as much as you like.

title: fresh lime cookies
directions: With electric beater, cream butter and sugar.
Beat in salt and lime juice.
Add flour with a wooden spoon.
Chill until firm. Shape into 2 (4-inch-long) rolls; chill until firm enough to slice.
Cut into thin (about 1/8-inch) slices.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Sprinkle with sugar and lime rind.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: spice cake
directions: Cream sugar, oleo and egg yolks.
Add all other ingredients. Last, add egg whites, well beaten.
Pour into greased and floured pan(s).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a casserole dish. Cook at 400° for 20 minutes in a covered casserole dish. Serve hot.

title: settlers beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer, the longer the better.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Cream shortening.
Add sugar, mixing well after each addition.
Add chocolate and potatoes until blended.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk, beat well until smooth.
Fold in nuts and pour into pan (greased and floured, 11 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 50 minutes, until cake springs back when touched.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Arrange chicken, skin side up, in a single layer in a shallow dish.
Combine soy sauce, sherry, sugar, garlic and ginger; pour over chicken.
Marinate in refrigerator, turning once or twice, for 2 hours.

title: easy lime pie
directions: Mix together condensed milk, lime concentrate and Cool Whip. Add a little yellow or green food coloring, if desired.
Pour into pie shell.	Refrigerate.
Serve garnished with mint leaves and a strawberry.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: *Could substitute 1 shell with bacon bits, 1 with just cheese, etc.

title: round steak casserole
directions: Coat meat with flour, melt shortening and brown meat.
Add onions, cook until onions are tender.
Pour meat into ungreased casserole dish and sprinkle with flour, salt, pepper and garlic. Pour 2 cups water over, mix and bake for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°, covered.
Take out of oven, add potatoes, sprinkle with salt and pepper and return to oven at 450°, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1/2 cup melted margarine and graham crackers.
Pat into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Beat eggs, powdered sugar and margarine with an electric mixer, no less than 15 minutes.
Spread over graham cracker crust.
Cover with bananas and pineapple.
Top with whipped topping.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts or coconut and chopped cherries.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: nanny's peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugars and butter together. Add beaten eggs and mix. Add flour and mix.
Beat peanut butter into mixture and add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Add oil.
Mix flour, baking powder and soda together.
Add cocoa and vanilla.
Mix alternately with the hot water.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown onion and hamburger.
Add other ingredients and simmer for at least 1 hour.
Serves 4 small or 3 large.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Trim leaves from broccoli and clean.
Cut into bite-size pieces and place in large bowl.
Add bacon, onions and raisins. Combine mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Mix well.
Stir into broccoli combination and mix well.
Chill well.
Serves 6.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except apples and cook until thick. Slice apples into unbaked crust.
Pour mixture over apples and sprinkle 10 packages of Sweet 'N Low over apples.
Put top crust on and bake in 400° oven for 45 minutes.

title: 1000 island with beets
directions: Blend all of the above in a blender.
This makes the most beautiful color of pastel lavender you have ever seen.
Not only is it a beautiful dressing, but it's also quite tasty.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: chocolate chip coffee ring
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 9-inch tube pan.

title: economy cake
directions: Boil first five ingredients 5 minutes, then let get entirely cool and add remaining ingredients.
Mix and bake in regular cake pan at 325° until it tests done.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a full, rolling boil.
Boil for 6 minutes.
Add soda and vanilla.
Stir and pour over popped corn. Stir and pour on buttered cookie sheet.

title: paula's punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ginger ale, and freeze.
When ready to serve, put into large punch bowl; pour ginger ale over it.

title: delight dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, place pineapple.
Spread over pineapple, sugar and nuts.
Sprinkle over that the cake mix (just out of box with nothing added).
Melt butter and dribble over top of mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: savory turkey rolls
directions: Combine 1/4 cup celery soup, stuffing mix, cranberry sauce, nuts and water in small bowl.
Place about 1/2 cup stuffing mixture on narrow end of turkey slice.
Roll up and fasten with toothpick.
Arrange one roll up along edge of 8 x 8-inch square microsafe dish.
Combine remaining soup and poultry seasoning and pour over roll-ups.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes until turkey is tender, rotating dish 1/2 turn after 4 minutes.
Let stand, covered, 2 minutes.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 250° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate bananas(a brazilian treat)
directions: You will need wooden sticks.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: In large saucepan, combine marshmallow cream, sugar, evaporated milk, butter and salt; bring to full boil over moderate heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly, over moderate heat.
Remove from heat.
Add Nestle real milk chocolate morsels and Nestle semi-sweet morsels.
Stir until morsels melt and mixture is well blended.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into aluminum foil-lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill in refrigerator until firm.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds candy.

title: beef barley soup
directions: Brown beef in oil.
Add 8 cups water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Dissolve bouillon in hot water. Add to meat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer 1 hour and 15 minutes or until meat and vegetables are tender.
Add small amounts of water, if needed.
Remove bay leaf. Yields 2 1/2 quarts.

title: tagliarini
directions: Chop the pepper and onion.
Brown in olive oil.
Add the hamburger and brown. Add chili powder. Salt and pepper to taste. Add tomato sauce.
Cook the noodles according to package directions. Combine noodles, corn and meat mixture.
Chop olives into small pieces and add to mixture. Save a few whole olives for top.
Grate cheese and sprinkle on top.
(I mix at least half of the cheese in with the meat mixture.)
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn oven off and let casserole remain in oven for 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: In small mixing bowl, beat eggs, milk, syrup and nutmeg.
Set aside.
Cut bread into thick slices, making every other slice to, but not through, the bottom to make pockets (8 to 10 pockets).

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Add all ingredients to salad.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: savannah lo boil
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large pot; let it boil on low heat until all is done.

title: sugar cookies(delightfully tasty any way you bake 'em!)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).
Lightly grease baking sheets. Combine Quick Mix and sugar in a medium bowl.
Blend well.
In a small bowl, combine milk or water, egg and extract.
Add to dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Drop by teaspoons onto prepared baking sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until lightly browned.
Makes 30 to 36 cookies.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat
the
3 egg yolks well.
Add sugar, flour, 1/2 cup milk and a pinch of salt.
Mix.	Add to 1 1/2 cups of milk in double boiler.
Add margarine.
Boil custard until thickened. Add coconut
and vanilla.
Pour in baked pie crust.
Top with meringue.

title: french toast sticks
directions: In a bowl, add all ingredients except bread and butter.
Beat well; set aside.
Slice the bread and cut in strips.
Soak bread in egg mixture.
Melt butter in griddle or skillet.
Place strips of bread in pan and brown on each side.
Serve with your favorite syrup.

title: crust or baked dumplings
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt, Crisco and milk to make a dough.
Roll dough on floured board to 1/4 inch thick and cut into 2 inch squares.
Place in broth,
add pepper and butter.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 475 degrees.

title: easy cherry cobbler
directions: Combine 3/4 cup sugar, cornstarch and 1/2 cup reserved cherry juice in saucepan; heat until it becomes bubbly and thickened. Mix in cherries and place in casserole pan.

title: pink cloud salad
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple, saving the cherry juice.
Beat cream cheese and cherry juice.
Cut up the cherries into small pieces and add to mixture.
Continue adding the following, mixing well after each addition, the pineapple, marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Mix well and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: peppered corn bread
directions: In a bowl, combine the cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda; set aside. Combine the eggs, corn, buttermilk and oil; stir into the dry ingredients just until blended. Fold in the cheese, peppers and onions. Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean. Cut into squares; serve warm. Yield: 12 to 16 servings.

title: breakfast egg casserole
directions: Layer bread, ham and cheese twice.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Pour over layers.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 55 to 70 minutes.
Serves 6 for breakfast.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Slip out yolks of eggs.
Mash with fork.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refill whites with egg yolk mixture, heaping it up lightly.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: pollo relleno
directions: Place each chicken piece between Saran wrap and pound lightly until 1/8 inch thick.
Mix cornmeal and taco seasoning together. Beat egg in another bowl.
Put 2 chili pepper halves on chicken, then one cheese stick.
Sprinkle with cilantro and both kinds of pepper.
Fold up sides, roll up jelly style.
Dip rolls in egg, then coat with cornmeal mix.
Put rolls seam down in uncovered pan.
Bake at 375° for 30-45 minutes, or until center of roll is done.
Sprinkle with extra cheese during the last 5 minutes of cooking.
Serve with salsa if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: santa fe appetizer
directions: Blend cream cheese & sour cream in a bowl. Spread evenly in shallow serving platter. Spread salsa over top to within 1 in. of edge. Sprinkle cheddar cheese around edge of platter. Sprinkle tomatoes, green pepper, onion & olives in bull's eye pattern over cream cheese layer. Chill until serving time. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops.
Place on top of rice in bottom of deep casserole.
Place thick slice of onion on each pork chop, then a slice of tomato and a slice of green pepper on each pork chop, then salt and pepper.
Pour the pork chop drippings over this, then pour the beef consomme mixed with a half can of water over all.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil water, sugar and cornstarch until thick.
Add jello. Cool, then add strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip, Dream Whip or ice cream.

title: spinach dip
directions: Defrost and drain spinach, blot with paper towels to absorb excess moisture.
Stir all ingredients together in mixing bowl. Refrigerate covered bowl overnight.
Excellent served with fresh, raw vegetables (carrot sticks, celery sticks, broccoli, cauliflower, cucumber slices).
Also excellent filling for baked potatoes.

title: ricotta quesadillas
directions: Combine cheeses in a bowl.
Divide mixture evenly between 4 tortillas.
Top with remaining tortillas.
Preheat oven to 300°. Heat nonstick skillet over medium heat and cook until lightly browned on both sides, 1 to 2 minutes.
Transfer to cookie sheet and keep warm in oven.
Repeat with remaining Quesadillas.
Cut into quarters before serving.

title: spinach and cheese bake
directions: Mix milk, flour, eggs, baking powder, salt and melted butter well, then add cheese, spinach and onion.
Butter well an oblong baking dish; pour in and bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: saltwater taffy
directions: Butter the sides of a 2 quart saucepan.
In it combine sugar, corn syrup, 1 cup water and 1 1/2 tsp salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking to 265° without stirring.
Mixture should boil gently over entire surface.
Remove from heat; stir in butter or margarine.
Add flavoring and food coloring, if desired.
Pour into a buttered 15 x 10 x 1 inch pan.
Cool about 20 minutes or until easily handled. Butter hands and pull candy until difficult to pull.
Cut into fourths; pull each piece into a long strand about 1/2 inch thick. With buttered scissors, snip taffy into bite size pieces.
Wrap each in clear plastic wrap.
Store overnight.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds of taffy.

title: lemon gelatin punch
directions: Boil sugar and water and add to gelatin, mixing well.
Add lemon juice, pineapple juice, almond extract and ginger ale.
Add enough water to make 6 quarts.
Chill.
Pour over Ice Ring in punch bowl.

title: divinity
directions: Combine first four ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Cook without stirring to 248° or until small amount forms a firm ball when dropped into very cold water.
Just before syrup reaches 248°, beat egg whites stiff, but not dry.
Slowly pour one-half of syrup over egg whites, beating constantly.
Cook remainder of syrup to 272°, or until small amount separates into hard, but not brittle, threads when dropped into very cold water.
Slowly beat into first mixture, beating constantly until mixture holds its shape.
Blend in vanilla.
Stir in nuts.
Drop from tip of spoon onto wax paper.
Makes about 1 1/4 pounds.

title: yummy cheese ball
directions: Form into ball, roll in finely chopped pecans and serve with crackers.

title: oatmeal crunch cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls and bake at 350° until brown.

title: scarborough casserole
directions: Saute together mushrooms and onions.
Add chopped meat and cook until redness disappears.
Put these ingredients into large bowl; add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and place in greased casserole.
Put bread crumbs and paprika on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° uncovered.

title: sherbet
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender, adding ice cubes last to make the thickness you like.

title: flourless chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Butter the bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Place a 12 x 12-inch sheet of waxed paper in the pie plate and butter the waxed paper.
In a medium saucepan, combine chocolate chips, butter, sugar, water and coffee granules. Heat over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes or until mixture is melted and smooth, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and allow to cool slightly.
Stir in eggs until mixture is smooth.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake 10 minutes; the cake will not be completely set in the middle.
Cool. Cover loosely, then chill 6 to 8 hours or overnight.

title: duck and walnut salad
directions: Combine duck and onions in a bowl.
Mix mandarin peel and dressing, pour over duck and onion.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
In a small skillet, heat butter over moderate heat.
Add garlic salt and walnuts, saute until nuts turn golden brown, stirring frequently.
About 1/2 hour before serving, combine mandarin segments with duck and dressing mixture.
Add more French dressing if necessary.
Salt and pepper to taste, serve duck mixture on lettuce leaves, top with sauteed nuts.
Serves 6.

title: perky nuts
directions: Mix sugar with cinnamon and salt, then add water with egg white. Stir well.
Pour nuts in and stir until all nuts are coated.
Bake on cookie sheet at 250° for 1 hour.

title: crock-pot swiss steak
directions: Layer onion, meat and tomatoes in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: rosalie's fruit tart(elegant but easy!)
directions: Mix milk, sour cream and pudding.
Fold in whipped cream.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: In baking dish, arrange broccoli; top with chicken.
Combine soup and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine butter and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until hot.
Microwave for 6 minutes on High until hot, rotating dish.
Cover with wax paper.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1 small can French fried onion rings or 2 cups corn flake crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 60 minutes.
This may be made ahead and frozen before baking.
Enjoy.

title: corn chowder
directions: Melt the margarine in a pan.
Layer the celery and onion in pan and cook until transparent.
Add the carrots and potatoes, cut up really small.
Add water, just enough to barely cover the potatoes and carrots.
Cook until mushy, about 20 to 30 minutes. Add the corn and milk (however much you want for a nice thickness).
Cook until warm and eat!

title: bailey burgers
directions: Place ground chuck in a large mixing bowl.
Add ginger, soy sauce, onions and pepper.
Mix together well.
Squash garlic through garlic press into mixture.
Blend well.
Form mixture into patties and cook on grill, in oven or Jet Stream to preference. Top with desired burger toppings.
Makes 8 burgers.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add mashed bananas and nuts. Add flour and milk and beat well.
Grease and flour pans.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for about 1 hour and 30 minutes if you use a tube pan and about 1 hour and 10 minutes if you use 2 large loaf pans.
Sometimes, I freeze one for later.

title: french applesauce cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in a large mixing bowl; beat for 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool in pan (upright) for 15 minutes and remove.
Dust with confectioners sugar when cool. Keeps very well in refrigerator for days and also freezes well.
